tes and hypertension — are associated with 164 million lost workdays per year, at a cost to employers of $30 billion.\r\n\r\n• Obesity-related diseases account for an estimated $147 billion a year—half financed through Medicare and Medicaid.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Might be adding some positive facts.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Workplace Health Facts', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '44-revision-4', '', '', '2012-08-28 16:50:26', '2012-08-28 16:50:26', '', '44', 'http://delica.websitewelcome.com/~sterling/?p=48', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
