INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('357', '1', '2012-08-28 17:04:02', '2012-08-28 17:04:02', 'Health screenings are an essential step in a comprehensive wellness program.  Lab work and biometric screenings can provide accurate data for participants and employers from which to create a benchmark to measure improvement and success.  Coupled with our Health Park program and HRA’s, lab and biometric screenings create the basis for a wellness initiative focused on results. Sterling feels strongly that every program participant should “know their numbers” and gain a better understanding of how to affect lifestyle changes based on identified risk factors.\r\n\r\nSterling specializes in comprehensive testing that focuses on complete health management. Screening packages, including finger stick and venipuncture options, can be customized to fit the needs of your company.  Our friendly and certified screening technicians can conduct screenings at your business to reduce lost time and ensure accurate reporting. Our team will load all results into the individual’s Health Risk Assessment and Electronic Personal Health Record.  Employers have the benefit of accurate screening data through our comprehensive aggregate reports.  These blind reports provide a better understanding of the overall health of your workforce, giving the information needed to target risk areas while respecting the privacy of individual participants. Offsite screening options are also available.\r\n\r\nAs with all results gathered by Sterling, responses are strictly confidential. Our experienced screening technicians place priority on respecting the privacy and confidentiality of each participant. Results are processed in CLIA-certified laboratories, providing results that are respected by doctors.  As an advocate of physician/patient relationships, participants can authorize Sterling to share results with a personal healthcare provider.', 'Health Screenings', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '31-revision-4', '', '', '2012-08-28 17:04:02', '2012-08-28 17:04:02', '', '31', 'http://delica.websitewelcome.com/~sterling/31-revision-4/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
