INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('422', '1', '2012-09-24 19:25:34', '2012-09-24 19:25:34', '<h2>An in depth look to your population\'s health.</h2>\r\nSimply completing a wellness screening is not enough. It’s how you use the comprehensive information you receive from the screenings and HRAs that makes the change. Our aggregate reports provide an in-depth look at your population’s overall health. Employers groups of 50 or more will receive a confidential aggregate summary report with an analysis of health risks including population profiles, identification of high risk participants, year-to-year comparisons, and participation tracking. Sterling’s confidential aggregate reporting respects the privacy of participants and follows HIPAA disclosure regulations. Reports can be broken down by location, job status and demographics.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Comprehensive aggregate reporting includes:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Population and demographic report<ins cite=\"mailto:Kayla%20Link\" datetime=\"2012-08-10T16:27\"></ins></li>\r\n	<li>Biometric and lab results</li>\r\n	<li>Lifestyle results</li>\r\n	<li>Readiness to change</li>\r\n	<li>Health status by risk group</li>\r\n	<li>Preventive exam compliance</li>\r\n	<li>Chronic disease impact</li>\r\n	<li>Future disease risk and predictive modeling</li>\r\n	<li>Trend reporting</li>\r\n	<li>Quarterly health coaching reports and utilization</li>\r\n	<li>Physician referral reports</li>\r\n	<li>Incentive tracking report</li>\r\n	<li>Participation report</li>\r\n	<li>Daily activity reports for screenings</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nSterling will also facilitate satisfaction surveys either through online survey tools or paper surveys at the completion of the screening process or the contract year.  This helps identify areas for improvement and gives participants a voice in the process.\r\n\r\nA Return on Investment (ROI) depends greatly on the type and quality of wellness programs being implemented. Health management style programs, such as