INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('818', '14', '2011-04-19 18:32:49', '2011-04-19 18:32:49', '<strong>Read about Sterling Wellness in the news! Sterling Wellness Solutions was recently featured in the Crowley Chamber of Commerce member spotlight. </strong><strong><a href=\"http://www.crowleychamber.com/PageDisplay.asp?p1=3059\">Click here</a> </strong><strong>to go to the Crowley Chamber of Commerce website to view the article, or read the article </strong><strong>below: </strong>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/sterling-team-11.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-298\" title=\"sterling team 1\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/sterling-team-11-300x214.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"214\" /></a>\n<div>Nestled into a beautifully renovated but somewhat unassuming office on Mill Street is the March Chamber member of the month, Sterling Wellness Solutions. Owners Claire and Keeffer Kelbaugh started the business in New Orleans in August 2001, then moved toCrowley in2003. With 25 employees in their Crowley and Thibodeaux offices, Sterling Wellness offers comprehensive worksite health management solutionsto companies consisting of 50 employees to 8,000 employees. Sterling services companies in Louisiana, Texas, Mississippi and has recently branched out into the national market with groups based inAtlanta, Georgia and Miami, Florida.</div>\nSterling Wellness Solutions is dedicated to reducing the cost of employer\'s health care by educating employees and their dependents about how to manage their health risk factors. Their comprehensive selection of wellness services provides clients with a complete health management solution. Services includeonsite health screenings and preventive lab testing, onsite and telephonichealth coaching, health risk profile analysis,incentive plan design and tracking, health challenges, online action plans, electronic personal health records, aggregate analysis and reporting, and a variety of onsite and online health education tools. Sterling also offers individual lab testing services through our nationwide clinical lab network at a discount with no physician order required. Sterling\'s goal for every client is to reduce healthcare costs and keep individuals out of the hospital by improving the employee\'s quality of life, decreasing absenteeism and increasing employee productivity, morale and longevity.\n\nThe Chamber is proud to recognize Sterling for the service they provide to their clients, ultimately resulting in reduced costs and a higher quality of life for all. Additionally, we recognize them for the many ways they give back to the community. They have been strong supporters of the Chamber. In addition to sponsoring and attending numerous Chamber events, Claire and Keeffer have served on planning committees for Gumbo Cook-offs and the Acadia Parish Health Fair. They are members of the Crowley Town Club, with Keeffer serving on the Board of Directors and Claire serving as the General Coordinator for the 2011 Mardi Gras ball. Keeffer is also a member of Kiwanis, currently serving as Vice President. They are strong supporters of the local arts and are also members of the Crowley Art Association.\n\nSterling\'s local staff pictured above Charles Mayeux, Claire Kelbaugh, Chamber Secretary Melinda Malmay making the presentation, and Keeffer Kelbaugh; (second row) Heidi Schmid, Marie Francis, Carmen Valentin, Jaclyn Beaty, Heather Hedrick; (back row) Annette Rosinski, Liz Alleman, Jennifer Witmer, Jessica Habetz; not pictured is Casey Lejeune.', 'Sterling Wellness Spotlight', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sterling-wellness-spotlight', '', '', '2011-04-19 18:32:49', '2011-04-19 18:32:49', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=296', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('819', '14', '2011-05-01 05:00:11', '2011-05-01 05:00:11', 'Congratulations to Sterling Wellness Solutions for becoming the first recognized \"Babies in the Workplace\" company in Louisiana. Sterling has created a baby friendly environment for new mothers wanting to bring their infant to work by providing a safe and nuturing space for feedings, diaper changes, and privacy. To see a complete list of Baby-Friendly workplaces across the country, <a href=\"http://www.babiesatwork.org/companies.html\">click here</a>.', 'Sterling Becomes a \'Baby-Friendly\' Workplace', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sterling-becomes-a-baby-friendly-workplace', '', '', '2011-05-01 05:00:11', '2011-05-01 05:00:11', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=300', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('820', '14', '2011-07-15 04:00:29', '2011-07-15 04:00:29', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/organic.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-322\" title=\"organic\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/organic.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"126\" height=\"126\" /></a>“Organic” seems to be a buzz word these days, but is it really worth the extra money? You be the judge. Many foods claim to be organic or made with organic ingredients, but what does that even mean?\n\nSince 2002, the USDA has set standards that food manufacturers must adhere to if they label their product as organic. An inspector from the USDA must examine farmers, their animals, animal feed, soils, and growing practices to determine if their final product can be labeled as organic. Organic foods are free from pesticides, antibiotics, synthetic ingredients, dyes, and growth hormones. Produce grown in organic soil has been shown to have more nutrients due to the nutrient rich soil. Pesticides, chemicals, and growth hormones have been linked to many conditions such as cancers, food allergies and ADHD.\n\nGenerally speaking, you typically don’t need to pay the extra cash for produce with thick skins or rinds that get pealed or aren’t eaten. This includes bananas, melons, pineapple, broccoli, and mango. However, it may be worth shelling out a few extra bucks for milk, meat, eggs, and produce with thin skins such as berries, peaches, and bell peppers.\n\nAlthough you may pay more, there are cheaper alternatives such as joining a farmers co-op, buying locally, or shopping at farmers markets. For more information visit the <a href=\"http://www.organicconsumers.org/\">Organic Consumers Association</a>.', 'Ins and Outs of Organic', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ins-and-outs-of-organic', '', '', '2011-07-15 04:00:29', '2011-07-15 04:00:29', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=321', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('821', '14', '2011-06-17 04:00:40', '2011-06-17 04:00:40', '[caption id=\"attachment_352\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"171\" caption=\"Don&#39;t leave home without your sunscreen, wide-brimmed hat, and sunglasses!\"]<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/sunshine11.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-352 \" title=\"sunshine11\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/sunshine11-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"171\" height=\"143\" /></a>[/caption]\n\nSummer is here, and so is the sun! Take care of your skin now, and your looks will thank you later. Aside from wrinkles and sun spots, the sun can cause skin cancer, the most common form of cancer in the United States.\n\nAs the CDC recommends, “When in the sun, seek shade, cover up, get a hat, wear sunglasses, and use sunscreen” If possible, avoid the bright sun from 10am-4pm. Seek shade during this time, or cover up wearing tight knit clothing, a wide brimmed hat and sunglasses. Wear a sunscreen of SPF of 15 or higher with both UVA and UVB coverage. It takes the average adult about an ounce of sunscreen to cover their body, roughly the size of a golf ball. Reapply after two hours, after swimming, and after sweating.\n\nFor more information visit the <a href=\"http://www.cdc.gov/cancer/skin/\">Centers for Disease Control</a>.', 'Sunshine, Summer Time, and Skincare', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sunshine-summer-time-and-skincare', '', '', '2011-06-17 04:00:40', '2011-06-17 04:00:40', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=329', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('822', '14', '2011-06-01 04:00:43', '2011-06-01 04:00:43', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/office-stretches1.jpg\"></a>\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_346\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"190\" caption=\"Walkstation, PediBike, and Ab Chair\"]<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/workplace-workouts-image1.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-346\" title=\"workplace workouts image\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/workplace-workouts-image1-190x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"190\" height=\"300\" /></a>[/caption]\n\nThe average adult sits for 8-10 hours a day. Almost 60% of Americans are overweight or obese. Sitting at a computer desk all day can increase the risk for diabetes, metabolic syndrome, heart disease, arthritis, and certain types of cancer. Here are a few tips to preventing the dreaded “secretary spread” and whittling the waistline while you work.\n\n1)      <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Walkstations</span>- Although somewhat pricey, walkststions are a perfect way to move during the day. By walking just two MPH, one can burn up to 800 calories a day. With a computer monitor and phone hooked up to the station, there is no need to remain stationary during the day. Visit the <a href=\"http://www.steelcase.com/en/products/category/tables/adjustable/walkstation/pages/overview.aspx\">online walkstation store</a> to learn more about availability and prices.  \n\n2)      <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Ab Ball Chairs</span>- Ab balls force proper posture and spinal alignment. They can also help strengthen abdominal muscles and burn calories. Ditch the slouching office chair and start your office fitness fun today. Learn more about the benefits and pricing <a href=\"http://www.gaiam.com/product/exercise-ball-ballanceball-chair.do\">here</a>.\n\n3)      <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Under the Desk Bikes</span>- Improve circulation and burn calories by peddling a <a href=\"http://lifehacker.com/263136/under+the+desk-pedal-exerciser\">micro bike</a> under your desk. This innovative machine will keep you moving during the day without getting up from your seat.\n\n4)      <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Follow the 60-60-60 Rule</span>- Every 60 minutes, walk 60 feet away, and do 60 seconds of stretching. Start at your head/neck and work your way down to your toes. Don’t forget to stretch your wrists and hands to prevent carpel tunnel. Follow along with this <a href=\"http://http://www.mayoclinic.com/health/stretching/WL00030\">Mayo Clinic slideshow</a> to learn great workplace stretches and <a href=\"http://daq.state.nc.us/employee/safety/ergo_stretch.pdf\">ergronomic stretches</a>.  \n\n<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/walkstation.jpg\"></a><a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/pedibike.png\"></a><a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/ab-chair.jpg\"></a>', 'Workplace Workouts', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'workplace-workouts', '', '', '2011-06-01 04:00:43', '2011-06-01 04:00:43', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=337', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('823', '14', '2011-08-02 04:00:37', '2011-08-02 04:00:37', '[caption id=\"attachment_355\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"121\" caption=\"Choose foods closest to their natural state, and avoid processed junk foods\"]<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/clean-eating.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-355\" title=\"clean eating\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/clean-eating.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"121\" height=\"169\" /></a>[/caption]\n\nThe concept of <strong>Clean Eating</strong> is not a new one. Dating back to Biblical times, populations were instructed to avoid eating unclean animals. Although the idea of clean eating has evolved slightly, it is still a highly sought after and recommended way of eating.\n\nClean eating recommends limiting or completely <strong>eliminating highly processed and packaged foods</strong> that are likely high in chemicals, fillers, food dyes. It encourages nutrient dense foods grown out of the ground and from plants.  A clean eating diet contains <strong>plenty of whole grains, legumes, fruits, vegetables (organic when possible), low fat dairy products, and lean clean meats</strong>. Eating clean includes drinking plenty of filtered water while <strong>avoiding soda, sugary drinks, and alcohol</strong>.\n\nAlthough this concept may be daunting to some, it is best to start small. Begin incorporating clean foods into just one meal a day and work your way up. Slowly rid your cabinets of processed and packaged foods. <strong>Learn to read food labels</strong>; generally speaking, the shorter an ingredient list is, the better. Avoid products that contain ingredients that you can\'t pronounce. The further the food is from its natural state, the more ‘dirty’ it is considered (think fresh organic strawberries vs. strawberry poptarts).\n\n<strong><em>Browse </em></strong><a href=\"http://www.cleaneatingmag.com/\"><strong><em>Clean Eating recipes</em></strong></a><strong><em> and learn more about the </em></strong><a href=\"http://eatcleandiet.com/what_is_the_eat-clean_diet.aspx\"><strong><em>Eat Clean diet</em></strong></a><strong><em>.</em></strong>', 'Clean Eating', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'clean-eating', '', '', '2011-08-02 04:00:37', '2011-08-02 04:00:37', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=354', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('824', '14', '2011-10-01 04:02:45', '2011-10-01 04:02:45', '[caption id=\"attachment_364\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"140\" caption=\"Support the Cure\"]<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/breast-cancer-ribbon1.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-364 \" title=\"breast-cancer-ribbon\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/breast-cancer-ribbon1-216x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"140\" height=\"197\" /></a>[/caption]\n\nIt is likely you or someone you know has been affected by breast cancer. This year, we celebrate 25 years of October being National Breast Cancer Awareness Month. As with any cancer, early detection is key to successful treatment.\n\nThe American Cancer Society recommends all women over the age of 20 perform a regular breast self exam each month. Women in their 20s and 30s should have a clinical breast exam as part of their physical screening every one to three years. Finally, women 40 and older should have a mammogram every year.\n\nThere are many lifestyle factors you can follow to help prevent breast cancer. Exercise 45-60 minutes at least 5 days a week, maintain a healthy weight, and limit alcohol intake.\n\n<strong><em> </em></strong><strong><em>To learn more or give back, visit the </em></strong><a href=\"http://www.nbcam.org/\"><strong><em>National Breast Cancer Awareness</em></strong></a><strong><em> website, the </em></strong><a href=\"http://www.cancer.org/\"><strong><em>American Cancer Society</em></strong></a><strong><em>, or the </em></strong><a href=\"http://ww5.komen.org/\"><strong><em>Susan G. Komen foundation</em></strong></a><strong><em>.</em></strong>', 'National Breast Cancer Awareness Month', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'national-breast-cancer-awareness-month', '', '', '2011-10-01 04:02:45', '2011-10-01 04:02:45', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=362', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('825', '14', '2011-07-01 04:00:16', '2011-07-01 04:00:16', '[caption id=\"attachment_374\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"153\" caption=\"Bottom&#39;s Up!\"]<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/water.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-374\" title=\"water\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/water-240x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"153\" height=\"172\" /></a>[/caption]\n\nIf water is truly the <a href=\"http://www.cdc.gov/healthywater/drinking/nutrition/index.html\">most essential nutrient</a>, then why do so many  avoid it? Water is essential for lubricating joints, regulating body temperature, and excreting waste through urination, perspiration, and bowel movements.  \n\nAs the thermometer rises, it is important to make sure our water intake rises too. As a rule of thumb, you should drink half your body weight in ounces of water. For example, a 150lb person should drink around 75 ounces of water a day.  \n\nWhat about soda, coffee and tea? Unfortunately, carbonated and caffeinated drinks don’t count. Caffeine works as a diuretic actually dehydrating you more. Choose liquids you can see through such as 100% fruit juices and decaf tea.\n\nCarry a water bottle everywhere you go, and squeeze a slice of lemon, lime, orange or even cucumber for a refreshing drink. Most fruits and vegetables have a high water content as well, so eat up!', 'The Most Essential Nutrient', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-most-essential-nutrient', '', '', '2011-07-01 04:00:16', '2011-07-01 04:00:16', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=373', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('826', '14', '2011-06-06 20:03:43', '2011-06-06 20:03:43', 'Join Sterling Wellness Solutions on Friday, June 17th from 6:30am to 10:00am at 210 W. Mill St. in Crowley, LA for the annual <a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Friends-and-Family-Event.pdf\">Friends and Family Event</a>. Get your complete wellness panel for just $50 a person (retail $529!). Please call 337-783-7840 by June 12 to schedule your appointment.\n\nThe complete wellness panel includes a lipid profile, glucose, comprehensive metabolic panel, thyroid, and complete blood count.  Please fast for 8-10 hours prior to your screening and drink plenty of water. All participants will receive a confidential copy of their results within 5 business days of testing and will receive a telephonic lab review with a health coach. Additional testing is available at minimal cost. Click <a href=\"../wp-content/uploads/2011/06/2011-Friends-Family-Flyer.pdf\">2011 Friends  Family Flyer</a> for a cost list of additional screenings.', 'Friends and Family Health Screening', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'friends-and-family-health-screening', '', '', '2011-06-06 20:03:43', '2011-06-06 20:03:43', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=380', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('827', '14', '2011-09-15 21:11:32', '2011-09-15 21:11:32', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/egg-pic.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-434 alignright\" title=\"egg pic\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/egg-pic-224x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"205\" height=\"274\" /></a>There’s a reason ‘incredible’ is often the adjective used to describe edible eggs. Coming in at only 70 calories per large egg, these gems are packed full of the highest quality of protein of any food. This protein can help build and repair muscle tissue, satisfy appetite longer, and even help with weight management. Eggs are home to a long list of vitamins and minerals including vitamin B 12 that can help with energy levels, and folate, which is an essential vitamin for pregnant women.\n\nAlthough eggs are nutritional royalty, a debate continues to exist over the cholesterol content in their yolks. Despite 100% of the cholesterol being found in egg yolks, the yellow center is also home to most of the calcium, iron, zinc, choline and vitamins A, D, E, and K. The recommended daily limit on cholesterol is 300mg, and one large egg has about 213mg. Therefore, those concerned with their cholesterol levels may consider just using egg whites, cholesterol free egg substitutes, or limiting other sources of cholesterol throughout the day.\n\nAs an affordable and convenient food, you can eggperiment different ways to cook them; hard-boiled, over easy, or scrambled. For other recipes and more nutrition facts, <a href=\"http://www.incredibleegg.org/\">click here</a>.', 'Eggcellent Food Choice', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'eggcellent-food-choice', '', '', '2011-09-15 21:11:32', '2011-09-15 21:11:32', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=433', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('828', '14', '2011-10-28 21:48:10', '2011-10-28 21:48:10', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Halloween is the kickoff to a seaso<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/candy-corn.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-455\" title=\"Candy Corn for Halloween\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/candy-corn-239x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"136\" height=\"172\" /></a>n of indulging in our fair share of sweets and seasonal favorites. Depriving yourself of festive treats can lead to overeating later, so plan ahead with what candies you will chose to eat. Choose 1 or 2 bite size chocolates, a tootsie pop, or 10 pieces of candy corn all for around 75 calories. If you want to do your heart a favor, opt for dark chocolate or a handful of nuts, both of which contain anti-oxidants.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Halloween can also be a good time to teach children (and adults!) moderation and healthy eating. Instead of traditional candies, pass out 100 calorie packs of crackers, granola bars, or bags of popcorn. Another option is to pass out non-food related items like stickers, pencils, or a small play dough.</p>', 'Have a Healthy Halloween', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'have-a-healthy-halloween', '', '', '2011-10-28 21:48:10', '2011-10-28 21:48:10', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=454', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('829', '14', '2011-11-07 20:19:06', '2011-11-07 20:19:06', 'November is American Diabetes Month. <a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/Walking-dog.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-463\" title=\"Young Couple Walking Dog\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/Walking-dog-186x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"186\" height=\"300\" /></a>Roughly 79 million Americans are at risk for developing <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=otbu8wdab&amp;et=1108317184344&amp;s=2757&amp;e=001bXaUG_B2z1z8_ViEy2I4bEBh7oYYVcThxtayVckuMVkeC_eQQILa1MkwMx5s7Fz6p8swM07mUCRpIMWuaG81drCZZ3RavQH0oIZ-FDtIs6gdWE8NgguIrO9g2ctTEZelunjaQ-L87CN1ujvjowzFRsLj91Faa0D1nqJNrjhB23_dWlsyOmU3x_J_-Z6_NfJrHSQEBe7LRwu-9mXZaZ8FMqxsGsjmOGJ_aazWtg_McmM8t-tJfat19XLMo8auZXIJgPYqdBzfuaGVjbTjuSvJfw==\" target=\"_blank\">type 2 diabetes</a> at some point in their life. It is estimated that by the year 2050, 1 in 3 Americans will have diabetes. This month, it\'s time to rally together to offer support for those with diabetes and promote the prevention of this costly and deadly disease.\n\nThe onset of type 2 diabetes can be prevented or delayed through a healthy lifestyle. Obesity is one of the biggest risk factors for diabetes, so maintaining a healthy weight and staying physically active is essential. A healthy diet also plays a big role in prevention. Include complex carbohydrates such as whole grains and plant-based foods such as fruits and vegetables. Avoid sugary foods such as soda, candy and desserts, as these can cause a rapid spike in blood sugar and also contribute to weight gain. To learn more about diabetes, visit the <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=otbu8wdab&amp;et=1108317184344&amp;s=2757&amp;e=001bXaUG_B2z1zCU8S7CMUswTipDqVKJOJoeSpEprSCrymvGJiJZG_wTCLreC2V-d8OcxuwKMhXk354vYvLTHaDx_XwW4Elirlo42NEOQcN9KGdIOYQyKznIKKAmHqgq1jQ8p62WllOfGaHx232pNCv3A47Elwift8kYfhJoIEzzC-C3NZXxXMjrYT6gViHGJn7_MJ1G3i0GvSIhsIe6vCOTwvoPZoWtMp-\" target=\"_blank\">American Diabetes Association</a>.\n\nIf you are interested in supporting efforts to stop diabetes, join the movement and <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=otbu8wdab&amp;et=1108317184344&amp;s=2757&amp;e=001bXaUG_B2z1wE2lDkNd9QWJeHoy-yq5NbiWbN5NzOHR2MSeR-g8GQlmPTwafjLg_g3ZHyXzI1blTSmQCWpZLJVMcqWhYJ3tW8vOaPlBQqinG1WqYpoIWrBxHSLI2rJWuyonrGafn0gUmIjBBbnCA7QWAcS-VArNIXDLIXdQEnUKdNry6njn0BdzLSjyHU0AfS5zjKJFo_wcMmGQHCqVTfdQP7RovyGWzoWPL0rpfQz1pZUk9DZuydrwJUfkzx207ieBZV4CG8SjRzPHkOUV1EyLyc01Yyn1iAhY2AwDOBBy7NqPOeZU6CJeUNcrzx9N6b5iI-koVnXQ0so7VhH1Qj0GOjijoa0WNUUzUkHM5ggDaHGKw3T-zhHA==\" target=\"_blank\">Step Out to Stop Diabetes</a>. Participate in one of the many Step Out walks happening across the country this month. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=otbu8wdab&amp;et=1108317184344&amp;s=2757&amp;e=001bXaUG_B2z1wE2lDkNd9QWJeHoy-yq5NbiWbN5NzOHR2MSeR-g8GQlmPTwafjLg_g3ZHyXzI1blTSmQCWpZLJVMcqWhYJ3tW8vOaPlBQqinG1WqYpoIWrBxHSLI2rJWuyonrGafn0gUmIjBBbnCA7QWAcS-VArNIXDLIXdQEnUKdNry6njn0BdzLSjyHU0AfS5zjKJFo_wcMmGQHCqVTfdQP7RovyGWzoWPL0rpfQz1pZUk9DZuydrwJUfkzx207ieBZV4CG8SjRzPHkOUV1EyLyc01Yyn1iAhY2AwDOBBy7NqPOeZU6CJeUNcrzx9N6b5iI-koVnXQ0so7VhH1Qj0GOjijoa0WNUUzUkHM5ggDaHGKw3T-zhHA==\" target=\"_blank\">Find out where the nearest walk is, and how you can donate or participate for this great cause.</a>', 'Step Out to Stop Diabetes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'step-out-to-stop-diabetes', '', '', '2011-11-07 20:19:06', '2011-11-07 20:19:06', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=462', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('830', '14', '2011-11-17 06:24:17', '2011-11-17 06:24:17', 'Make November 17th Your Day to Quit. <a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/no-smoking.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-467\" title=\"no smoking\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/no-smoking-214x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"138\" height=\"179\" /></a>The American Cancer Society is marking its annual <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=otbu8wdab&amp;et=1108317184344&amp;s=2757&amp;e=001bXaUG_B2z1xnyngwjPYrVs_nTRPjFPhuRFp5jFnMrGtiR8kIAuHKggXp-MzYG8PQcI2J8lDalhhaK8lc5OZKhRudzVnnW1_2PDxDMZ0fhZEsvsVF_51hMNfxCHJT8i7lQdv-Y6kwDkV7QVyMqJr3grBCufWG5y85HUZiZkO3m3xElUMIkrH6cW6jzU2Vj1NQ\" target=\"_blank\">Great American Smokeout</a> on Thursday, November 17th.  The observance encourages smokers to use the date to make a plan to quit, or to plan in advance and quit smoking that day. Nearly every 8 seconds a life is lost due to tobacco, which accumulates to 5 million deaths a year. Roughly 80-90% of lung cancer deaths happen to those who smoke. Smoking harms nearly every organ in the body, and drastically increases the risk for heart disease, COPD, and multiple kinds of cancer. Quitting the habit is not easy, but with a network of support and help from great resources like the American Cancer Society, it is possible. If you are interested in quitting smoking, <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=otbu8wdab&amp;et=1108317184344&amp;s=2757&amp;e=001bXaUG_B2z1yHeokTXT2T4OSOjINUifSfvgSM7Ll10-PBRetJxG7CNNkcGGB6_TqpcxZDdh7vHhQyxj4Zny0FJpAUuItJUKUvAO0kPDdKgyPiUIaZXUis7FueIhXxVlGGjdLiZWBZW88_d-ZMV36NwZ9OFyy3jBsoPiULJJjJ59rMEmU9-drUg95aHSC4DGhH\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> to find the strategy that will work best for you. Join the estimated 46 million Americans that have quit smoking for good, and make November 17th the last day for you.', 'Great American Smokeout- Happening Today!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'great-american-smokeout-happening-today', '', '', '2011-11-17 06:24:17', '2011-11-17 06:24:17', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=466', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('831', '14', '2011-11-22 08:00:12', '2011-11-22 08:00:12', 'As we acknowledge Good Nutrition Month in November, we want to shed light on some of our season<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/Thanksgiving-meal.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-472\" title=\"BXP45536\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/Thanksgiving-meal-240x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"148\" height=\"185\" /></a>al favorites that can take a nutritional twist to decrease calories without sacrificing flavor. Canned cranberry sauce can be alternated with chopped whole cranberries, oranges, and apple bits for a colorful fruit salad with less sugar and more fiber. Pies can be made with less cholesterol by substituting two egg whites for every whole egg. For baked goods like cakes and quick breads, try substituting unsweetened applesauce for oil. Greek yogurt is a great alternative for any recipe calling for cream, sour cream, or mayonnaise. Try this high protein yogurt in mashed potatoes or sweet potato casserole. Steamed cauliflower is an easy addition to mashed potatoes to sneak in an extra serving of vegetables. Removing the skin from the turkey can also cut fat and calories. Make en effort this year to offer healthy sides and low fat desserts, and remember to keep portions in check! Resources such as <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=otbu8wdab&amp;et=1108317184344&amp;s=2757&amp;e=001bXaUG_B2z1zJO0ppXbRmj0oKmP26O5GEVBNaAQFAvRDkyp3HE2OjPxrfuGdYFKHE88muL2LAKX_UCMQxeIK6Fz-AGiQHX-SDYUMFcUzoEfrcbD8XFvhfN-QaTZYYRV-ot0-C2xLDFlKLCN7qEruntpwR6I4Hx7W-wxX9DVuRuTst0WnlB35Yiw==\" target=\"_blank\">Check Your Health</a> and <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=otbu8wdab&amp;et=1108317184344&amp;s=2757&amp;e=001bXaUG_B2z1wLjOh6VYmbud3eQCn4XnMN8Mm0anQ7WbinP6ae1krYU9eozPVujbEIaoOSbaFbyNfs_u-oje0D5Mlxy7CYhBK9JRib8TMvFoC0fnYHcgEmCw==\" target=\"_blank\">The Sneaky Chef</a> offer endless possibilities.', 'Healthy Substitutions for Your Holiday Meal', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'healthy-substitutions-for-your-holiday-meal', '', '', '2011-11-22 08:00:12', '2011-11-22 08:00:12', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=471', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('832', '14', '2011-12-12 19:40:58', '2011-12-12 19:40:58', '[caption id=\"attachment_501\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"160\" caption=\"Happy Hot Cocoa Day!\"]<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/Healthy-Hot-Cocoa.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-501\" title=\"Healthy Hot Cocoa\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/Healthy-Hot-Cocoa-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"160\" height=\"160\" /></a>[/caption]\n\nGood news for hot cocoa lovers- A study from Cornell University reveals winter\'s favorite beverage may have more antioxidants per cup than a glass of red wine or green tea. Cocoa powder is derived from a bean that contains large quantities of the flavonoid, procyanidin. Antioxidants and flavonoids are compounds that have been shown to slow aging and prevent chronic diseases such as cancer and heart disease. The antioxidants in cocoa powder show up in highest amounts in unprocessed chocolate.\n\nMany pre-packaged hot cocoa mixes made from milk solids don\'t contain as many antioxidants and flavonoids as pure dark cocoa powder. For maximum antioxidant benefit, mix one tablespoon of pure organic dark chocolate cocoa powder with one cup of skim milk which adds a bone building dose of calcium and vitamin D. For a healthy variation, try making a batch with soy milk, a sprinkle of cinnamon, or a teaspoon of pure maple syrup. Try this <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=otbu8wdab&amp;et=1108649526741&amp;s=2757&amp;e=001FwiBhLdZEPs2YLJZCCjzS-MEd7OiKb4io4jeU-ta6Byj0nHMoovk4oTfyWomFFcjwllmakXVZbvk56zN3Ygbn2kTPkyvGVlhhu2Y9PuDGP2RSjntBi36imYZ9p08VL91laTJBafFUzeOm_iIopa8vz5yYL4FyGXb\" target=\"_blank\">healthy hot cocoa recipe from EatingWell</a>, and get a tasty dose of antioxidants.', 'Crazy For Cocoa', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'crazy-for-cocoa', '', '', '2011-12-12 19:40:58', '2011-12-12 19:40:58', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=500', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('833', '14', '2011-12-16 08:00:55', '2011-12-16 08:00:55', 'It\'s the season to give<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/christmas-gift.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-509\" title=\"christmas gift\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/christmas-gift-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"203\" height=\"136\" /></a>, and also to receive. Giving and receiving health and fitness related gifts are a great way to encourage physical activity and promote weight loss. Ask for wellness related gifts such as a health magazine subscription, a healthy cookbook, or a body fat analyzing scale. Investing in indoor fitness equipment will prevent excuses when the weather is gloomy. You may consider asking for fitness equipment like dumbbells, workout DVD\'s, a yoga mat, or a gym membership. Your loved ones will become aware of your health and wellness efforts and support you in the process.', 'Give the Gift of Good Health', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'give-the-gift-of-good-health', '', '', '2011-12-16 08:00:55', '2011-12-16 08:00:55', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=508', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('834', '14', '2011-12-21 08:00:16', '2011-12-21 08:00:16', 'According to the Centers for Disease Control, \"the single most important thing you can do to keep f<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/hand-washing.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-516\" title=\"42-15653295\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/hand-washing-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"176\" height=\"176\" /></a>rom getting sick is to wash your hands.\" Although women tend to be healthier hand hygiene warriors, one study showed that only 75% of women and 50% of men washed their hands after using the restroom (and you don\'t even want to know what that statistic was for high school boys; a scanty 8%!). Hand washing may seem like an obvious move after using the bathroom or changing a diaper, but most people don\'t sprint to the sink after sneezing, coughing, handling money, or touching pets. Germs can easily enter the body by touching the eyes or nose, or through food prepared with contaminated hands. The <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=otbu8wdab&amp;et=1108649526741&amp;s=2757&amp;e=001FwiBhLdZEPsSgKWdGO8IfwmoH8afktlX6yGnQVquXj7qLBq3nMUCF2zMZ3y95LCTkrV8hhLRqwhYdYB80igif8OHtObZkn7-Be87ZQbzYx2ZFUhXjLek7kD3qfXeMiRYs_ss1Vof9OhfVnNTs_EBl9F6M44aswq6\" target=\"_blank\">Community Health Centers</a> recommends washing with warm water and soap for 15-20 seconds, long enough to sing the \'Happy Birthday\' song. Wash under the nails, between fingers, and under rings. Once hands are completely dry, turn off the faucet and open the door with a paper towel to prevent recontaminating your hands. Alcohol based hand sanitizers work when a sink isn\'t available, but make sure they contain at least 60% alcohol and rub vigorously for 25 seconds. If you do get a cold or flu, please respect your coworkers by staying home and preventing the further spread of germs.', 'Stay Well this Flu Season', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'stay-well-this-flu-season', '', '', '2011-12-21 08:00:16', '2011-12-21 08:00:16', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=515', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('835', '14', '2012-01-09 19:30:07', '2012-01-09 19:30:07', 'For many people, the New Year will start off with goals to get fit, lose weight, or eat healthy. Instead of failing to keep those resolutions two weeks after they were made, try making them a lifestyle change instead. Follow the tips below to begin a lifetime of vibrant health and wellness once and for all.\n\n1)       Make your health goal something YOU want to do, not something your boss, spouse, or friend wants you to do. Keep the focus on what you want to desire from these goals such as confidence, happiness, or more energy.\n\n<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/Set-Goals-Chalkboard.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-527 alignright\" title=\"Set Goals Chalkboard\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/Set-Goals-Chalkboard-300x235.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"193\" height=\"149\" /></a>2)      Make small changes one step at a time. Instead of attempting a sweeping change with lofty goals, try making incremental steps that build on each other. For example, if you want to start exercising, don’t attempt to run a marathon if you aren’t a runner. Rather increase your workouts by 5-10 minutes each week until you have reached a desired duration.\n\n3)      Write it down! Keep track of your progress in a journal or a piece of paper. This serves as a visual reminder of how far you have come. Post reminders and encouragements on your refrigerator, bulletin board, and bathroom mirror. For added accountability, tell a friend.\n\n4)      Avoid the <em>‘do not’s’</em> and stick to the ‘<em>do’s</em>.’ No one wants to follow a restrictive laundry list of things they shouldn’t do; don’t drink soda, don’t smoke, don’t eat dessert.  Focus on your goals in a positive light instead; drink more water, take stretch breaks at work, eat more fruits and vegetables. These positive behaviors will cascade into healthy habits that won’t make you feel restrained.\n\nThis year, make a life-long resolution to maintain habits of health and wellness.  Eat, drink, and be healthy in 2012!', 'Healthy Weight Month', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'healthy-weight-month', '', '', '2012-01-09 19:30:07', '2012-01-09 19:30:07', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=526', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('836', '14', '2012-01-16 08:00:19', '2012-01-16 08:00:19', '<div></div>\n<img src=\"https://origin.ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/126.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"10\" vspace=\"10\" width=\"221\" height=\"164\" align=\"right\" />\n\nIndoor fitness provides  an off-season outlet to maintain muscle strength, flexibility, and  cardiovascular health when outdoor workouts aren\'t an option. Take your  workouts to your living room floor and invite a family member to join  you. No fitness equipment required! Create your own indoor circuit by  doing 10-20 repetitions of the following exercises; Jumping jacks,  push-ups, crunches, squats, wall sit, and high knees. Repeat this series  3-5 times. After this strength building workout, cool down with a few  flexibility stretches. Start by stretching your head/neck first then  move down the body with shoulder rolls, torso and hip stretches.  Finally, end with a lower body stretch to the quads, calves, and ankles.  To track improvement, log your repetitions and increase duration and  frequency each week. View more <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=otbu8wdab&amp;et=1108980106055&amp;s=0&amp;e=001C77a4OrELQ7UOGzML6gxY7j5z312uX0NtUPZxdEJhINrx62t8gLJCV93IBlbLVyX5JKwJYEwFr8foz8E0I5Hmlr2ulpVVNYiE2__TQFKyN0Ym-FJk7WPBwmBLDIV8rEyW5wreC2bJF6s-ZiO8dbEqAiVGqrYjOC5JE4nf8xEexY=\" target=\"_blank\">Indoor Workout Routines</a> and <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=otbu8wdab&amp;et=1108980106055&amp;s=0&amp;e=001C77a4OrELQ7UOGzML6gxY7j5z312uX0NtUPZxdEJhINrx62t8gLJCV93IBlbLVyX5JKwJYEwFr_UrrP5_vvkBLZ_Ll3ydza0z0mhJRypIWfbxfwN_mOwarF85htNFjBUpjUY9pKAsmdRYSSS9_E1nyBn_ICPvskF-e-2TgTFzsc=\" target=\"_blank\">Stretching Examples</a> here.', 'The Winter-Proof Workout - Take it Indoors Fitness', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-winter-proof-workout-take-it-indoors-fitness', '', '', '2012-01-16 08:00:19', '2012-01-16 08:00:19', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=541', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('837', '14', '2012-01-17 16:04:22', '2012-01-17 16:04:22', '[caption id=\"attachment_656\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"120\" caption=\"Deana Leonard is a Registered and Licensed Dietitian for Sterling Wellness Solutions.\"]<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Deana-Leonard.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-656\" title=\"Deana Leonard\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Deana-Leonard.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"120\" height=\"160\" /></a>[/caption]\n\nA: Practicing proper portion control is one of the best ways to aid in your weight loss efforts. To determine the portions right for you, enter your age, gender, height and weight at <a href=\"http://www.choosemyplate.gov\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">MyPlate.gov</a> and get an estimated daily caloric intake for losing or maintaining your weight. Practice the <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=otbu8wdab&amp;et=1109062225186&amp;s=0&amp;e=0016RizSOMk8x4iwNKrvErLZVrKXV2PULYoxRZo-b7TKGg7cylSXeIEFVgCGW18RSeXEe9QWw0gS2ZACjMJSI3xekcAx-klQR4ApMmh2uSM2Lw=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">MyPlate</a> method by filling half your plate with fruits and vegetables, a quarter with a whole grain or starch, and a quarter with lean meat. Many restaurant portions have more than doubled, so consider sharing an entree or ordering an appetizer while dining out.\n\nFor serving sizes, use this printable <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/diet/printable/portion-control-size-guide\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">portion size table from WebMD</a> as a guide to remembering what a serving size should look like. A serving of meat should be the size of a deck of cards. Compare a serving of fruit to a baseball and a serving of cheese to a stack of three dice. Finally, be cautious with fats. One serving of butter, salad dressing, mayo or oil should only be the size of a poker chip. Consider measuring your servings at home for two weeks to reevaluate how much you are actually eating.', 'Q: \"My depression and anxiety peak during winter months. What can I do to manage it better?\"   ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'q-my-depression-and-anxiety-peak-during-winter-months-what-can-i-do-to-manage-it-better-2', '', '', '2012-01-17 16:04:22', '2012-01-17 16:04:22', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=655', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('838', '14', '2012-01-23 08:36:06', '2012-01-23 08:36:06', 'Practicing  proper portion control is one of the best ways to aid in your weight  loss efforts. To determine the portions right for you, enter your age, gender, height and weight at <a href=\"http://www.choosemyplate.gov/\" target=\"_blank\">MyPlate.gov</a> and get an estimated daily caloric intake for losing or maintaining your weight. Practice the <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=otbu8wdab&amp;et=1108980106055&amp;s=0&amp;e=001C77a4OrELQ7UOGzML6gxY7j5z312uX0NtUPZxdEJhINrx62t8gLJCV93IBlbLVyX5JKwJYEwFr8foz8E0I5HmqpdbNH_x3BTI-_qOI9Ttrqbl1oc_zezsw==\" target=\"_blank\">MyPlate</a> method by filling half your plate with fruits <img src=\"https://origin.ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/134.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" width=\"210\" height=\"180\" align=\"left\" />and vegetables, a quarter with a whole grain or starch, and a quarter with lean  meat. Many restaurant portions have more than doubled, so consider  sharing an entree or ordering an appetizer while dining out.\n\nFor serving sizes, use this printable <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/diet/printable/portion-control-size-guide\" target=\"_blank\">portion size table from WebMD</a> as a guide to remembering what a serving size should look like. A serving of meat should be the size of a deck of cards. Compare  a serving of fruit to a baseball and a serving of cheese to a stack of  three dice. Finally, be cautious with fats. One serving of butter, salad  dressing, mayo or oil should only be the size of a poker chip. Consider measuring your servings at home for two weeks to reevaluate how much you are actually eating.', 'Proper Portion Control', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'proper-portion-control', '', '', '2012-01-23 08:36:06', '2012-01-23 08:36:06', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=538', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('839', '14', '2012-01-27 08:00:07', '2012-01-27 08:00:07', '<div><strong><a name=\"Nutrition\"></a></strong></div>\n<div><a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=otbu8wdab&amp;et=1108980106055&amp;s=0&amp;e=001C77a4OrELQ7UOGzML6gxY7j5z312uX0NtUPZxdEJhINrx62t8gLJCV93IBlbLVyX5JKwJYEwFr-iy4dMEJN88turL9BYwUdp6duQr13HKXK28qfyjDL8gd7Lq0DDJGkVs5XL13rIm5xS7vvmqbrrzrEJOcIaqBcYAL3X2MvzU4Q=\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://origin.ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/125.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" width=\"118\" height=\"178\" align=\"left\" /></a></div>\nConsumers  buy more oatmeal in the month of January than any other month. It\'s the  perfect start to a chilly morning and provides antioxidants, iron and  vitamins for optimal energy through the day. Oatmeal is a complex  carbohydrate and also falls into the category of a whole grain. The  soluble fiber in oats has been proven to lower cholesterol, blood  pressure, and also stabilize blood sugar levels making it an optimal  choice for those at risk for heart disease and diabetes. With less than  100 calories in ¾ cup, oatmeal can control your hunger, making it a  diet-friendly food.\n\nOats  are an inexpensive and versatile ingredient that can be added into  cookies, meatloaf, breads and desserts. Experiment for yourself with one  of these oat recipes from <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=otbu8wdab&amp;et=1108980106055&amp;s=0&amp;e=001C77a4OrELQ7UOGzML6gxY7j5z312uX0NtUPZxdEJhINrx62t8gLJCV93IBlbLVyX5JKwJYEwFr8foz8E0I5HmhyE-l6YdUv3NHsp5yaB-LHMALL2226kJ-i2L1gHgHQGeTHtG4XI8xjeJvaf9jUEgi91zRFgeI_ipxgTBeJzaooC3PSwPAZtGQ==\" target=\"_blank\">Eating Well.</a>', 'January Nutrition Spotlight - Oatmeal Nutrition', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'january-nutrition-spotlight-oatmeal-nutrition', '', '', '2012-01-27 08:00:07', '2012-01-27 08:00:07', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=544', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('840', '14', '2012-02-09 21:21:56', '2012-02-09 21:21:56', 'Lifestyle habits play a crucial role in the prevention and treatment of hypertension. Despite uncontrollable risk factors such as increasing in age and family history, there are many factors you can control.  <a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/blood-pressure-2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright  wp-image-551\" title=\"Doctor Checking the Blood Pressure of a Patient\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/blood-pressure-2-295x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"138\" height=\"140\" /></a>\n<ul>\n	<li><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Exercise-</span></strong> Regular physical activity makes your heart stronger allowing it to pump more blood with less effort. Exercise will also help maintain a healthy weight.  Being overweight or obese is a sole risk factor for hypertension and heart disease.</li>\n	<li><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Nutrition-</span></strong> Reduce sodium in the diet by replacing salt with herbs and spices. Eat a low fat diet consisting of lean meats, fruits and vegetables, and whole grains. Limit alcohol, and don\'t smoke.</li>\n	<li><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Stress Management-</span></strong> During stressful situations, try practicing stress management techniques such as deep breathing, meditation, and yoga. Stressful situations can cause your blood pressure to rise temporarily due to a flood of hormones and narrowing of blood vessels.</li>\n	<li><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Support-</span></strong>  Support from family and friends can help with the changes you need to meet your goal. Share your goals with someone who can hold you accountable. If lifestyle efforts aren\'t enough, your doctor may suggest prescription medication.</li>\n</ul>\nHigh Blood Pressure is often asymptomatic, which is why it\'s called \"The Silent Killer.\" If you are at high risk for hypertension and experience chest pain, shortness of breath, dizziness or blurred vision, visit your primary care provider. A normal blood pressure reading is &lt;120/80mm/Hg. When this number is elevated, it may indicate pre-hypertension. Hypertension', 'Healthy Hearts Against Hypertension', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'healthy-hearts-against-hypertension', '', '', '2012-02-09 21:21:56', '2012-02-09 21:21:56', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=550', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('841', '14', '2012-02-13 08:27:56', '2012-02-13 08:27:56', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/hand-drawing-heart-beat.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-554\" title=\"hand drawing heart beat\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/hand-drawing-heart-beat-300x110.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"197\" height=\"72\" /></a>The Heart is a fascinating organ. According to WebMD, your heart shuttles 2,000 gallons of oxygen-rich blood through about 60,000 miles of branching blood vessels in your body over the course of a day. Your heart is roughly the size of your fist and weighs approximately 10 ounces. As the body\'s lifeline, we must take care of it so it takes care of us. Treat your heart to healthy fats found in fish, walnuts, avocados, and olive oil. Stress and inactivity are big risk factors for heart disease. During stressful times, the stress hormone, cortisol, can cause cholesterol deposits in the arteries to rupture and travel to the heart or brain causing a heart attack or stroke. It may be no surprise to learn that Monday mornings before 10am is the most common time for heart attacks to occur. Lower stress levels through exercise, meditation and laughing. Performing CPR can save a life if you are found in an emergency situation where someone\'s heart has stopped beating. To learn more about a healthy heart or to enroll in a local CPR class, visit the <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=otbu8wdab&amp;et=1109062225186&amp;s=2757&amp;e=0016RizSOMk8x5HE1TMRMOwfWwes0ZeBQD45UtnMN1o62LuzAXRZ-LcCpjxa8q2OYPOFcH-EUDJnlDuw2F5zntiu107ta0dtPxEZrkVklox10MFUW3_s9FwD1eEzJWQPnUF9gZq-H_Dd7E5Y5YtPMHeeDPLZ6L-1uVtceJUwtYxp-qfM_qJzf_27w==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">American Heart Association</a>.', 'And the Beat Goes On... ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'and-the-beat-goes-on', '', '', '2012-02-13 08:27:56', '2012-02-13 08:27:56', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=553', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('842', '14', '2012-02-02 21:31:12', '2012-02-02 21:31:12', 'Depression and anxiety can greatly affect how you function in your everyday life. Many people find the winter months with it\'s cold, overcast <a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/family-fun.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright  wp-image-559\" title=\"CB026240\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/family-fun-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"99\" /></a>days can make the symptoms worse. Exercise is a great way to beat the \'winter blues\'. When you exercise, your body releases endorphins, a chemical found in your brain. When these endorphins are released the body begins to feel more relaxed, less stressed and a more optimistic outlook on life. Most people who take time to exercise also report better sleep patterns. Getting a good night\'s sleep will greatly affect your outlook on the day in a positive way.\n\nExercise can also increase life expectancy. Exercising for 30 minutes a day most days of the week will strengthen your heart, increase your energy levels, and decrease your chances of getting diseases such as diabetes and heart disease.  Everyone can feel better knowing they are adding years to their life with exercise.\n\nDepression and anxiety can be difficult to control at times. If you find that positive thinking, regular exercise and healthy lifestyle choices are not working, talk to you doctor about other options.', 'Beating Winter Blues', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beating-winter-blues', '', '', '2012-02-02 21:31:12', '2012-02-02 21:31:12', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=558', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('843', '14', '2012-02-20 08:43:54', '2012-02-20 08:43:54', 'February\'s food spotlight falls on a seasonal nutrition gem: the grapefruit. Found only in winter months<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/Grapefruit-Chicken-Salad.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-563 alignleft\" title=\"Grapefruit Chicken Salad\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/Grapefruit-Chicken-Salad-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"134\" height=\"134\" /></a>, this citrus fruit is power-packed with antioxidants, vitamins and fiber. Grapefruit is high in antioxidants beta-carotene and lutein which are essential for healthy vision. Red grapefruit varieties contain lycopene, an antioxidant shown to offer protection against certain cancers. This heart healthy food is high in pectin, an insoluble fiber that has been shown to reduce blood cholesterol levels. One half a grapefruit contains a mere 40 calories making it a great option for weight management. Once thought to be solely a breakfast food, their newfound versatility can be added to salads, fish, smoothies and desserts. Browse <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=otbu8wdab&amp;et=1109062225186&amp;s=2757&amp;e=0016RizSOMk8x6EHYXyWpcgmJdK8F0I-8zj91_pycFswFvDdJI2NcDm7lZMWTfs3XtPmcpQQHE-tL8galobzz4VE9zBo2_C95xotzq7-MGzab7qBGmuPBS1hhxyWZ5KqC7n6nmdUFxLSY5a3t2IEuj7nFsWCiUHJO7LjuoU_ndE3NqjWEiVa9j05dtvRTT29bMQbcz7b3GSPAgARmY2WMptmLEWK5XDOmkYE3PiDvcmATikN_s01LhCfg==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">EatingWell</a> for more creative ways to include grapefruit in your diet.\nDespite its health benefits, be cautious when consuming grapefruit with prescription medication. Experts warn of adverse drug interactions or toxic effects if certain medications are taken within 72 hours of grapefruit or grapefruit juice consumption. Contact your physician or pharmacist or view the <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=otbu8wdab&amp;et=1109062225186&amp;s=2757&amp;e=0016RizSOMk8x5tAYmAE9pVUNrBWglTXqQJ0BAZXVWllcaMxXAicpXtOlPppHpOHuWCRMQGpWKRwuKnV1sb_SU4VRqgfw88Hjad3hTz6SESgRb34sdjxAIWggsyh6fGkv5T3eGEN8lYCDH3Ex0WKBbozp1KY8OTUWq4bw_yfFIYxt4=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Mayo Clinic</a> website if you have questions about drug interactions.', 'The Power of Grapefruit', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-power-of-grapefruit', '', '', '2012-02-20 08:43:54', '2012-02-20 08:43:54', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=562', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('844', '14', '2012-02-28 08:48:08', '2012-02-28 08:48:08', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/woman-hiking.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright  wp-image-567\" title=\"woman hiking\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/woman-hiking-199x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"147\" height=\"221\" /></a>The American College of Sports Medicine (ACSM) was on to something when they coined the phrase \"Exercise is Medicine\". Physical activity has been proven to prevent and treat chronic diseases so drastically that many doctors have been able to take their patients off prescription medications. According to the ACSM, research proves that exercise has a role in the treatment and prevention of more than 40 chronic diseases. It\'s no surprise to learn heart disease and hypertension are two conditions considerably affected by exercise. Physical activity, particularly cardiovascular exercise, has been shown to reduce blood pressure, cholesterol levels, and triglycerides while increasing HDL (good) cholesterol levels.\n\nThe Centers for Disease Control (CDC) recommends 150 minutes of moderate intensity aerobic exercise each week. This calculates out to 30 minutes a day, 5 days a week. Include activities such as brisk walking, water aerobics, or riding a bike into your daily schedule for a lower risk for heart disease and hypertension. For more information, visit the <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=otbu8wdab&amp;et=1109062225186&amp;s=2757&amp;e=0016RizSOMk8x63LgujYcPAWqwPEePGzUmSZvLvwyabttAc2KyIL1DCjrxkY9VrOoXXyxzFcAp4IVV7_ZGEXzra9tlQ8vSIhRn-uRMdiNCV5XisrIM3nPJABEWaie-XtYdJYhDVtU_rRQ4=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">ACSM</a> or <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=otbu8wdab&amp;et=1109062225186&amp;s=2757&amp;e=0016RizSOMk8x4LcKwix-ZcJosuix_-nbuLYnPTRKZ1WaZsa0_OS0DtZhdQQNxZ1hT4-s-tvOm2vhJr9LKWU5WMmYbTRm6io-54datqDGjvv0gXrBtj4VWsx5ZiIZtOwADm0ndYtbFydf_pJNjNBaQCOqY8ItLsMHVdQx2JTLEHE83NqXtgLqAD11NlQd8eM8hK\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">CDC</a>.', 'The Cardio Cure', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-cardio-cure', '', '', '2012-02-28 08:48:08', '2012-02-28 08:48:08', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=566', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('845', '14', '2012-03-01 18:30:20', '2012-03-01 18:30:20', 'Every March, we recognize National Nutrition Month, a nutrition campaign created by the Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics. This year\'s campaign focuses on creating a healthy plate by making informed food choices and develo<a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?et=1109362339893&amp;s=0&amp;e=001Mi4thZJMp15bBTiufjCn4ELWE_CVJ1Ls9ii-RaBrDMGXv6pF9RPNirDwxntDG8u8nGhh9Tpi2mhxhA29_nSPYgAPIVAmIiQ1o5meOyvFRFotzaZG3fx54q6Gy5Xfhknv\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://origin.ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/171.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.171\" width=\"206\" height=\"199\" align=\"left\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></a>ping physical activity habits:\n\n<strong>Make hal</strong><strong>f your plates fruits and veggies-</strong>  Eat a variety of colorful fruits and vegetables during meals and snacks.\n\n<strong>Switch to fat free or low fat milk-</strong> The calcium and vitamin content is the same as higher fat dairy products.\n<div><strong> </strong><strong>Cut back on empty calories</strong><strong>-</strong> Added sugar, salt, and saturated fats sneak into our food products. Reduce intake of soda, packaged and processed foods, and high fat desserts and fast food.</div>\n<strong>Be physically active</strong>- Move more. Find an activity you enjoy and log at least 2 hours and 30 minutes of exercise each week.\n\nFor more information visit the <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?et=1109362339893&amp;s=0&amp;e=001Mi4thZJMp15bBTiufjCn4ELWE_CVJ1Ls9ii-RaBrDMGXv6pF9RPNirDwxntDG8u8nGhh9Tpi2mhxhA29_nSPYgAPIVAmIiQ1o5meOyvFRFotzaZG3fx54q6Gy5Xfhknv\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics</a> or <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?et=1109362339893&amp;s=0&amp;e=001Mi4thZJMp15bBTiufjCn4ELWE_CVJ1Ls9ii-RaBrDMGXv6pF9RPNirDwxntDG8u8nGhh9Tpi2mhVZL7woS-kogkrkk5CspcO1UvvlcVZbO7nzxOu9HnQtBrh5tD8j9muI_v4EOodOQArGIjO-oslimB1WDgH4s5XinPhUtUwrdmhNingOQgEbQ1upwCiDYSAsTsjYe0W1tI=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">download this printable health tips sheet</a>.', 'Get your Plate in Shape  - March is National Nutrition Month', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'get-your-plate-in-shape-march-is-national-nutrition-month', '', '', '2012-03-01 18:30:20', '2012-03-01 18:30:20', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=572', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('846', '14', '2012-03-12 18:35:08', '2012-03-12 18:35:08', '<table width=\"119\" align=\"right\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\" width=\"119\"><img src=\"https://origin.ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/168.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.168\" width=\"109\" height=\"148\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"0\" vspace=\"0\" /></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n<div><em>Support awareness by going blue</em></div></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\nEarly detection is the best way to prevent colon cancer. Colon cancer is the third leading cause of death due to cancer in America. The American Cancer Society recommends all people over the age of 50 get a colonoscopy every 10 years. Knowing your family history may determine if you need a colonoscopy before the age of 50. If you or someone in your immediate family has a history of inflammatory bowel disease, colon cancer, or digestive problems, a colonoscopy may be recommended at an earlier age. During a colonoscopy screening, the doctor is able to remove polyps or pre-cancerous lesions and send them off for a biopsy. Polyps are generally benign in early stages, but if left undetected, they may grow into cancer. If an abnormal test is returned, a patient may be asked to have a repeat colonoscopy in two to five years. For more information on colon cancer screenings, visit the <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?et=1109362339893&amp;s=0&amp;e=001Mi4thZJMp15bBTiufjCn4ELWE_CVJ1Ls9ii-RaBrDMGXv6pF9RPNirDwxntDG8u8nGhh9Tpi2mhxhA29_nSPYgPfGsNFi5O1ttjSz5O2SRJUiK-RfSoscvYXN4lEVwbMLI1xdB0UDybuFwSQW8amPw==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Centers for Disease Control.</a>', 'Colorectal Cancer Screenings Save Lives', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'colorectal-cancer-screenings-save-lives', '', '', '2012-03-12 18:35:08', '2012-03-12 18:35:08', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=576', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('847', '14', '2012-03-04 18:37:02', '2012-03-04 18:37:02', 'It may be no surprise to learn that the National Sleep Foundation claims over 60% of Americans suffer from poor sleep. Research proves that adults need 7-8 hours of sleep each night for our bodies to adequately cycle through the 5 stages of sleep at least 3 to 5 times. The impact of inadequate sleep can lead to car accidents, suppressed immune system, marital problems, and irritability. In the workplace, sleep deprivation can lead to decreased creativity skills, frequent colds or sick days, and inability to cope with stress. You may be sleep deprived if you have trouble getting out of bed, fall asleep while watching TV, or get sleepy in meetings, lectures or while driving.\n<div><img src=\"https://origin.ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/170.jpg\" alt=\"Rise and shine feeling rested!\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.170\" width=\"148\" height=\"148\" align=\"left\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"0\" vspace=\"20\" /></div>\n&nbsp;\n\nTo get a good night of rest, avoid computer, TV, and phone screens at least 2-3 hours before bed. Limit your intake of caffeine after lunch, and avoid nicotine, alcohol and eating before bed. Finally, if you cuddle up to a restless sleeper or someone who snores, it may be affecting your sleep. This includes pets and children. If you suffer from serious prolonged sleep issues, consider visiting a sleep specialist. Click here for a <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?et=1109362339893&amp;s=0&amp;e=001Mi4thZJMp15bBTiufjCn4ELWE_CVJ1Ls9ii-RaBrDMGXv6pF9RPNirDwxntDG8u8nGhh9Tpi2mhxhA29_nSPYvYgHsUqAhtVy1inOt7Tzp_aiWTph4TOhypLX6QaEGDobYomZfO8sFIg6Lyf2dTuOSHOB8efcWahXKJyEXMq4EusOPHoV6y11Q==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">list of accredited sleep disorder centers and physicians</a>, and learn more tips for healthy sleep habits from the <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?et=1109362339893&amp;s=0&amp;e=001Mi4thZJMp15bBTiufjCn4ELWE_CVJ1Ls9ii-RaBrDMGXv6pF9RPNirDwxntDG8u8nGhh9Tpi2mhxhA29_nSPYoPuzILpGiu6TuaOe3RjW1dCcjeRJwhUzUOAH0t5cbgs\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">National Sleep Foundation</a>.', 'Good Night, Sleep Tight... Seep Awareness Week is March 4-10 ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'good-night-sleep-tight-seep-awareness-week-is-march-4-10', '', '', '2012-03-04 18:37:02', '2012-03-04 18:37:02', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=581', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('848', '14', '2012-03-21 08:38:20', '2012-03-21 08:38:20', '<div align=\"left\"><a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/Peanut-Butter-Nutrition.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-586 alignleft\" title=\"peanut butter sandwich\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/Peanut-Butter-Nutrition-192x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"99\" height=\"155\" /></a>Did you know that the peanut is not actually a nut but a legume related to beans and lentils? You could say good things come in small packages when referring to these popular shelled bite-sized snacks. Peanuts have a higher antioxidant capacity than grapes, green tea, and tomatoes. As a naturally cholesterol free food, peanuts contain more than 30 nutrients and phytochemicals. America\'s favorite way to eat these gems is undoubtedly in the form of peanut butter. Peanuts and peanut butter provide a great source of protein, folate, and heart healthy monounsaturated fats. For those concerned with peanut allergies, almond butter and cashew butter are great alternatives to peanut butter, providing comparable protein and nutrient concentrations. Whether you like your peanuts raw, boiled, or in a spread, keep moderation in mind. Peanuts and peanut butter are high in calories, so be mindful of serving sizes. Visit the<a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?et=1109362339893&amp;s=0&amp;e=001Mi4thZJMp15bBTiufjCn4ELWE_CVJ1Ls9ii-RaBrDMGXv6pF9RPNirDwxntDG8u8nGhh9Tpi2mhxhA29_nSPYvNVG4JLKkgVRd2lND2-OxNfFLh_r53PgO2FYogNOELivzNK8ECnKcB0dc2lF8f58Q==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"> National Peanut Board</a> for more nutrition facts and recipes.</div>', 'Peanut Packed Nutrition', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'peanut-packed-nutrition', '', '', '2012-03-21 08:38:20', '2012-03-21 08:38:20', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=585', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('849', '14', '2012-03-30 18:40:51', '2012-03-30 18:40:51', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/woman-stretching.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright  wp-image-589\" title=\"young woman exercising in a park\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/woman-stretching-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"144\" height=\"192\" /></a>Stretching has been ingrained in us as part of a necessary physical activity since elementary school PE class. This convenient exercise can be performed almost anywhere, from living room floors to office cubicles. As we age, our muscles naturally lose flexibility and mobility, increasing our need to stretch regularly. Some of the greatest benefits from stretching include a reduced chance of major joint replacement surgeries of the knees, hips, and shoulders. Stretching can decrease the risk of back injuries and workplace traumas like carpel tunnel, tendonitis, and tennis elbow. As if that\'s not argument enough to get flexible, frequent stretching can even reduce the risk of developing osteoarthritis or stiffness and pain in joints, the #1 cause of disability worldwide. Stretch at least 2-3 times a week, and always after exercising once muscles are warm. Click here to view stretching exercises for the workplace.', 'Stretch Away Pain', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'stretch-away-pain', '', '', '2012-03-30 18:40:51', '2012-03-30 18:40:51', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=588', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('850', '14', '2012-03-16 18:42:22', '2012-03-16 18:42:22', 'Our Direct Access Lab Testing is an extremely easy and affordable way to have lab work done. You can order lab work for numerous tests without visiting your physician. Confidential testing allows patients to keep lab results out of their medical records, and away from potential insurers. To order a test, simply log on to <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?et=1109362339893&amp;s=0&amp;e=001Mi4thZJMp15bBTiufjCn4ELWE_CVJ1Ls9ii-RaBrDMGXv6pF9RPNirDwxntDG8u8nGhh9Tpi2mhxhA29_nSPYo4iRGzXz3jX8XQUJfqmZ5Ti6KhtCVAqyiO_VgEoZ9B2\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Sterling Wellness Solutions website</a>, and click on the Sterling Labs tab. The testing categories are listed on the left hand side or you can enter search words in the search box in the upper right corner. Sample tests include general wellness panel, cardiovascular and cholesterol panel, prostate and thyroid testing, STD testing, liver and kidney function, and many more! Add the test you would like to order to the cart and proceed to secure checkout. After you checkout, print the order and bring it with you to any<img src=\"https://origin.ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/173.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.173\" width=\"138\" height=\"91\" align=\"left\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> LabCorp in the U.S. and have blood work drawn. Some tests may require you to fast for 8-10 hours prior to getting screened. Results are printed in our central office and an experienced nurse or health coach will contact you with the results within 2-3 business days. A copy of your results can either be securely emailed or mailed directly to you. For more information about our Direct Access Lab Testing services call 1.800.838.0337 or visit our <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?et=1109362339893&amp;s=0&amp;e=001Mi4thZJMp15bBTiufjCn4ELWE_CVJ1Ls9ii-RaBrDMGXv6pF9RPNirDwxntDG8u8nGhh9Tpi2mhxhA29_nSPYo4iRGzXz3jX8XQUJfqmZ5Ti6KhtCVAqyoKUPuXGVxXkhj5m0jf3b-M=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Sterling Labs page</a>.', 'Direct Access Lab Testing', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'direct-access-lab-testing', '', '', '2012-03-16 18:42:22', '2012-03-16 18:42:22', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=591', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('851', '14', '2012-03-23 19:27:19', '2012-03-23 19:27:19', '[caption id=\"attachment_603\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"170\" caption=\"Rene L., 26 Dallas, TX\"]<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/Rene-Leger.png\"><img class=\"wp-image-603  \" style=\"border-style: initial; border-color: initial;\" title=\"Rene Leger\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/Rene-Leger-237x300.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"170\" height=\"216\" /></a>[/caption]\n\n\"I hadn\'t gotten blood work done before, but I wanted to check the current status of my health.  I called Sterling Wellness to discuss what type of lab work I should get done to test all of my levels.  Jessica was a big help in explaining which tests I should run and what the results would tell me.  I ordered my labs at a location in Dallas, TX and was in and out in 10 minutes.  I got a call from Sterling 2 days later to go over the results with me to let me know what they meant.  Turns out everything\'s great!  Couldn\'t be more pleased with the results and how the process was handled.  It was very comforting to speak to someone about my results in the comfort of my home and who could answer all of my questions.  I highly recommend Sterling Wellness for lab work.\"\n<div>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n</div>', 'Direct Access Lab Testing Testimony', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'direct-access-lab-testing-testimony', '', '', '2012-03-23 19:27:19', '2012-03-23 19:27:19', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=602', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('852', '14', '2012-04-03 15:21:41', '2012-04-03 15:21:41', 'Although everyone experiences stress at some point in their lives, the perception of the stress plays a big part in the emotional and physical response. Stress affects the immune system and can contribute to obesity, heart disease, stroke, and high blood pressure. To manage the stress in our everyday lives, consider the following techniques:\n\n<strong>Evaluate the Situation-</strong>  It\'s easy to exploit a minor situation into a five-alarm frenzy. Ask yourself if this is really something worth stressing over. Will worrying get you anywhere?\n\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/relaxing1.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-617 alignleft\" title=\"Enjoying life\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/relaxing1-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"270\" height=\"180\" /></a></strong>\n\n<strong>Be Physically Active</strong>- Move. Find an activity you enjoy, and schedule it into your calendar. Exercise burns anxious energy and releases feel good endorphins to improve your mood. There\'s a reason they call it the \'runner\'s high.\'\n\n<strong>Choose and Lose-</strong> Choose your priorities wisely, and lose the rest. Write down the things that matter most to you and rank them in\n\norder of which ones deserve your most attention. Determine what is important to you, and don\'t get stressed out over the things that aren\'t.\n\n<strong>\nPractice Stress Relaxation Techniques-</strong> Deep breathing, yoga, mindful meditation, and prayer can all clear the mind of clutter. Consider setting an alarm or chime to go off every hour as a reminder to take 5-10 slow deep breaths, and do slow neck and shoulder stretches to relax tension.\n\nFor more information on stress relaxation techniques, visit the <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001e0BjQliEB_Qj_dFaQvi1s-l6maZYvnt1XHgnJJNtnihFNTCDC_nn0wQYgDZzYAe4HoI6F4SYIrgW9yXxx0EUR8TxT5rSUQ-6-nUP9zDAmQi-rNovHwDRDg==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">American Institute of Stress</a> or the <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001e0BjQliEB_R645Ud0MzF1b8WBsiCEJP_dwmWfhT7vIQcwf6mA0GNKpwU4fRC22hsYLQwmVt_MuTopFCYvFb2uY7SO_D1YSh8meanjTR7p8B43j6oNNKmZf4IV8tk9q4rrlhIzpjhRLqpJPPUivi1U02K-PohJor3b5_GF43LYlw=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Mayo Clinic.</a>', 'Relief for the Over-Stressed; April is Stress Awareness Month', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'relief-for-the-over-stressed-april-is-stress-awareness-month', '', '', '2012-04-03 15:21:41', '2012-04-03 15:21:41', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=615', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('853', '14', '2012-04-09 15:22:21', '2012-04-09 15:22:21', 'We often talk about the empty calories we consume through our beverages, especially alcoholic ones. The reality is, that consuming too much alcohol can effect more than just your waistline. Like most things in life, moderation is the key to responsible alcohol intake. When choosing a healthier alcoholic beverage, consider red wine for its high antioxidant content, light beer, or mixing equal parts seltzer water and wine to create a low calorie spritzer.<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/alcohol.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright  wp-image-623\" title=\"alcohol\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/alcohol-220x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"176\" height=\"240\" /></a>\n\nOverindulging on a regular basis can take a physical toll on the body leading to liver cirrhosis, high triglycerides, high blood pressure, sleep disorders, and birth defects. So how much is too much?  Heavy drinking is considered 4 drinks a day/14 drinks a week for men, or 3 drinks a day/7 drinks a week for women. Not only does the social isolation of binge drinking and alcoholism effect your health, but it affects those around you as well. Heavy drinking can lead to greater chances of accidents and injuries. If left uncontrolled, alcohol abuse can cause severe depression, anxiety, injury, and even death. Since binge drinking and alcoholism should not be taken lightly, many resources are available if you or someone you know may be a risky drinker. For more information visit <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001e0BjQliEB_RmXBa4_hMgL3eTF3CA4gb8krv3ADhk2ai_qmeq_y9bPqJ3BHs0COeZaePGPrQ5LBwuxLI3JJY_vbBsRJv6pgAPq-JW1ho_CUbPkgUpiOJgkA==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Alcoholics Anonymous</a>, <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001e0BjQliEB_RmXBa4_hMgL3eTF3CA4gb8krv3ADhk2ai_qmeq_y9bPqJ3BHs0COeZaePGPrQ5LBwRL_pS7vOT4kX_Pl_no7KPdPRnhApXO5i_MTr6oBsoTBq_Rx_bPMJ3NXRxDouLYgNUmtLAPFOacwn0uDt2MUEk3Y5zlAwuYDkcq5v0uciuvQ==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">The Help Guide</a>, or <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001e0BjQliEB_RmXBa4_hMgL3eTF3CA4gb8krv3ADhk2ai_qmeq_y9bPqJ3BHs0COeZaePGPrQ5LBwt4Gi_XJlpHe3sX1fFNNQR5hQ6sy8zE9g=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Smart Recovery</a>.', 'How Much is Too Much?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-much-is-too-much', '', '', '2012-04-09 15:22:21', '2012-04-09 15:22:21', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=622', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('854', '14', '2012-04-05 15:25:26', '2012-04-05 15:25:26', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Easter-Baskets.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-626\" title=\"Two Young Girls Sitting with a Basketful of Candy\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Easter-Baskets-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"240\" height=\"240\" /></a>Before little bunny foo-foo hops into your house with baskets of festive sweet treats, consider substituting them for a few healthy alternatives. Although children (and adults!) are drawn to high sugar, high fat, artificially colored food-like substances, try introducing healthier options of snack items and toys in lieu of candy and chocolate. Children are taught by example, so encouraging healthy behaviors at a young age can create a lifetime of positive health habits. Offering kids toys that encourage movement is a great choice. Consider giving games, sports equipment, or puzzles. Sidewalk chalk, sunglasses, and a new swim suit can get a child anticipating the warm months ahead. To satisfy the sweet tooth, opt for dark cocoa instead of milk chocolate, fruit snacks made from real fruit, oatmeal cookies, or rice krispie treats.', 'Healthy Treats for your Peeps   ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'healthy-treats-for-your-peeps', '', '', '2012-04-05 15:25:26', '2012-04-05 15:25:26', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=625', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('855', '14', '2012-04-14 15:30:51', '2012-04-14 15:30:51', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Cooper-Institute.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-637\" title=\"Cooper Institute\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Cooper-Institute-300x172.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"172\" /></a>Sterling Wellness Solutions puts great emphasis in training and equipping its employees to become educated and qualified leaders in the industry. Pictured here are a few of Sterling’s Health Coaches participating in a Health Coaching continuing education certification course at the Cooper Institute in Dallas, TX. The Cooper Institute is internationally known for its groundbreaking research, training, and health promotion in the fitness and wellness field. Visit <a href=\"http://www.cooperinstitute.org/\" rel=\"nofollow nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.cooperinstitute.org/</a> to learn more about their health and wellness resources available to you.', 'Continuing Education for Health Coaches', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'continuing-education-for-health-coaches', '', '', '2012-04-14 15:30:51', '2012-04-14 15:30:51', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=636', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('856', '14', '2012-03-17 15:58:43', '2012-03-17 15:58:43', '[caption id=\"attachment_650\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"120\" caption=\"Jessica Habetz is a Client Services Coordinator and Administrative Associate Team Leader for Sterling Wellness Solutions.\"]<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Jessica-Habetz.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-650\" title=\"Jessica Habetz\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Jessica-Habetz.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"120\" height=\"160\" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<strong><em>A:</em></strong> Our Direct Access Lab Testing is an extremely easy and affordable way to have lab work done. You can order lab work for numerous tests without visiting your physician. Confidential testing allows patients to keep lab results out of their medical records, and away from potential insurers. To order a test, simply log on to <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?et=1109362339893&amp;s=0&amp;e=001Mi4thZJMp15bBTiufjCn4ELWE_CVJ1Ls9ii-RaBrDMG9XEIeJIkXsIHdDeREdhkooGk426sonTSDo9nwXy7EJNqVnwNh8JyL3Bjv8Hnr1uE=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Sterling Wellness Solutions website</a>, and click on the Sterling Labs tab. The testing categories are listed on the left hand side or you can enter search words in the search box in the upper right corner. Sample tests include general wellness panel, cardiovascular and cholesterol panel, prostate and thyroid testing, STD testing, liver and kidney function, and many more! Add the test you would like to order to the cart and proceed to secure checkout. After you checkout, print the order and bring it with you to any LabCorp in the U.S. and have blood work drawn. Some tests may require you to fast for 8-10 hours prior to getting screened. Results are printed in our central office and an experienced nurse or health coach will contact you with the results within 2-3 business days. A copy of your results can either be securely emailed or mailed directly to you. For more information about our Direct Access Lab Testing services call 1.800.838.0337 or visit our <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?et=1109362339893&amp;s=0&amp;e=001Mi4thZJMp15bBTiufjCn4ELWE_CVJ1Ls9ii-RaBrDMG9XEIeJIkXsIHdDeREdhkooGk426sonTSDo9nwXy7EJNqVnwNh8JyLSXC8QzjdQzarRwImKbTPSufdKakXo7dU\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Sterling Labs page</a>.', 'Q: \"I see Sterling offers Direct Access Lab Testing. What is that and how does it work?\"', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'q-i-see-sterling-offers-direct-access-lab-testing-what-is-that-and-how-does-it-work', '', '', '2012-03-17 15:58:43', '2012-03-17 15:58:43', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=649', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('857', '14', '2012-02-17 16:02:38', '2012-02-17 16:02:38', '[caption id=\"attachment_653\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"125\" caption=\"Marie Beechy is a Registered Nurse for Sterling Wellness. Marie specializes in behavioral and mental health issues.\"]<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Marie-Beechy.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-653\" title=\"Marie Beechy\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Marie-Beechy.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"125\" height=\"160\" /></a>[/caption]\n\nA: Depression and anxiety can greatly affect how you function in your everyday life. Many people find the winter months with it\'s cold, overcast days can make the symptoms worse. Exercise is a great way to beat the \'winter blues\'. When you exercise, your body releases endorphins, a chemical found in your brain. When these endorphins are released the body begins to feel more relaxed, less stressed and a more optimistic outlook on life. Most people who take time to exercise also report better sleep patterns. Getting a good night\'s sleep will greatly affect your outlook on the day in a positive way.\n\nExercise can also increase life expectancy. Exercising for 30 minutes a day most days of the week will strengthen your heart, increase your energy levels, and decrease your chances of getting diseases such as diabetes and heart disease.  Everyone can feel better knowing they are adding years to their life with exercise.\n\nDepression and anxiety can be difficult to control at times. If you find that positive thinking, regular exercise and healthy lifestyle choices are not working, talk to you doctor about other options.', 'Q: \"My depression and anxiety peak during winter months. What can I do to manage it better?\"', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'q-my-depression-and-anxiety-peak-during-winter-months-what-can-i-do-to-manage-it-better', '', '', '2012-02-17 16:02:38', '2012-02-17 16:02:38', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=652', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('858', '14', '2012-04-20 15:27:28', '2012-04-20 15:27:28', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Zucchini.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-630\" title=\"Zucchini\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Zucchini-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"240\" height=\"240\" /></a>If you are looking for a flavorful, low calorie, and nutritious addition to your everyday recipes, look no further than the zucchini. Since more than 95% of a zucchini is water, this vegetable can add volume, fiber, and color to our plates without adding calories. Chopped zucchini can easily boost the nutrient content in family favorites like pasta, quick breads, and casseroles. For ideas on incorporating this veggie into your meals, visit <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?t=roaptnjab.0.9bjrrpjab.otbu8wdab.2757&amp;ts=S0746&amp;p=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.health.com%2Fhealth%2Fgallery%2F0%2C%2C20509747%2C00.html\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Health.com\'s 26 Quick and Tasty Zucchini Recipes</a>. When shopping for the perfect summer squash, select the squash with the darkest green skins, since the darker skins hold the highest concentration of nutrients. Always wash, but don\'t peel the skin. The skin houses most of the nutrients like folate, vitamin C, and beta carotene. Zucchini\'s adaptability allows for it to be eaten raw as a snack, sauteed, grilled, or left up to your own imagination to find a new creative way to serve this versatile food.', 'Zucchini\'s Versatility  ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'zucchinis-versatility', '', '', '2012-04-20 15:27:28', '2012-04-20 15:27:28', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=629', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('859', '14', '2012-04-24 15:29:03', '2012-04-24 15:29:03', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/tennis.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-634\" title=\"Man Preparing to Serve Tennis Ball\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/tennis-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"112\" height=\"168\" /></a>Few sports can boast a full-body workout the way tennis can. Due to the nature of the game, tennis can develop mental, physical, and social health. Because tennis requires keen hand-eye coordination, this sport can stimulate concentration, balance, and depth perception. Although this skilled sport may require some patience and practice, even a beginner can gain physical benefits. Playing tennis requires running, lateral movement, upper body rotation, and strong abdominal muscles. The competition of the sport can provide positive camaraderie, accountability, and a social outlet. Tennis leagues are cropping up all over cities and communities. Check with your local Parks and Recreation department or Fitness Club about lessons or leagues, and visit <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?t=roaptnjab.0.8bjrrpjab.otbu8wdab.2757&amp;ts=S0746&amp;p=http%3A%2F%2Fsearch.active.com%2Fsearch%3Fk%3D%26l%3Deverywhere%26f%3Dactivities%26m%3Dmeta%3AendDate%3Adaterange%3Atoday..%2Bmeta%3Achannel%3DTennis\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Active.com</a> for a list of nationwide tournaments for all levels. Tennis is a lifetime sport with low impact on the joints, so it\'s never too late to pick up a racquet and start swinging!', 'Shape Up with Tennis', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'shape-up-with-tennis', '', '', '2012-04-24 15:29:03', '2012-04-24 15:29:03', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=633', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('860', '14', '2012-04-17 15:35:27', '2012-04-17 15:35:27', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Busy-Moms-Cookbook.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-640\" title=\"Busy Mom\'s Cookbook\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Busy-Moms-Cookbook-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"180\" height=\"240\" /></a>Sterling President, Claire Kelbaugh, had the opportunity to meet Top Chef Contestant Antonia Lofaso at the 9th Annual World Health Care Congress in Washington DC. Antonia is currently working on a cookbook with over 100 recipes geared towards busy mothers. “The Busy Mom’s Cookbook” is projected to come out in August and will contain tips and suggestions from her own experiences and those of other celebrity single moms.', '9th Annual World Health Care Congress', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '9th-annual-world-health-care-congress', '', '', '2012-04-17 15:35:27', '2012-04-17 15:35:27', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=639', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('861', '14', '2012-04-22 15:39:16', '2012-04-22 15:39:16', '<strong><em>A: </em></strong> Although these are common symptoms that many of us frequently experience in our fast paced society,\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_646\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"125\" caption=\"Liz Alleman, LPN, is a Nurse and Certified Healthy Behaviors Coach for Sterling Wellness.\"]<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Liz-Alleman.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-646 \" title=\"Liz Alleman\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Liz-Alleman.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"125\" height=\"160\" /></a>[/caption]\n\none has to consider if there is an underlying problem when these symptoms persist and begin interfering with daily life. Several conditions can cause similar side effects, but one possibility is a thyroid disorder.\n\nThe thyroid is a gland in the front of the neck that produces hormones to keep the metabolism working properly. Hypothyroidism occurs when the thyroid cannot make enough thyroid hormones to keep the body functioning as it normally should, therefore slowing down the metabolism. Symptoms of an under-active thyroid include constant fatigue, despite getting the proper amount of sleep, difficulty staying focused, weight gain for no obvious reason, dry skin or brittle hair, and depression.\n\nConversely, the thyroid can also make too much thyroid hormone causing hyperthyroidism. The higher levels of thyroid hormone production leads to the body\'s metabolism working too fast. Grave\'s disease and goiter are common forms. Symptoms include heart palpitations, feeling nervous, weight loss for no reason, hand tremors, perspiration at rest, and bulging eyes.\n\nIf you have one or more of these symptoms that persist, notify your physician. Contrary to some beliefs, thyroid disorders occur in men as well as women. Treatment depends on the symptoms and severity of the condition. Regular follow-ups and blood work are usually performed to ensure that your levels are within normal limits, and to try to get you feeling back to your normal self again.', 'Q: \"I\'ve been experiencing noticeable fatigue and weakness lately. I get adequate sleep at night, but I don\'t feel like I can function without an afternoon nap and some caffeine. It\'s been pointed out to me that my memory has been a little foggy too. Is this anything to worry about?\"', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ask-the-expert-thyroid-help', '', '', '2012-04-22 15:39:16', '2012-04-22 15:39:16', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=645', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('862', '14', '2012-05-03 15:56:24', '2012-05-03 15:56:24', '<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1026\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\n margin-left:0;margin-top:605.25pt;width:176.25pt;height:117pt;z-index:251658240;\n mso-wrap-distance-left:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:3.75pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-right:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:3.75pt;\n mso-position-horizontal:left;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/204.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/204.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.204\" width=\"235\" height=\"156\" align=\"left\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /><!--[endif]-->The heart and soul of any successful company is its employees. In a time of escalating health care costs, unhealthy lifestyles have become costly expenditures on American businesses. Employers around the world are recognizing the benefit of healthy employees, which leads to this movement of workplace wellness. Healthier employees have been shown to be more productive and have fewer sick days and work comp claims.\n\nThis May recognizes <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001MvkEXPYjURgdFaEdPBZ8azCytTj4J9GMhC_RdkhK3VBSbojRgLZdJpF1IVxGPRK5ldQiAl1fZpOBOfZ0daH6NPmiAYcy42kLfhcPiWECj6_Of_BARkNM9KxRI5UNq0lbcZQZ1bbeYww=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Employee Health and Fitness Month</a> by the National Association of Health and Fitness. We encourage you to take advantage of this health observation month by taking simple steps toward health and fitness. Consider stretching breaks before or after meetings, walking meetings, or lunchtime physical activity opportunities. If you or your employer would like help organizing a lunchtime walk, educational presentation, or stretching class, <a href=\"mailto:hhedrick@sterling-wellness.com\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">let us know</a>!', 'Healthy Employees, Healthy Company-  May is Employee Health and Fitness Month    ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'healthy-employees-healthy-company-may-is-employee-health-and-fitness-month', '', '', '2012-05-03 15:56:24', '2012-05-03 15:56:24', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=665', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('863', '14', '2012-05-06 16:01:11', '2012-05-06 16:01:11', '<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1027\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\n margin-left:339.55pt;margin-top:831pt;width:170.25pt;height:112.5pt;z-index:251658240;\n mso-wrap-distance-left:0;mso-wrap-distance-top:0;mso-wrap-distance-right:0;\n mso-wrap-distance-bottom:0;mso-position-horizontal:right;\n mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;mso-position-vertical-relative:line\'\n o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/205.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/205.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.205\" width=\"227\" height=\"150\" align=\"right\" border=\"0\" /><!--[endif]-->Osteoporosis, or the thinning of bone tissue, is largely thought of as a condition afflicting only elderly women. Although being a Caucasian woman over the age of 50 greatly increases your chances of osteoporosis, men and younger adults are susceptible to low bone density as well. It is estimated that by 2020, half of all Americans will have osteoporosis. This low bone density can lead to bone fractures, loss of height, broken bones, and severe back pain. To keep your bones solid, follow these tips:\n<ol start=\"1\">\n	<li>Do regular weight bearing and strength training exercises. High impact exercises like running, weight lifting, and jumping rope will increase bone mass.</li>\n	<li>Don\'t drink too much soda or alcohol, and don\'t smoke. The phosphoric acid in soda draws calcium out of the bones.</li>\n	<li>Get the recommended amount of Calcium and Vitamin D. Dietary levels of <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001MvkEXPYjURg5m71I85bWyoWoPHpPzanBZ5zJ4KDsLTBb0U_12970IKfIUujFpZ7i2Tiy32_PLBasgY1iqZTEqJAelUNwUq3mtHjpxTwPt5v-QT0f4kcBWo-5owiRanAzhR-aHKPDm1sC4Uq0O6mSr4-kO-6NAJcPMkmQmZxaHRU=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Calcium</a> and <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001MvkEXPYjURgmSLvEW5hT16MaAY1V3vBo9i8GjKcWATIgawwg-lVvt56LQkO2RUUzcD1QMZJRVazxFZ87DMSrURkk0ljfElf1Vat3XbehqTtV-KHll0Y6B7SdthXDhwHVvN9MqOmv4H3cS7otaWlAy5twFEZ3Dtl_\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Vitamin D</a> vary widely by age and gender. If the diet is low in dairy products, fish, and fortified foods, additional supplements may be necessary.</li>\n	<li>Know your family history and risk factors. Having a thin frame, being inactive, or having other medical conditions such as rheumatoid arthritis or hormone treatment can increase your risk.</li>\n	<li>Take action before it\'s too late. Getting adequate nutrition and exercise in younger years will build a strong bone frame for the later years. Inform your doctor about your risks, and have a bone density scan to predict your risk for fractures.</li>\n</ol>\nFor more information about preventing, detecting, or managing osteoporosis, visit the <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001MvkEXPYjURgWWOYWCUtg6TdLmLimkbMqa4_aCwqNNfw9wf8z6eaKc1T_ZHp4KcKUYOGosssk7M1K1YCsNMwLtJhXRjIR5Bb1Yz8SU9rH3nmzh3xt9U8CQ97c5LZlk9Nl\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">National Osteoporosis Foundation</a>.', '5 Ways to Better your Bone Health   ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '5-ways-to-better-your-bone-health', '', '', '2012-05-06 16:01:11', '2012-05-06 16:01:11', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=667', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('864', '14', '2012-05-09 18:05:23', '2012-05-09 18:05:23', '<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1028\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\n margin-left:0;margin-top:82.5pt;width:117.75pt;height:176.25pt;z-index:251658240;\n mso-wrap-distance-left:7.5pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:7.5pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-right:7.5pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:7.5pt;\n mso-position-horizontal:left;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/206.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/206.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.206\" width=\"157\" height=\"235\" align=\"left\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"10\" vspace=\"10\" /><!--[endif]-->As we Spring into Summer, the warmer clothes get packed away, and the summer wardrobe comes out to play. It\'s important to take extra precautions to protect our body\'s largest organ from the sun\'s damaging rays. Skin cancer is the most common form of cancer in the United States. Up to 90% of visible skin changes from aging are due to the sun\'s UV rays. Take care of your skin this summer by following these skin-saving tips:\n<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Save your Skin</span>- Be generous with an SPF of 15 or higher that offers protection against UVA and UVB rays. It takes approximately one ounce of sunscreen to cover an entire body. That\'s roughly the size of a golf ball or shot glass.</li>\n	<li><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Take Cover</span>- Find a wide brimmed hat to protect your ears and neck. Since the sun\'s rays can penetrate through clothes, find an extra layer of protection from a hat, umbrella, or tree.</li>\n	<li><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Ban the Bed</span>- Tanning beds are a proven risk for developing skin cancer. For men and women wanting a sun kissed glow, opt for spay or self tanners.</li>\n</ul>\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Protect your Peepers</span>- Sun can damage eyes, leading to increased risk of cataracts, a damaged retina, or chances of skin cancer on the eyelids. Wear sunglasses that reflect light and block out 99-100% of UVA and UVB rays.', 'Shading your Skin from the Sun    ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'shading-your-skin-from-the-sun', '', '', '2012-05-09 18:05:23', '2012-05-09 18:05:23', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=669', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('865', '14', '2012-05-14 18:08:42', '2012-05-14 18:08:42', '[caption id=\"attachment_672\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"120\" caption=\"Marie Francis is the Director of Screening Services for Sterling Wellness.\"]<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Marie-Francis.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-672\" title=\"Marie Francis\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Marie-Francis.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"120\" height=\"160\" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<strong><em>A: </em></strong> These three biometric screening methods all indicate a different result. There are pros and cons to each method. Although they are each appropriate for certain readings, one must also take into consideration physical activity, eating habits, and lifestyle factors as well. Being \"healthy\" is not making the grade on a body composition screening, but rather getting a sense of the whole picture through other evaluations as well.\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Body Mass Index (BMI)-</span> BMI is a ratio of your weight to your height. This is a good indicator of a healthy weight range, but does not work well for people with muscular builds. Since muscle weighs more than fat, those with high lean body mass can register in the overweight category.  Generally speaking, BMI is a good approximation to determine if your weight is a healthy range for your height. To determine if you are in a healthy weight range, <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001MvkEXPYjURjl34SM09vi4RKS5Y3rP9J876h701onndX-tPauRQ7BQu1DtqNuEoD0ujhI4re9WtBXIVXEhBPDcV7v1xzopqi-ftkA_whNbTV3JSBZkH9HR0r6-uPZc4BrGvJwaLkX_rm9RuErJD5wS7ItZ72ofqQizhHpC37Crsg=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">calculate your BMI here</a>.\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Body Fat Percentage</span>- We are able to measure the percentage of fat composition in the body by sending a weak electrical current through your arms (measuring only upper body fat) or through your legs (measuring only lower body fat). Both methods fail to measure abdominal fat, the most important indicator of health status. The results of this bioelectrical impedance method we use varies greatly depending on hydration status, recent exercise, and food consumption. The most accurate way to measure true body fat is through underwater weighing or a DEXA scan.\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Waist to Hip Ratio-</span>  By taking the waist circumference and dividing it by the hip circumference, one can determine health risks according to fat distribution.  When fat is distributed around the abdominal area, such as in \"apple\" shape body types, the risk for chronic diseases such as type II diabetes, heart disease, and hypertension increases. To calculate your Waist to Hip ratio, <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001MvkEXPYjURi5kXN7IWidgP3qHphgtCs2LPnEOFgERMI2_zFouYSP1aEw9QKgtxohHxEMDPRVdZjmbdv4HES6m8a-6chgI7Jvf4fsUsknykzPEPeXc4Q_3DfnZve2E3v1vLEZpIE8FVgleuFbI4M9b5FKduoTpSmF\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a>.\n\nWhile all three methods of screening are important, we must not reduce one\'s health to the result of one test. Determining health risks requires comprehensive look at other indicators as well.', 'Ask the Expert Q: \"I\'ve heard conflicting evidence on Body Mass Index, Body Fat, and Waist to Hip Ratio. What is the difference between those measurements, and what is the most accurate?\"   ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ask-the-expert-q-ive-heard-conflicting-evidence-on-body-mass-index-body-fat-and-waist-to-hip-ratio-what-is-the-difference-between-those-measurements-and-what-is-the-most-accurate', '', '', '2012-05-14 18:08:42', '2012-05-14 18:08:42', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=671', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('866', '14', '2012-05-16 18:09:01', '2012-05-16 18:09:01', 'If your idea of a salad conjures up images of rabbits on a picnic, it might be time to change the way you think about this versatile dish. By definition, a salad is a dish of various mixtures, often containing raw or cooked vegetables, pasta, or fruit. With new flavors from seasonal produce arriving on market shelves and in gardens across the country, it\'s a great time to get creative with your preferred method of delivery.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1031\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\n margin-left:0;margin-top:953.25pt;width:100.5pt;height:144.75pt;z-index:251658240;\n mso-wrap-distance-left:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:3.75pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-right:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:3.75pt;\n mso-position-horizontal:left;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/208.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/208.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.208\" width=\"134\" height=\"193\" align=\"left\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /><!--[endif]-->Salads are a party of nutrients, and when paired with a healthy fat like olive oil or walnuts, the fat soluble vitamins are more easily absorbed. There is no limit to the different ingredients to add to your salad, and you may find yourself adding everything but the kitchen sink. For a healthy base, opt for dark greens like spinach or red leaf lettuce in lieu of iceburg lettuce. For picky family members, consider a salad bar night where each person can add their own toppings. Some great options for salad mixers include whole wheat spiral pasta, dried cranberries, sunflower seeds, and chopped olives. Perhaps the salads can even replace a meat dish for a meatless meal once a week. Visit <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001MvkEXPYjURilxVtisbqiPaiPwMRoywtPf7HZ3xG57_N07NzN4IGXWRptRtIag_ziPbQQ17LijySjSQGeP0x6iuayiXDNC1868NbeVlA8vCXzOnCGqnbPi70z6SSQPIQQnGrDqelKIAk=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">AllRecipies</a> for an extensive list of innovative salad combinations.', 'Get Creative for a Super Salad   ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'get-creative-for-a-super-salad', '', '', '2012-05-16 18:09:01', '2012-05-16 18:09:01', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=674', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('867', '14', '2012-05-07 18:09:48', '2012-05-07 18:09:48', 'There is no generational gap seperating the fun one can have while riding a bike. Cycling is a joint-friendly low impact exercise that is appropriate for all ages. The coordination and balance required to learn to ride a bike as a child is still needed today. A 60 minute bike ride can burn up to 300-500 calories and will continue to boost your metabolic rate, burning more calories long after you\'ve put your kickstand down. The repetitive low impact motion of pedaling is beneficial for hip and knee mobility, offering a great exercise for those suffering from lower body joint pain.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1032\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\n margin-left:267.55pt;margin-top:0;width:87pt;height:129.75pt;z-index:251658240;\n mso-wrap-distance-left:7.5pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:7.5pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-right:7.5pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:7.5pt;\n mso-position-horizontal:right;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/209.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/209.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.209\" width=\"116\" height=\"173\" align=\"right\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"10\" vspace=\"10\" /><!--[endif]-->Riding a bike is an excellent aerobic activity that improves cardiovascular fitness by using the body\'s largest muscle group in the legs. For those wanting to tone the lower body, cycling slowly increases stamina, muscle strength, and definition in the legs, hips, core, and buttocks. Whether you choose an indoor stationary bike, or an outdoor ride through the park, biking is a family friendly year round activity. Pedal with a purpose May 14-18 for national \'<a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001MvkEXPYjURiVKf3BBIXM2nF0o_yE-_XjKDGm5oc59PR9iG_2YIRnY2OgFqBQGNLxxOmteYfZxOhHCYHzvLXQdfLJZ-so_9c43QA9D5qlYv_MhyKn8mINAVtfasCsOpwv3J0y7LOI4YCxVAz2Q86nRg==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Ride your Bike to Work Week</a>\'. If riding your bike to work isn\'t an option, make it a goal to ride your bike in exchange for driving to an errand. Remember to put safety first by wearing a helmet and high visibility clothing.', 'Pedaling with a Purpose  ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'pedaling-with-a-purpose', '', '', '2012-05-07 18:09:48', '2012-05-07 18:09:48', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=676', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('868', '14', '2012-05-25 18:10:43', '2012-05-25 18:10:43', '<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1033\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\n margin-left:362.8pt;margin-top:288.75pt;width:185.25pt;height:159pt;z-index:251658240;\n mso-wrap-distance-left:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:3.75pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-right:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:3.75pt;\n mso-position-horizontal:right;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/212.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/212.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.212\" width=\"247\" height=\"212\" align=\"right\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /><!--[endif]-->The month of May provides little grace for slowing down and resting. This month\'s calendar slots get inevitably filled up with graduations, summer vacation planning, and end of school parties. Amidst the frenzy of social, family, and work obligations, remember to take time for yourself.\n\n<em>\"Sometimes the most important thing in a whole day is the rest we take between two deep breaths.\"</em> -Etty Hillesum<em>  </em>\n\nTime alone is often viewed as a selfish act, but it\'s necessary to realize you can\'t take care of others if you aren\'t taking care of yourself. This especially rings true for caretakers of young children or elderly adults. Spend time in silence for a few moments each day to relax, breathe, think, dream, pray, or meditate. This renewing time can provide a calming sense of satisfaction and stress relief.', 'Take Time for Yourself  ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'take-time-for-yourself', '', '', '2012-05-25 18:10:43', '2012-05-25 18:10:43', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=678', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('869', '14', '2012-05-22 18:16:06', '2012-05-22 18:16:06', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/fleur-4.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-683\" title=\"fleur 4\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/fleur-4.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"88\" height=\"139\" /></a>Sterling Wellness Solutions is seeking an enthusiastic and experienced LPN or RN for a Health Coaching position in Crowley, LA. Applicant must have 2-3 years of experience in the health care field. Responsible for reviewing abnormal lab results and addressing risk factors, motivating healthy lifestyle change, and providing intensive onsite and telephonic health coaching. Must have excellent presentation and interpersonal skills and be computer proficient. Required to uphold time sensitive deadlines and maintain privacy and confidentiality. Serious applicants only. Please send cover letter and resume to <a href=\"mailto:awalker@sterling-wellness.com\">awalker@sterling-wellness.com</a>.', 'Nurse/Health Coach', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'nursehealth-coach', '', '', '2012-05-22 18:16:06', '2012-05-22 18:16:06', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=680', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('870', '14', '2012-06-07 13:31:16', '2012-06-07 13:31:16', 'For a number of years, Sterling Wellness Solutions has hosted a Friends &amp; Family Day offering Health Screenings at special prices. You do not need a physician referral to take advantage of this lab screening offer.\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Thursday, June 14, 2012</strong>\n<em>6:30am - 10am</em>\nCall 337-783-7840 to Sign Up by June 11\n210 West Mill Street, Crowley\n<strong>Complete Wellness Lab Panel</strong>\nJust $50 per person (Retail $529)\nAdditional Tests available at reduced rates!</p>\nIf you are interested in getting any elective lab work done, please call Sterling at 1-337-783-7840 to set up your lab requisition form. You do not need a physician order. You can print it out from your home and take it to any LabCorp near you.  A health coach will call to review your results within 5 days, and you will also get a copy emailed to you.\n\nView this <a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Sterling-Wellness-2012-Family-Friends-Screening.pdf\">Sterling Wellness-2012 Family Friends Screening</a> flyer for more information. The second page of the flyer lists the various tests you can have done at the discounted rate.', 'Friends and Family Event!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'friends-and-family-event', '', '', '2012-06-07 13:31:16', '2012-06-07 13:31:16', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=686', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('871', '14', '2012-06-01 13:44:54', '2012-06-01 13:44:54', 'The first Sunday in June recognizes <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001QNsnRxCJUDS-rdS72320MqeZ91R7U0JRHdAhtUNVeVwWK-EBJrTYokevqChEV-lxROtyne8KkjstYWx4Mq94CA-gdnMFVLEcy9zIcJKUJW0kNXM4yUygMxN-qaIrE_Ts\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">National Cancer Survivor\'s Day</a>, a time to celebrate the life of those who have overcome the fight from any form of cancer. Many communities across multiple countries unite for a time of celebration and support to show that life after cancer can be productive and meaningful. This non-profit foundation offers guidance, networking, and education to hospitals and community groups in need of support.\n\n<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1026\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"NCSD logo\"\n style=\'position:absolute;margin-left:0;margin-top:1142.25pt;width:95.25pt;\n height:95.25pt;z-index:251658240;mso-wrap-distance-left:0;\n mso-wrap-distance-top:0;mso-wrap-distance-right:0;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:0;\n mso-position-horizontal:left;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"http://www.ncsdf.org/Images/PlainCircleNDBlue.gif\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"http://www.ncsdf.org/Images/PlainCircleNDBlue.gif\" alt=\"NCSD logo\" width=\"127\" height=\"127\" align=\"left\" border=\"0\" /><!--[endif]-->\nDue to great strides in medical technology, research, and cancer treatment, there are over 12 million cancer survivors in the United States today. If you or someone you know may be interested in hosting a National Cancer Survivor\'s Day event, you can download the <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001QNsnRxCJUDTKjE4sZNlJ_V9lBb8y5y1f9AOWkTLfpRVOkmXW-GlShM31sVEsqDiued2Hpx55s0ojoJfC3brGtnsQNp-_SrQDQiWKVmcrbSkRjCgf5mAW2XIeDaiYe4QT2jbTNPocteg=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">planning guide</a> here.', 'A Celebration of Life', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-celebration-of-life', '', '', '2012-06-01 13:44:54', '2012-06-01 13:44:54', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=693', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('872', '14', '2012-06-05 13:55:32', '2012-06-05 13:55:32', 'School is out and summer is here! Don\'t let the excitement of fun summer traditions overshadow simple safety practices. Let this month be your reminder to keep your loved ones out of harms way by following these practices:<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1027\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\n margin-left:350.8pt;margin-top:268.5pt;width:177.75pt;height:134.25pt;\n z-index:251658240;mso-wrap-distance-left:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:3.75pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-right:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:3.75pt;\n mso-position-horizontal:right;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/243.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/243.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.243\" width=\"237\" height=\"179\" align=\"right\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /><!--[endif]-->\n<ul>\n	<li>Check each smoke alarm throughout the house.</li>\n	<li>If you don\'t already do so, get in the habit of wearing your seat belt.</li>\n	<li>Learn CPR and the Heimlich maneuver.</li>\n	<li>Dispose of expired food and prescription medications.</li>\n	<li>Ensure helmets and life jackets are properly fitted.</li>\n	<li>Restock First Aid Kits in your car and home.</li>\n	<li>Keep spectators at a safe distance from fireworks. If shooting off fireworks, always wear safety glasses and have water close by.</li>\n</ul>\nFor a complete list of safety reminders for your home, work, or recreation, visit the <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001QNsnRxCJUDS_n7sBbYX2kXw41Jv-_KY1Y9XXwQBD-3ecxmrQIOxOd5zJNFzfqWz2HNcjuPJNXYKvnlRKk1EOSl1ch8K6If0JJDxZcMG8odbUyOeljfWyl4hnQFQDucrs\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">National Safety Council</a>.\n\nStay injury free, and have a safe and healthy summer!', 'Be Prepared, Be Safe     ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'be-prepared-be-safe', '', '', '2012-06-05 13:55:32', '2012-06-05 13:55:32', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=695', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('873', '14', '2012-06-03 13:57:28', '2012-06-03 13:57:28', '<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1028\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\n margin-left:0;margin-top:612.75pt;width:117.75pt;height:141.75pt;z-index:251658240;\n mso-wrap-distance-left:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:3.75pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-right:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:3.75pt;\n mso-position-horizontal:left;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/238.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/238.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.238\" width=\"157\" height=\"189\" align=\"left\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /><!--[endif]-->Each June, a nationwide movement aims to bring awareness to preventable men\'s health issues and encourage early detection and treatment. Men are less likely to seek medical help, and schedule preventative annual physical exams.\n\n<strong><em>\"There is a silent health crisis in America...it\'s the fact that, on average, American men live sicker and die younger than American women.\"</em></strong> -Dr. David Gremillion, Men\'s Health Network.\n\nThe life expectancy of men in America is 76 years. Women on the other hand, tend to live a few years longer, to 81 years of age. The #1 cause of death for men is heart disease, followed by cancer and accidents or injuries.\n\nVisit <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001QNsnRxCJUDSSsJ75hdNfz-5xENfvBo0JRj5SN8ma90irULQGfi1B_CZ1Rhunh0WSt-kEeXGJMwph5hxlPfUYQNcE1buwn4WCyzI49x7-UCaOxaWpR9c5Gm_L0yv8SCIy\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Men\'s Health Month</a> to find information about recommended ages for preventive screenings, a men\'s health library, and a calendar of events. You can also learn more about local screenings, health fairs, and events.', 'Shining a Light on Men\'s Health-  June is Men\'s Health Month    ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'shining-a-light-on-mens-health-june-is-mens-health-month', '', '', '2012-06-03 13:57:28', '2012-06-03 13:57:28', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=697', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('874', '14', '2012-06-11 13:59:14', '2012-06-11 13:59:14', 'Since almost 70% of an adult\'s body is made up of water, it is important to replenish the water stores frequently. Sip water frequently throughout the day aiming for an ultimate goal of eight, 8 ounce glasses of water. Often times, if you feel thirsty, you are already dehydrated. Roughly 80% of the water we consume comes from liquids we drink, and the other 20% is found in the foods we eat. Almost all fruits and vegetables have high water content, so enjoy up to 5-9 servings of produce a day!   <!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1029\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\n margin-left:278.05pt;margin-top:911.25pt;width:108.75pt;height:162.75pt;\n z-index:251658240;mso-wrap-distance-left:0;mso-wrap-distance-top:0;\n mso-wrap-distance-right:0;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:0;\n mso-position-horizontal:right;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/229.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/229.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.229\" width=\"145\" height=\"217\" align=\"right\" border=\"0\" /><!--[endif]-->\n\n<strong><em>Fun Facts about Water: </em></strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>Dehydration and lack of water is the #1 cause of afternoon fatigue.</li>\n	<li>Water is an essential nutrient excreting waste and flushing toxins through urination, perspiration, and bowel movements.</li>\n	<li>Iceberg lettuce contains the most water of any food, followed by watermelon, cucumbers, and celery.</li>\n	<li>Broth based soups and stews are a good source of water.</li>\n	<li>If you eat a diet high in fiber, your water needs increase.</li>\n</ul>\nCaffeinated beverages like soda and coffee act as a diuretic excreting excess water out of the body. Consider drinking one cup of water after every caffeinated beverage consumed. Other clear or transparent beverages like herbal tea, 100% fruit juice, and lightly sweetened lemonade are great sources of water as well. For a fresh flavor to your standard water, try adding a sprig of fresh mint leaves, lemon or lime slices, or cucumber slices.', 'Staying Healthy through Proper Hydration', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'staying-healthy-through-proper-hydration', '', '', '2012-06-11 13:59:14', '2012-06-11 13:59:14', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=699', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('875', '14', '2012-06-14 14:00:42', '2012-06-14 14:00:42', 'Picnics, campfires, and backyard BBQ\'s are a favorite summertime tradition. Don\'t let poorly handled food ruin a good time. Follow these 5 tips to keep your food safe and edible.  <!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1030\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\n margin-left:268.3pt;margin-top:54.75pt;width:95.25pt;height:143.25pt;\n z-index:251658240;mso-wrap-distance-left:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:3.75pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-right:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:3.75pt;\n mso-position-horizontal:right;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/237.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/237.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.237\" width=\"127\" height=\"191\" align=\"right\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /><!--[endif]-->\n<ol start=\"1\">\n	<li><strong>Keep hot foods hot and cold foods cold</strong>- Keep raw meat covered in an ice filled cooler or refrigerator until ready to prepare.</li>\n	<li><strong>Wash your hands</strong>- Keep hands, plates, cutting boards, and utensils clean so that bacteria can not cross contaminate to other foods.</li>\n	<li><strong>Cook meat thoroughly</strong>- Use a thermometer to determine if your food is cooked to the <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001QNsnRxCJUDTpZmWQ0mHq_dVKuCOQiTxyIyWua1iSV3x-UjRedAic-2mSa1FJHH0kXtss4ToiirAJjgOteucUG4JYivKwAbYMfquoXvvfzK7J55_D7YF1kaufKoj2erMoWjvSjJZOFrZ3raehpgBts3eJuXi7RAP7\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">safe minimum temperature</a>.</li>\n	<li><strong>Defrost safely</strong>- Never let frozen meat thaw on a counter top. Thaw in a refrigerator, microwave, or bowl of water instead.</li>\n	<li><strong>When in doubt, throw it out</strong>- If you have to question the safety, age, or freshness of a food, it\'s probably not worth eating.</li>\n</ol>\nVisit WebMD for more tips on preventing <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001QNsnRxCJUDTRooUvhyiK_S66qXMTdSIQqAXAIh4fCoD24200KEzGSUiZngSHbLJp5o31DDlwB5UzJcleRGUxJ-91knbelTYIpp5NGjD58pZlQ6t-TBxPrqZuQ5FKjvWOaAcyzQO-PpETr2QobI48i1ShvXWe-qENmt9lEVc8yLInr3FL7bnJFX7XWt9FFztD\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">food poisoning</a>, and get creative with <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001QNsnRxCJUDTB1GGlPEFRg0y20UOTGZS0vSH6Nbr9KmBT3vTpbVrDDrur9ddNOd4-0SIMvdK8m3hQkwnWlKsgRgUIAlH9AyNoS44RGt_cKWqmXz0bQ81iu7WevO0rqXCZlIxvVotm1S1WZKhg6iauWqzQNNSFfrqEoJc107b-oHM=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">healthy recipes to grill</a> meat, fruits and vegetables from EatingWell.', '5 Safety Tips to Avoid Food Poisoning   ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '5-safety-tips-to-avoid-food-poisoning', '', '', '2012-06-14 14:00:42', '2012-06-14 14:00:42', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=701', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('876', '14', '2012-06-16 14:02:58', '2012-06-16 14:02:58', '<strong><em>A: </em></strong>The most common and accepted forms of screening available are the Prostate Specific Antigen test or PSA, and a digital rectal examination. The lifetime risk of contracting prostate cancer is only about 16%, while the risk of dying from it is only about 3%. Controversy exists over the proper approach to prostate screening.\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_706\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"155\" caption=\"Dr. Stephen Cannon, MD is the Medical Director for Sterling Wellness.\"]<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Stephen-Cannon1.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-706 \" title=\"Stephen Cannon\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Stephen-Cannon1-222x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"155\" height=\"210\" /></a>[/caption]\n\nThe American Urological Association (AUA) advocates the combination of PSA testing and digital rectal examinations beginning at the age of 40. The American Cancer Society recommends discussing the risks and benefits of screening with men between the ages of 50 and 75 years of age, and initiating screening at 45 years of age in African American males and those with a first degree relative with prostate cancer at an age less than 65.\n\nAnyone with prostate symptoms should have a digital rectal exam and a PSA. If you have an abnormal PSA result, you should talk to your doctor! An abnormal PSA can be due to several factors the <em>least</em> common of which is prostate cancer. The most common cause is prolonged pressure or trauma to the prostate gland, such as prolonged driving, horseback riding, lawn mowing etc., followed closely by benign prostatic hypertrophy (BPH) which is a benign and medically treatable disease.  Your physician should conduct a digital rectal examination. The decision to proceed with further testing should then be based on the results of this exam, your personal risk of prostate cancer, and your own comfort level.\n\nFor more information please refer to <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001QNsnRxCJUDQaFN_PWZN7opKFwfUuXuZ48tGUztM3PsrZ3emGgka_qAcJpEr_JInFxr_90xaF_AAmpz59S5exf1jThFjnZRFCHCz5343R8RX7KrwlW8IsNcQkwzKXECMN0ouIwQoUYtI=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">The US Preventive Services Task Force (USPSTF)</a>, the <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001QNsnRxCJUDTr56R-k8ljxLjDLe6Xk_xImwV9jP4FW4feA0M-tYtwmF2CGOSOKsQR0-ip-kjuEzWEUP8-Ssgaa1H1e4Jvt8ITBCBdeJtcueu4o65BzZr8MzZhSkZcrpXYqSRGl65lpdYSedkk8HNspOQGIaTCWLXb\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">American Urological Association (AUA)</a>, and the <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001QNsnRxCJUDQygMZ_WNyb5IMxZOUCOIiZWVh0d_nJm1EWcW7NA6QKqJiLMozb7KgGbX-kJGUmdldUCsVYTpL3hTRWsRvz1BD3rvWrXn10CIGSoDiR0vKvShw4eTOXLxN7-9dIm7oTF5Q=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">American Academy of Family Physicians (AAFP)</a>.', 'Ask the Expert  Q: \"I just turned 42 and was told I need to get a PSA test. What is the process for that test, and what will it tell me?\"', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ask-the-expert-q-i-just-turned-42-and-was-told-i-need-to-get-a-psa-test-what-is-the-process-for-that-test-and-what-will-it-tell-me', '', '', '2012-06-16 14:02:58', '2012-06-16 14:02:58', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=703', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('877', '14', '2012-06-19 14:08:23', '2012-06-19 14:08:23', '<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1034\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\n margin-left:0;margin-top:676.5pt;width:122.25pt;height:182.25pt;z-index:251658240;\n mso-wrap-distance-left:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:3.75pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-right:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:3.75pt;\n mso-position-horizontal:left;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/231.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/231.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.231\" width=\"163\" height=\"243\" align=\"left\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /><!--[endif]-->There\'s something iconic about a cold glass of iced tea in the summertime. Although iced tea\'s southern counterpart is typically laden with sugar, there are many health benefits to traditional unsweetened tea. When brewed from fresh leaves or tea bags, this thirst quenching beverage contains many beneficial antioxidants and flavonoids. White tea, green tea, and black tea all vary in flavor, caffeine content, and beneficial compounds. White tea has been shown to have more anticancer and antiviral properties than green or black teas. Studies have shown green tea to be a heart healthy beverage of choice for lowering the risk of atherosclerosis, or hardening of the artery walls from heart disease. The green variety has also been praised for its anti-aging benefits and ability to stabilize blood sugar levels. Generally speaking, black tea contains the most caffeine, followed by green tea and then white tea.\n\nTo reap the most health benefits from iced tea, avoid adding sugar. Instead opt for a lemon or lime slice, or mint leaf. This summer, enjoy freshly brewed unsweetened tea, and feel good about the health benefits you are delivering to your body. Visit WebMD to read more about the <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001QNsnRxCJUDQx5_FU_QT1TXFsWPPIOfYHHpCpcIhA9p0f0SdmAJxzK808yvOBLAhPYCL8cwFwUM1us1FEjTuBw-m28bLjhq1aCgqcYbo4JebLHhAOrwy9ou789SR_0B_XC9NyXw8AVwKt5fYNVtMwWkOLkP-_zmHcVMuYltAumg6lOPe3ez1EttDecFUJMnmU\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">health benefits of tea</a>.', 'A Healthy Take on Tea', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-healthy-take-on-tea', '', '', '2012-06-19 14:08:23', '2012-06-19 14:08:23', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=708', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('878', '14', '2012-06-25 14:09:33', '2012-06-25 14:09:33', 'The Pilates movement migrated to America around the 1920\'s when founder Joseph Pilates and his wife started a Pilates studio in New York City. This exercise has boomed into a popular activity world-wide and was developed to focus on spinal alignment, awareness of breath, and core stability.  <!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1035\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\n margin-left:275.05pt;margin-top:921.75pt;width:94.5pt;height:112.5pt;\n z-index:251658240;mso-wrap-distance-left:7.5pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:7.5pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-right:7.5pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:7.5pt;\n mso-position-horizontal:right;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/232.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/232.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.232\" width=\"126\" height=\"150\" align=\"right\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"10\" vspace=\"10\" /><!--[endif]-->\n\nPilates is a great low impact movement that benefits core muscles in the back and abdominal area. Those with joint pain or reduced range of motion can benefit from the strength building advantages of Pilates. This exercise has also been shown to improve flexibility, agility, and proper posture. If you would like to give Pilates a try, read these <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001QNsnRxCJUDS12QHWM3XA6sjHMvRQpYaNUpciiiWbN4ZSTeMDXdNxNOy1Op-gjSAq-2ZMo8DowkAarouQ15ReMkl7t6xRniPwg9Iaw3iyZ2r0Zo8-9OjycqyXnkCZ9RW6PLzNir_N_NwI4axz5pJNN45jBzniBPu7i68Qb1ZQQYo=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Getting Started</a> tips. Contact a local gym in your area or download a <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001QNsnRxCJUDQ9U6ra6mTptoeq8VcN22Tjn5BcFRa1DycD11AgAELow2cRRGyTGtkZBZJkWC3mkrJiRmLeZ8aH9O1WIVGoSgmVLYRwttFGjILB-ucqN7_Zvj2aKvjl5gg4\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">sample Pilates video</a>.', 'Gaining Strength with Pilates', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'gaining-strength-with-pilates', '', '', '2012-06-25 14:09:33', '2012-06-25 14:09:33', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=710', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('879', '14', '2012-07-04 14:18:27', '2012-07-04 14:18:27', 'During the month of July, we always pause to reflect on the freedoms we have as Americans. With special thanks, we salute the brave men and women that have fought for our country so we can enjoy the liberties granted to us. Wellness Facts for the Fourth:<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1026\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\n margin-left:262.3pt;margin-top:256.5pt;width:89.25pt;height:152.25pt;\n z-index:251658240;mso-wrap-distance-left:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:3.75pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-right:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:3.75pt;\n mso-position-horizontal:right;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/255.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/255.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.255\" width=\"119\" height=\"203\" align=\"right\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /><!--[endif]-->\n\n• If you were to walk the 3 mile route of the longest running Independence Day parade, located in Bristol, RI, your pedometer would register 6,000 steps.\n\n• Fireworks register at a sound of 130-190 decibels, which is louder than some rock concerts. To prevent hearing loss, sit further from the fireworks, or wear earplugs.\n\n• The favorite all-American dessert is a piece of apple pie. One slice can exceed 400 calories and 19 grams of fat so keep portions in check.\n\n• Independence day tops the charts for the most popular outdoor cooking day with approximately 150 million hot dogs consumed. Don\'t forget to grill your vegetables too!\n\nHappy 236th Birthday, America!', 'Picnics, Parades, and Patriotism ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'picnics-parades-and-patriotism', '', '', '2012-07-04 14:18:27', '2012-07-04 14:18:27', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=712', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('880', '14', '2012-07-07 14:20:13', '2012-07-07 14:20:13', 'When you think of skin care essentials, you may think of topical lotions, creams, and soaps. However, what is applied to the exposed layer is just a portion of the healthy skin equation. Follow these 5 tips for healthy skin from the inside out.\n\n<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1027\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\n margin-left:311.05pt;margin-top:650.25pt;width:138pt;height:112.5pt;z-index:251658240;\n mso-wrap-distance-left:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:3.75pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-right:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:3.75pt;\n mso-position-horizontal:right;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/253.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/253.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.253\" width=\"184\" height=\"150\" align=\"right\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /><!--[endif]-->\n\n1) <strong><em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Get hydrated-</span></em></strong> Water is undeniably the greatest nutrient you can consume for your skin. Not only does it keep skin hydrated and glowing, but water also plumps the look of skin to reduce fine lines and wrinkles.\n\n2) <strong><em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Eat healthy fats</span></em></strong>- Load up on healthy fats found in fatty fish like salmon and tilapia, nuts like almonds and walnuts, olive oil, flax, and avocados. These foods offer a dose of anti-inflammatory fats in the form of Omega-3\'s.\n\n3) <strong><em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Eat the rainbow</span></em></strong>- Various colors of fruits and vegetables will offer the greatest amount of antioxidant protection for your skin. The darkest, richest colors of produce typically offer the highest levels of anti-aging compounds.\n\n4) <strong><em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Be carb smart</span></em></strong><strong>-</strong> If you are prone to skin conditions from inflammation including psoriasis, acne, or roseaca, you may want to steer clear of simple carbohydrates. Opt for complex carbs containing whole grains and fiber over high sugar foods like soda and white flour.\n\n5) <strong><em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Skip the chips</span></em></strong>- Processed and packaged foods often contain <em>trans</em> fats, chemically altered ingredients, and unnatural additives and dyes. During digestion, the body may treat these ingredients as toxins, creating an inflammatory response.\n\nNot only is this method of eating beneficial to feed skin from the inside out, but these dietary habits are essential to optimal daily living as well. Keep your skin nourished today for a lifetime in the only skin you were given.', 'Healthier Skin Comes From Within', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'healthier-skin-comes-from-within', '', '', '2012-07-07 14:20:13', '2012-07-07 14:20:13', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=714', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('881', '14', '2012-07-14 14:21:14', '2012-07-14 14:21:14', '<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype\n id=\"_x0000_t75\" coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\"\n path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\" filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1026\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\n margin-left:0;margin-top:0;width:81.75pt;height:117.75pt;z-index:251660288;\n mso-wrap-distance-left:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:3.75pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-right:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:3.75pt;\n mso-position-horizontal:left;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"https://imgssl.constantcontact.com/ui/stock1/running-kite-man.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"https://imgssl.constantcontact.com/ui/stock1/running-kite-man.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"109\" height=\"157\" align=\"left\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /><!--[endif]-->You may have heard the recent hype about vitamin D. Also known as the \"sunshine vitamin,\" this nutrient can be synthesized in our skin from sun exposure and is also found in foods such as fish, egg yolks, and fortified milk. Although this fat soluble vitamin has long been known to keep bones strong, recent studies prove it\'s much more than that. Vitamin D acts as an immune enhancer. This vitamin may boost your immune system and protect you against ailments such as the common cold and flu. A study by the Cancer Treatment Centers of America suggests vitamin D can even play a role in preventing colon, breast, and prostate cancer. A recent Harvard Medical Study found vitamin D can also reduce the frequency and severity of asthma symptoms and also keep your brain sharper longer into life.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nBut just how much should you be getting? The NIH recommends 600IU of vitamin D for all adults age 18-70. Depending on geographic location and season, many people can get their required dose of vitamin D from 15-30 minutes of sunlight on exposed skin. Additional dietary sources include cod liver oil, yogurt, and orange juice. For more information on vitamin D, visit the <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=0016AezBh1UtIa0zwgY9mfUaJ-HIgSlN5r0qk2hHFLczKyVGXbKs_r4Ok61BjHT-f5H3l71bctoVlGvnkSvDQF02QYf6Of16lQj2hfHlp1kQ0lCrGMV6s3etXus1yMNSeoniYYgEqrZY17rNPSmq2e0ozVXeWoDH8V6UV2P2NWViVY=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">National Institutes of Health.</a>', 'Vitamin D touted as the Sunshine Vitamin    ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'vitamin-d-touted-as-the-sunshine-vitamin', '', '', '2012-07-14 14:21:14', '2012-07-14 14:21:14', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=716', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('882', '14', '2012-07-17 14:21:55', '2012-07-17 14:21:55', '<strong><em>A: </em></strong>Many think of massage as just an activity that can assist in stress reduction, however relaxation is just one of the more popular benefits. Additional benefits can be seen depending on the frequency of massages received along with the individual\'s receptiveness to each technique.\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_719\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"131\" caption=\"Heather Hedrick is the Director of Health Education for Sterling and is also a Licensed Massage Therapist.\"]<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Heather-Hedrick.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-719\" title=\"Heather Hedrick\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Heather-Hedrick.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"131\" height=\"160\" /></a>[/caption]\n\nMassages received on a regular basis can help decrease anxiety, lower blood pressure, and increase circulation. Massage therapy has also been known to speed recovery from injury, improve sleep habits, and increase concentration. For some, massage helps to reduce fatigue while increasing their energy to handle stressful situations.\n\nRemembering that everyone can receive multiple benefits from a variety of massage techniques, it is a perfect prescription for good health. Massage is also beneficial for cancer patients. Massage helps to stimulate the flow of lymph, the body\'s natural defense system, against toxic invaders. For example, in breast cancer patients, massage has been shown to increase the cells that fight cancer.\n\nTreat yourself to a massage during <em>EveryBody Needs a Massage Week</em>, July 16-20.', 'Ask the Expert Q: \"I know a lot of people who get frequent massages and claim there are many health benefits to them. Is there more to a massage than I think? \" ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ask-the-expert-q-i-know-a-lot-of-people-who-get-frequent-massages-and-claim-there-are-many-health-benefits-to-them-is-there-more-to-a-massage-than-i-think', '', '', '2012-07-17 14:21:55', '2012-07-17 14:21:55', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=718', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('883', '14', '2012-07-20 14:23:56', '2012-07-20 14:23:56', '<img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/250.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.250\" width=\"115\" height=\"167\" align=\"left\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" />If you\'re like many berry lovers, you may feel like you could eat your weight in blueberries. As we celebrate Blueberry Month in July, it\'s only appropriate to share the nutritional resume of these dense power foods. All berries are packed full of antioxidants, vitamins, and minerals. Also known as \"natures candy\" these tasty fruits are plentiful, versatile, and oh so delicious. Blueberries in particular are a tiny blue fruit loaded with Vitamin C, E, and fiber.\n\nTime after time, blueberries top the charts as one of the most powerful foods for phytochemicals and antioxidants. These compounds fight off free radicals and prevent aging. Blueberries are easy to pick, and can be used in muffins, waffles, pancakes, smoothies, and eaten fresh or frozen. For more great recipes on the versatile use of this fruit, visit EatingWell\'s <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=0016AezBh1UtIaEM9wX848AJLFlsCkA8proNVN2NMktzxMUxi3Yu7c49JoWbLp0qgJBbdT_gScxcW-XrxuKA6iLMG1Lz0ZdVTm67cFO_RPJy53PoTprKkKXs2e1Zz3FitUbMw3UWrcvzfud4fC4UjtbAFBlxGlpZGejgKTRrWKHc4LCekGefAAPhRQySyGtsn9j\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">collection of blueberry recipes</a>.', 'Blueberry Snack Attack', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'blueberry-snack-attack', '', '', '2012-07-20 14:23:56', '2012-07-20 14:23:56', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=721', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('884', '14', '2012-07-24 14:25:41', '2012-07-24 14:25:41', 'As the world waits in anticipation of this summer\'s Olympic games in London, let the excitement overflow into your own backyard. Get creative by adapting popular games to fit the world-class athletes in your own family. Let these ideas prompt you as you develop your own Olympic games:\n<table width=\"153\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"right\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"153\"> <a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/torch.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-725\" title=\"torch\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/torch-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"147\" height=\"147\" /></a><em>This summer, host your own family Olympic games!</em></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<ul>\n	<li><strong><em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Show your Spirit</span></em></strong>- Let each participant choose a country, color, or mascot to symbolize them. Dress the part to represent your team. Give an award to the best dressed athlete!</li>\n	<li><strong><em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Develop new Games</span></em></strong>- Adapt traditional Olympic games such as track and field, badminton, or softball. Consider new games to get everyone moving like three legged races, capture the flag, or water balloon toss. Did you know tug-of-war was an Olympic sport until 1920?</li>\n	<li><em><strong>Soundtrack for Success-</strong></em> Nothing sets the tone of the games quite like the \"Olympic Fanfare and Theme\" composed by John Williams. Download it from your <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=0016AezBh1UtIb6KfS4_LkZmcvpXb2uWWoKxn3GfOvFmFg5yw_iNBdbuoDGMZSZgubWxz2q0wdQbNdDkos_QsB1MWMZSyDKojx5THB0q88PZiCJ81T440g8CtbBF2bQoOax\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">itunes</a> store.</li>\n	<li><em><strong>Gold, Silver, and Bronze</strong></em>- Award your athletes for a job well done by making inexpensive medals out of ribbon and construction paper. Who will be the most decorated Olympic athlete in your family?</li>\n	<li><em><strong>Make your list</strong></em>- In order to pull off a successful family Olympics, have a running list of games to keep your athletes interested. Involve children in the planning by letting them choose their favorite activities. You may never know how much fun you can have in a bubble gum blowing contest or an egg toss.</li>\n</ul>\nAs with any physical activity, keep water on hand to prevent dehydration and over heating. Have your camera available for snapping pictures during the games, and don\'t forget to invite your coworkers, neighbors, and friends to <em>let the games begin</em>!', 'Let the Games Begin!   ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'let-the-games-begin', '', '', '2012-07-24 14:25:41', '2012-07-24 14:25:41', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=724', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('885', '14', '2012-07-30 14:30:10', '2012-07-30 14:30:10', 'What better way to cool off in this heat wave than going for a dip in a local pool? Since water offers 10 times the resistance of air, <!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1031\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\n margin-left:300.55pt;margin-top:799.5pt;width:120pt;height:120.75pt;z-index:251658240;\n mso-wrap-distance-left:7.5pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:7.5pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-right:7.5pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:7.5pt;\n mso-position-horizontal:right;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/251.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/251.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.251\" width=\"160\" height=\"161\" align=\"right\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"10\" vspace=\"10\" /><!--[endif]-->swimming exercises encourage strength building and cardiovascular development. There is very little risk for injury during water related exercises since the buoyancy of water reduces strain on your back, knees, and joints. This low impact exercise is especially good for anyone looking to increase joint range of motion or develop strength around painful joints. To add variety into a swimming routine, try including kick boards, fins, or water weights. If this equipment isn\'t available, simply running laps, lap swimming, and jumping jacks can provide a great workout. Swimming is adaptable for all ages and athletic abilities, so get the whole family moving with this fun activity. Click here for more <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=0016AezBh1UtIbifOERitKrmOst_PtrAt6mT_GD2MqadIrg1WoFdLmHmzvIeWWH2PItPFCQw4abmfW4eDLW2Sx0R3QPWUidMLI3cSY8JTaabdpevhPfQh5bTf5prvkHFcpOQVaXeC4oK-a9HaqMxb7glWUJNkr8zNphaQY_IzsUjSe74g4jq507u0LlRa3K0IeNas5CDwCS_2I=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">water workout ideas</a>.', 'Swim into Fitness ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'swim-into-fitness', '', '', '2012-07-30 14:30:10', '2012-07-30 14:30:10', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=727', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('886', '14', '2012-08-01 14:38:52', '2012-08-01 14:38:52', '<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype\n id=\"_x0000_t75\" coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\"\n path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\" filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1026\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\n margin-left:52.3pt;margin-top:0;width:103.5pt;height:171.75pt;z-index:251658240;\n mso-wrap-distance-left:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:3.75pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-right:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:3.75pt;\n mso-position-horizontal:right;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"https://origin.ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/268.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"https://origin.ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/268.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.268\" width=\"138\" height=\"229\" align=\"right\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /><!--[endif]-->August 1st marks the 11th Anniversary of Sterling Wellness Solutions.  In 2001, Claire and Keeffer Kelbaugh founded Sterling Wellness Solutions with a mission to educate employers on the benefits of implementing workplace wellness programs.\n\nAfter more than a decade of providing corporate health management programs, Sterling Wellness Solutions is now a full-service wellness company serving the national market. We remain dedicated to reducing the costs of health care by educating employees and their dependents about how to manage their health risk factors and motivating positive change.\n\nAs we continue to grow, our commitment and passion for workplace wellness is reflected in each Sterling Wellness employee. It is with great pleasure that we partner with you and your employer to provide wellness services that will impact your workplace and your overall quality of life.', 'Happy Birthday, Sterling Wellness Solutions!       ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'happy-birthday-sterling-wellness-solutions', '', '', '2012-08-01 14:38:52', '2012-08-01 14:38:52', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=732', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('887', '14', '2012-08-05 14:39:27', '2012-08-05 14:39:27', 'Vaccines help prevent many serious and potentially fatal diseases. During National Immunization Awareness Month, we encourage you to review and discuss your immunization records with your physician. Although vaccines are often thought of as an infant and childhood ritual, there are certain immunizations adults need to protect them against serious diseases as well. <!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1032\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"Boy with Immunization Card\"\n style=\'position:absolute;margin-left:327.55pt;margin-top:641.25pt;width:154.5pt;\n height:100.5pt;z-index:251658240;mso-wrap-distance-left:3.75pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-top:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-right:3.75pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-bottom:3.75pt;mso-position-horizontal:right;\n mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;mso-position-vertical-relative:line\'\n o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"https://origin.ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/64.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"https://origin.ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/64.jpg\" alt=\"Boy with Immunization Card\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.64\" width=\"206\" height=\"134\" align=\"right\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /><!--[endif]-->\nCommon adult immunizations include:\n<ul>\n	<li>Flu (Influenza)</li>\n	<li>Tetanus</li>\n	<li>Diphtheria</li>\n	<li>Pertussis</li>\n	<li>Shingles</li>\n	<li>Pneumococcal</li>\n	<li>HPV</li>\n</ul>\n<a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001MP74giHQ2cfURQtxOYmsNES_uVhncDdL4PBARI3tx549m4LxVIcWuCI1GRRJHjx82bMM-rObFLZ1aWUVeABFzTR8Qkv2sKvFewKJbzKfMWI=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Vaccines.gov</a> and <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001MP74giHQ2cfURQtxOYmsNES_uVhncDdL4PBARI3tx549m4LxVIcWuCI1GRRJHjx82bMM-rObFLYGaxPU-arC_jCL8U-Hw9XJHAYXxA0-hH4=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">immunize.org</a> are available to provide information on vaccines and immunization for infants, children, teenagers, adults, and seniors. Visit these sites to download an immunization schedule, find local clinics, or read more information on each vaccine.', 'Are Your Vaccines Current?  ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'are-your-vaccines-current', '', '', '2012-08-05 14:39:27', '2012-08-05 14:39:27', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=734', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('888', '14', '2012-08-14 14:41:03', '2012-08-14 14:41:03', 'The back to school frenzy is in full force. New notebooks, sneakers, and... healthy lunch ideas? A great way to help your child excel in school this year is to fuel them with a nutritious lunch. Most lunches can be packed the night before, allowing for plenty of time to make it to the bus stop.\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_737\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"240\" caption=\"Follow us on Pinterest for more appealing lunch ideas! Image Source: Full House\"]<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Back-to-Cool-lunches.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-737 \" title=\"Back to Cool lunches\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Back-to-Cool-lunches-300x256.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"240\" height=\"205\" /></a>[/caption]\n\nWhen pairing lunch items, be sure to include protein, complex carbohydrates, fruit, and vegetables. Whole grain bread, wheat crackers, or whole grain noodles are great sources of complex carbohydrates and fiber. Try including hard boiled eggs, nuts, deli meat, or almond butter for protein. Get creative with packaging and displaying food for your child. Packing a lunch in a visually appealing way is a great way to introduce new foods that the child might not eat otherwise. Finally, include a healthy drink such as low fat milk, 100% fruit juice, or water. Excessive sugar intake in children has been linked to hyperactivity and impaired learning abilities, so avoid sodas and sugary drinks. For more ideas on healthy kid-friendly lunches, find our \'Kid-Friendly Food\' board on <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001MP74giHQ2cfURQtxOYmsNES_uVhncDdL4PBARI3tx549m4LxVIcWuCI1GRRJHjx8SjOw8lgDsqFLOutZjghHBVy6BMXdl17L\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Pinterest</a>.', 'Back to Cool Lunches  ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'back-to-cool-lunches', '', '', '2012-08-14 14:41:03', '2012-08-14 14:41:03', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=736', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('889', '14', '2012-08-19 14:43:19', '2012-08-19 14:43:19', '<strong><em>A: </em></strong>A plant-based diet emphasizes fruits, vegetables, legumes, whole grains, nuts and seeds. Not only can a plant-based diet be rich in vitamins and minerals, but it can also be low in calories and can provide all of the protein, carbohydrates and fat that your body needs. To be sure you are getting all of the nutrients that you need, include a variety of fruits and vegetables by filling your plate with a mixture of colors.\n<table width=\"115\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"right\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"148\"> <a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Summer-2.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-740\" title=\"Summer, 2\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Summer-2-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"126\" height=\"168\" /></a><em>Summer James is the Health and Wellness Advisor for Sterling and a Certified Health Coach.</em></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\nWhile fruits and vegetables play a vital role in providing vitamins and minerals, it is also important to incorporate other healthy sources of protein and carbohydrates. Build your plate around low fat protein sources such as beans, nuts, seeds and legumes.  Be sure to incorporate complex carbs into your plant-based diet as well. Avoid refined carbohydrates that come from white bread, rice and pasta. Instead, chose complex carbohydrates that come from fruits and vegetables, oats, beans, whole grain bread, brown rice and whole wheat pastas.\n\nFinally, when eating a plant-based diet, be sure to include a source of healthy fat at each meal. Sources of healthy plant-based fats include olives, nuts, flax seeds, avocado, canola oil and olive oil. Whether you choose to make the switch to a plant-based diet or not, always remember to include a variety of foods within each group. If you choose to eat animal-based foods such eggs, meat, or dairy, select low fat versions and always fill up the majority of your plate with fruits and vegetables.', 'Ask the Expert Q: \"I\'ve heard a lot of buzz recently about plant-based diets. What qualifies as a plant-based diet, and can it provide all of the nutrition that I need?\" ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ask-the-expert-q-ive-heard-a-lot-of-buzz-recently-about-plant-based-diets-what-qualifies-as-a-plant-based-diet-and-can-it-provide-all-of-the-nutrition-that-i-need', '', '', '2012-08-19 14:43:19', '2012-08-19 14:43:19', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=739', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('890', '14', '2012-08-22 14:46:08', '2012-08-22 14:46:08', 'There\'s a reason you always end up buying more at the grocer than you had on your list. It\'s not by accident that the milk is always at the back of the supermarket. Thousands of other products are vying for your attention before the gallon of milk ends up in your cart.\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_743\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"300\" caption=\"Decisions, decisions! Most grocery stores sell over 40,000 different food products!\"]<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Supermarket.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-743\" title=\"Supermarket\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Supermarket-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>[/caption]\n\nFollow these tips to navigate the supermarket without regret:\n\n1) <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Shop the perimeter first-</span> The healthiest foods like fruits, vegetables, lean meats, and dairy products can always be found on the outskirts.\n\n2) <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Look past eye level</span>- The most expensive and often unhealthiest items are at eye level within a child\'s reach. The less expensive store brands are usually above or below the name brand.\n\n3) <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Come prepared-</span> Don\'t shop on an empty stomach or with others. Both may cause you to purchase items you wouldn\'t normally buy. Come with a list, and stick to it.\n\n4) <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Don\'t be deceived</span>- Grocers purposely place flowers and freshly baked bread at the entrance. This sensory overload sets the stage for you to purchase more items you didn\'t intend to buy.\n\n5) <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Be skeptical of a \'sale\'</span>- Ask yourself if you really need 10 of any one item to qualify for the 10 for $10 sale. Likely, it will be the same price if you buy one or two.\n\nNavigating your way to find healthy foods among thousands of products is not for the faint of heart. Take more tips from <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001MP74giHQ2cfURQtxOYmsNES_uVhncDdL4PBARI3tx549m4LxVIcWuCI1GRRJHjx82bMM-rObFLbCqfpGD4QJxhnT1d7q620BAX_8O_9SYltbmpZxlCb6Jg==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Supermarket Savvy</a> or <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001MP74giHQ2cfURQtxOYmsNES_uVhncDdL4PBARI3tx549m4LxVIcWuCI1GRRJHjx8KynguigtExqQ6e20BBu40ckfohAaLBjEghqbZivlBT4=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Mindless Eating.</a>', 'Supermarket Sweep!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'supermarket-sweep', '', '', '2012-08-22 14:46:08', '2012-08-22 14:46:08', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=742', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('891', '14', '2012-08-25 14:48:24', '2012-08-25 14:48:24', '<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1036\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\n margin-left:0;margin-top:578.25pt;width:86.25pt;height:129pt;z-index:251658240;\n mso-wrap-distance-left:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:3.75pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-right:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:3.75pt;\n mso-position-horizontal:left;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"https://origin.ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/262.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"https://origin.ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/262.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.262\" width=\"115\" height=\"172\" align=\"left\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /><!--[endif]-->Every summer, the perfect peach finds a way to make it to the local farmers\' market. Dripping with sweet juice and iconic of late summer, this fruit has as many different varieties as there are ways to prepare them. In the United States alone, over 300 varieties of peaches are grown. This nutritious fruit contains vitamins A and C, both essential for a strong immune system and healthy vision. A medium size peach has approximately 40 calories, making it a perfect portion.\n\nPeaches can be a nutritious addition to many favorite dishes. Try peach salsa, topping a salad with peach chunks, or a peach marinade for chicken or pork. A few slices of peach can jazz up a glass of ice water or unsweetened tea. Although peaches are sweet enough on their own, they make a great topper for a small scoop of low fat ice cream on a hot summer night. For more peachy ideas, visit <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001MP74giHQ2cfURQtxOYmsNES_uVhncDdL4PBARI3tx549m4LxVIcWuCI1GRRJHjx82bMM-rObFLZLeAXhfJ5FDFh7wRobNF43jCno-Im7A6e08lyVLnfgClGJO_ApKuFdMLh-HhQzUuL8VvBcdJFt5kw8vF3Xv1COM5XFwnNop_4=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Cooking Light</a>\'s 16 favorite peach recipes.', 'That\'s a Peach!   ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'thats-a-peach', '', '', '2012-08-25 14:48:24', '2012-08-25 14:48:24', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=745', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('892', '14', '2012-08-29 14:49:01', '2012-08-29 14:49:01', 'Muscle is important for daily function and mobility. As we age, muscle naturally diminishes. It\'s important to keep our muscles strong before they\'re gone. Some of the benefits of muscle mass include:<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1037\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\n margin-left:283.3pt;margin-top:761.25pt;width:102.75pt;height:135.75pt;\n z-index:251658240;mso-wrap-distance-left:7.5pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:7.5pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-right:7.5pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:7.5pt;\n mso-position-horizontal:right;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"https://origin.ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/263.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"https://origin.ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/263.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.263\" width=\"137\" height=\"181\" align=\"right\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"10\" vspace=\"10\" /><!--[endif]-->\n<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Weight management</span>- Muscle is more metabolically active than fat, causing it to burn more calories, even when sedentary.</li>\n	<li><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Better bones</span>- Strength training can increase bone mass and reduce the risk for osteoporosis.</li>\n	<li><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Reduce risk for injury</span>-  Back pain, stress fractures, and joint pain are often caused from weak surrounding muscles.</li>\n</ul>\nIf you don\'t have access to a gym or weight equipment, using your own body weight is a great way to incorporate strength training. Try increasing repetitions of push-ups, sit-ups, and pull-ups. Other strength training options include resistance bands, free weights, and weight equipment. For more information on strength training guidelines, visit the <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001MP74giHQ2cfURQtxOYmsNES_uVhncDdL4PBARI3tx549m4LxVIcWuCI1GRRJHjx8tBGV6o7ZJ5PaqSL-Z7VVnIE38mdRRKRcmSMysVQLmOQ-p8FVb1j466ZBztQvxETQ6FvcTRFnDpibP1YvgAMrG6aRa-XqE_Al4wugnrTmyJG5zPpxWPZLaA==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">American College of Sports Medicine</a>.', 'Building a Better Body with Strength Training  ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'building-a-better-body-with-strength-training', '', '', '2012-08-29 14:49:01', '2012-08-29 14:49:01', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=747', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('893', '14', '2012-09-07 19:06:55', '2012-09-07 19:06:55', '<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype\n id=\"_x0000_t75\" coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\"\n path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\" filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1026\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\n margin-left:127.3pt;margin-top:0;width:178.5pt;height:141.75pt;z-index:251658240;\n mso-wrap-distance-left:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:3.75pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-right:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:3.75pt;\n mso-position-horizontal:right;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/297.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/297.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.297\" width=\"238\" height=\"189\" align=\"right\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /><!--[endif]-->Every September, the America on the Move Foundation (AOM) challenges citizens to increase their steps in an effort to become more physically active.\n\nSmall realistic changes in lifestyle habits can eventually lead to big successes in overall health. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=0017TzL4Ft5bk0n3ZT-3nlB4aBzb1_JtbypChwXxzVtB_gAF98VTnwCQ7_Uqj3jgapM29676sgjmy7vqxuUa_LAFSxmJ0wElSV5mchkXsOfSHctCv9U0ca1JWxThtLn3RJi\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">America on the Move\'s STEPtember challenge</a> encourages participants to get an extra 2,000 steps a day, about equivalent to one mile, while also reducing 100 calories from the diet, about the serving of one tablespoon of butter. Their goal is to make Americans realize the simplicity and health benefits of making small changes in their life. Wear a pedometer to determine your current activity status, and gradually work to increase that level. A great goal to work toward is maintaining a level of 10,000 steps a day, as recommended by the Centers for Disease Control.\n\nTo join the movement of making small steps for a healthier life, visit <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=0017TzL4Ft5bk0n3ZT-3nlB4aBzb1_JtbypChwXxzVtB_gAF98VTnwCQ7_Uqj3jgapM29676sgjmy7vqxuUa_LAFSxmJ0wElSV5mchkXsOfSHctCv9U0ca1JWxThtLn3RJi\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">America on the Move</a>.', 'America is on the Move this STEPtember!       ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'america-is-on-the-move-this-steptember', '', '', '2012-09-07 19:06:55', '2012-09-07 19:06:55', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=753', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('894', '14', '2012-09-10 19:07:13', '2012-09-10 19:07:13', '<table width=\"187\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"left\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"187\"> <a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/pea.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-756\" title=\"pea on fork\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/pea-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"210\" height=\"158\" /></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p align=\"center\"><em>Fill half your plate with fruits and vegetables!</em></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\nGetting the recommended daily servings of fruits and vegetables requires planning. Although caloric needs vary by age, gender, and activity level, the American Heart Association and the American Cancer Society both recommend at least 5 servings of fruits and vegetables a day. As we recognize September as <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=0017TzL4Ft5bk3aDJ8n23tkz0oTW1UGUALogFpP0g2kDKgNsjnJy6rPn06OzK_tos13_5JJ3fBsztF9sWSvyz_K0YPQTXiPMceOr_05fomHXfWjHvp-aPH7sjXQFQOJuTZxPQaB2_7CDrs=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Fruits &amp; Veggies More Matters®</a> month, aim to fill half your plate with fruits and vegetables for a minimum of 5 servings each day. Select produce that has deep hues of color such as sweet potatoes, eggplant, berries, and spinach. Colorful fruits and vegetables offer a variety of nutrients, antioxidants, and vitamins. Most fruits and vegetables are low in calories and high in water content and fiber, making them friendly on the waistline.\n\nTake the guesswork out of meal planning and <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=0017TzL4Ft5bk0FGX60XR-r69MpIpYYpeUGXDlNnRIvtaVUxPEOEk2iPc8TwwfeerkMyB3t9G7cRSx8j2U4vVR9O0kbw0Z00M0S5pFqC6pslTa0L4cqNe6JwQc88xIdheP-tGpXmrDrUh_lXCuh8xWHyohFiG3vijLq_g6-Ffr6WTKreXfF6ov7_RKQcAm0_cWZ\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">print a two week healthy menu and shopping list</a> that outlines meals containing whole grains, lean proteins, and plenty of fruits and vegetables. Most grocery stores are filled with nontraditional produce so try a new fruit or vegetable this month such as a star fruit, spaghetti squash, or pummelo melon. Allow everyone in the family a chance to choose a vegetable they want to try.', 'Are You Eating Your Veggies? When it Comes to Fruits and Vegetables, More Matters!       ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'are-you-eating-your-veggies-when-it-comes-to-fruits-and-vegetables-more-matters', '', '', '2012-09-10 19:07:13', '2012-09-10 19:07:13', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=755', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('895', '14', '2012-09-14 19:09:48', '2012-09-14 19:09:48', '&nbsp;\n<table width=\"204\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"right\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"206\"> <a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/mature-couple-taking-pictures.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-759\" title=\"Senior Couple Using Digital Camera at Marina\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/mature-couple-taking-pictures-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p align=\"center\"><em><strong>September is Healthy Aging Month</strong></em></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\nWe\'ve all had that moment when we wish we could turn back time, take a sip from the fountain of youth, and relive our glory days. Although the term \'young\' is relative, here are a few secrets to stay young-at-heart for years to come:\n<ol start=\"1\">\n	<li><strong>Stay active</strong>- Muscle mass decreases with age. Exercise fuels the brain with oxygen and allows your physical body to stay independent and agile.</li>\n	<li><strong>Learn a new skill</strong>-Mental stimulation prevents cognitive degeneration. Try sadoku, crossword puzzles, reading, or a new hobby.</li>\n	<li><strong>Stay social</strong>-Keep your relationships healthy and balanced. That includes relationships with our spouse, friends, and family.</li>\n	<li><strong>Maintain a healthy weight</strong>- Frequent exercise and a diet full of fruits, vegetables, whole grains, and lean proteins will help keep your body young.</li>\n	<li><strong>Laugh often</strong>- Maintain a positive outlook on life and practice healthy coping mechanisms and stress management techniques.</li>\n</ol>\nTo learn more secrets to age gracefully, visit <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=0017TzL4Ft5bk3t67IpW6hQ0UT6x6d6eC3-OoAL_kj0qssmPr5BnIilWucbksGp8QCKls_SQ9AI_0SBLSX0y0z4eQpJ5gmBES6eJDgEJ7ek41dtq1Y8tphQjQ==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Healthy Aging®</a> or the Mayo Clinic\'s guide to <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=0017TzL4Ft5bk3UqHNlhYbCt0TapSLXsvasF9uF5JEP85AR3v8NDPPe0xUoSk0BoQ4xahrycYLeP0v41Vj3XYBHqG4zYiFqK_Av3weMnBY418-GTWe1AfxVUwAjHbwEn3VrsssFD3h4Bav_RCj2-GoqNA0i-kLKWQjZ\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Healthy Living.</a>', '5 Ways to Age Gracefully      ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '5-ways-to-age-gracefully', '', '', '2012-09-14 19:09:48', '2012-09-14 19:09:48', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=758', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('896', '14', '2012-09-17 19:12:27', '2012-09-17 19:12:27', '<strong><em>A: </em></strong> The lipid panel can provide important information if heart disease runs in your family. Often times, this test can be done with a simple finger-stick procedure and results\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_762\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"150\"]<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/Selma.jpg\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-762\" title=\"Selma\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/Selma-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a> Selma Witcher, RN BSN, is a Registered Nurse and the bilingual Health Coach for Sterling[/caption]\n\ncan indicate your risk for heart disease, heart attack, or stroke. A lipid panel typically includes total cholesterol, HDL cholesterol, LDL cholesterol, triglycerides, and risk ratio.\n<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Total cholesterol</span> levels should be &lt;200mg/dL and are effected by diet and activity. Your total cholesterol is a combination of HDL, LDL, and VLDL levels.</li>\n	<li><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">HDL is the \"good\" cholesterol</span> and should be greater than &gt;40 mg/dL for males or &gt;50 mg/dL for females. The higher the number the more disease fighting power your body has to prevent your arteries from blockage. You can elevate your HDL through aerobic exercise, smoking cessation, and removing trans fatty foods from your diet.</li>\n	<li><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">LDL or \"bad\" cholesterol</span> should be &lt;100 mg/dL. A diet high in saturated fat, cholesterol from animal products, and high fat dairy products can lead to a build up on the inside of your artery walls causing blockage, hardening, and narrowing of your arteries.</li>\n	<li><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Triglycerides</span> are a different type of fat that your body makes from unused carbohydrates and/or fats. Your goal number should be &lt;150 mg/dL. Elevated LDL and triglycerides are known as the \"silent killer\" because there are no signs and symptoms to elevated levels.</li>\n	<li><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">The risk ratio</span> refers to the total cholesterol divided by the HDL and is often the best indicator of heart disease. Numbers less than 4 indicate a lower risk for heart disease.</li>\n</ul>\nIf you would like to get a lipid profile test, visit our <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=0017TzL4Ft5bk0F7ZjgJ5gc0X9osZ-_DDCiWXpdh8YjEFnqZ-2ppTJQnM-OQQd_2Ncd5x7eUfXqsX_hnHvsKxAh6xe6Ry6IQB-07M6TazmGMt8DCTto1__XDFAPEHOzzmHHAQs21ciLRnQ=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Sterling Labs</a> or call 1-800-838-0337 to order your direct access lab testing. Take your requisition form into any local LabCorp, and one of our health coaches will call you to confidentially discuss your results.', 'Ask the Expert Q: \"Heart disease runs in my family, so I\'ve been told to get a lipid profile test. What does that involve, and what will the results show me?\" ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ask-the-expert-q-heart-disease-runs-in-my-family-so-ive-been-told-to-get-a-lipid-profile-test-what-does-that-involve-and-what-will-the-results-show-me', '', '', '2012-09-17 19:12:27', '2012-09-17 19:12:27', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=761', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('897', '14', '2012-09-20 19:14:12', '2012-09-20 19:14:12', '<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1027\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"Mature Couple on Beach\"\n style=\'position:absolute;margin-left:0;margin-top:205.5pt;width:131.25pt;\n height:125.25pt;z-index:251658240;mso-wrap-distance-left:3.75pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-top:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-right:3.75pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-bottom:3.75pt;mso-position-horizontal:left;\n mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;mso-position-vertical-relative:line\'\n o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/60.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/60.jpg\" alt=\"Mature Couple on Beach\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.60\" width=\"175\" height=\"167\" align=\"left\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /><!--[endif]--><strong>Attention, MEN:  This serves as your yearly reminder to get a Prostate Screening!</strong>\n\nProstate cancer is the second most common form of cancer in men, falling just behind skin cancer. The American Cancer Society recommends that men begin screening for prostate cancer starting as early as 40 for high risk individuals that have a first degree relative that has been diagnosed with the condition, but no later than 50 for low risk individuals. A blood test can also be given to detect elevated levels of Prostate Specific Antigen (PSA).  Early detection increases the chances of survival, so make an appointment with your healthcare provider today. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=otbu8wdab&amp;et=1107376337812&amp;s=0&amp;e=001ftC7Ci9RSfc6IblUu8bs41fSQAdDDAOnRGha4CNgl2JN37f4PVyYImkZS0089n3fNhGygR4C5qizK8lDU8g8jpAztOkoO0WLUyx8MccvByHVdvDhhOHPi_legWiwLWdei8tYZHBg2sybbRBDe9xCcv-Ip96K8oPdcDHroEiFmszdIa_dd4RoOfUdMK8I1Izn\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more about your risk factors, prevention, and screenings visit the American Cancer Society.</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Attention, WOMEN:  This serves as your yearly reminder to get a pelvic exam!</strong>\n\nRanked as the ninth most common cancer among women, ovarian cancer is the fifth leading cause of cancer-related deaths among females. Many patients are often asymptomatic until the cancer has progressed. A gynecologist will perform a pelvic exam by pressing on the woman\'s organs to feel their size and shape. High risk individuals may request an ultra sound, and a blood test may also be administered to determine CA-125 levels. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=otbu8wdab&amp;et=1107376337812&amp;s=0&amp;e=001ftC7Ci9RSfc6IblUu8bs41fSQAdDDAOnRGha4CNgl2JN37f4PVyYImkZS0089n3fNhGygR4C5qizK8lDU8g8jpAztOkoO0WLUyx8MccvByEnQ6Y7S0ld9xNGoICZXqEimWb8Rsf9lWjV4WW4N93C937h0Wu7_e0Psk-lI26xMsNOoxM_PpwS27FUEjcTaB_hzBFRNs9g2JQ=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">To learn more about your risk factors, prevention and screening of ovarian cancer visit the American Cancer Society.</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nIf you participate in annual screenings through your employer and Sterling Wellness, be sure and ask if a PSA or CA-125 can be added to your lab work.', 'Early Detection is Vital- September is Prostate and Ovarian Cancer Awareness Month', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'early-detection-is-vital-september-is-prostate-and-ovarian-cancer-awareness-month', '', '', '2012-09-20 19:14:12', '2012-09-20 19:14:12', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=764', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('898', '14', '2012-09-24 19:15:47', '2012-09-24 19:15:47', '<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1028\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\n margin-left:0;margin-top:489.75pt;width:136.5pt;height:90.75pt;z-index:251658240;\n mso-wrap-distance-left:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:3.75pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-right:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:3.75pt;\n mso-position-horizontal:left;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/293.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/293.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.293\" width=\"182\" height=\"121\" align=\"left\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /><!--[endif]-->Certain types of fish are an excellent source of lean protein and heart healthy omega-3 fats. The American Heart Association recommends people eat fish high in omega-3 fatty acids at least twice a week. Consuming two servings of this type of fat has been shown to reduce the risk of heart disease, inflammation, and even triglycerides.\n\nSalmon, tuna, and herring contain the most omega-3\'s, however other fish such as cod and sardines still offer similar heart protective benefits. When preparing fish, much of the health benefits are dependent on how it is prepared. Grilling or baking fish is generally recommended over frying. Fish is a great source of lean protein, helping you feel fuller longer than other foods. When considering portions, remember that one serving of fish is approximately 3 ounces, or about the size of a deck of cards. For ideas and recipes on how to prepare your next heart healthy meal, visit <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?t=fytarskab.0.7aym8skab.otbu8wdab.2757&amp;ts=S0806&amp;p=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.eatingwell.com%2Frecipes_menus%2Fcollections%2Fhealthy_salmon_recipes\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">EatingWell\'s collection of Salmon recipes.</a>', 'O\'fish\'ally a Super-food   ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ofishally-a-super-food', '', '', '2012-09-24 19:15:47', '2012-09-24 19:15:47', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=766', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('899', '14', '2012-09-27 19:16:31', '2012-09-27 19:16:31', 'Athletic injuries are on the rise. Although safety gear is commonplace in school aged children, adults are less likely to heed precautions when participating in sports and <!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\n <v:formulas>\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\n </v:formulas>\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1029\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\n margin-left:284.05pt;margin-top:684.75pt;width:102.75pt;height:110.25pt;\n z-index:251658240;mso-wrap-distance-left:7.5pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:7.5pt;\n mso-wrap-distance-right:7.5pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:7.5pt;\n mso-position-horizontal:right;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\n <v:imagedata src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/294.jpg\"/>\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs041/1103500019310/img/294.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.294\" width=\"137\" height=\"147\" align=\"right\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"10\" vspace=\"10\" /><!--[endif]-->recreational activities. Concussions, torn ligaments, and muscle injuries can happen at any age during any sport. As adult sports leagues and community recreation clubs become more popular, it is important that adults take necessary measures to prevent sports injuries as well.\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Wear appropriate safety gear</strong>- Helmets, shin guards, and mouth pieces are all relatively inexpensive pieces of equipment for the amount of protection they offer.</li>\n	<li><strong>Stay in shape</strong>- Maintaining adequate fitness levels year-round will help reduce muscle injuries and stress fractures on game day.</li>\n	<li><strong>Form over function</strong>- Practice proper form for your sport to reduce repetitive and overused muscle injuries.</li>\n</ul>\nFor a complete list of sports injury prevention tips and resources, visit <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?t=fytarskab.0.6aym8skab.otbu8wdab.2757&amp;ts=S0806&amp;p=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.stopsportsinjuries.org%2F\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Stop Sports Injuries</a>.', 'Protect your Inner Athlete  ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'protect-your-inner-athlete', '', '', '2012-09-27 19:16:31', '2012-09-27 19:16:31', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=768', '0', 'post', '', '0');
