INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1316', '14', '2012-10-26 19:49:11', '2012-10-26 19:49:11', '<a href=\"http://bit.ly/PHFstx\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-1295\" title=\"health park 004\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/health-park-004.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"381\" height=\"214\" /></a>\r\n<h2 style=\"padding-left: 270px;\"> <strong>Wellness 24 / 7</strong></h2>\r\n<blockquote>Sterling’s Health Park Program provides participants with access to the tools and support that can truly impact overall well-being.</blockquote>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 120px;\"><a href=\"http://bit.ly/PHFstx\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1234 alignnone\" title=\"HP-login\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/HP-login.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"216\" height=\"48\" /></a></p>\r\nSterling Wellness Solutions utilizes web-based technology for delivery of online wellness services as a component of our total wellness approach.  The Health Park portal allows program participants to have access to their wellness initiative anytime, anywhere, in a secure environment that protects personal health information.  Health Park provides access to wellness beginning with a Health Risk Assessment. A customized report coupled with access to our certified health coaches and nursing staff, can provide a platform for lifestyle change.  Interactive education through online action plans can reinforce the message of healthy living, while health challenges provide opportunities for engagement and change. Participants also have access to a Personal Electronic Health Record, encouraging them to take control of their health care.  The Health Park program also allows Sterling to track and manage company incentive programs, giving participants access to their rewards and points.\r\n\r\nSterling’s health coaching team also utilizes Health Park to engage employees in their personal health journey, track the progress of participants, and interact in a secure, web-based environment.', 'Health Park Program', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '63-revision-48', '', '', '2012-10-26 19:49:11', '2012-10-26 19:49:11', '', '63', 'http://dev.sterling-wellness.com/63-revision-48/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1317', '1', '2012-10-17 14:43:06', '2012-10-17 14:43:06', '<h2>Meet the Health Coaches</h2>\r\nSterling Wellness Solutions is ready to help you make health and wellness part of your everyday routine.  Our team of professionals includes a Medical Director, registered nurses, registered dietitians, fitness experts, certified wellness experts and health coaches, with the support of a complete administrative staff and communications team.  Our health coaches are degreed professionals with additional certifications from the Cooper Institute, a nationally recognized training program based on research in the areas of health and fitness best-practices.  Members of our team also have certifications from WELCOA, National Wellness Institute, NSCA, ACSM and more.\r\n<blockquote>Sterling’s degreed team of health and wellness practitioners focuses on lifestyle coaching through a positive, participant-led approach. Our health coaches have additional certifications from the Cooper Institute, a nationally recognized training program based on research in the areas of health and fitness best-practices.  Members of our team also have certifications from WELCOA, National Wellness Institute, NSCA, ACSM and more.</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[one_third]\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4><strong>Heather Hedrick</strong></h4>\r\nis a graduate of the University of Louisiana at Lafayette where she majored in Health Promotion and Wellness. Heather is certified as a Healthy Behaviors Coach by The Cooper Institute.  She also holds certifications as a Youth Adolescent Fitness Instructor, Medic First Aid CPR/AED Instructor, and Licensed Massage Therapist. She has been working in the corporate health field for 5 years and is a member of WELCOA. Heather has a passion for health education and promotion, and is honored to educate her clients on the importance of health and wellness.\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4><strong>Jaclyn Beaty</strong></h4>\r\nis a graduate of the University of Missouri where she earned a Bachelor’s in Nutritional Sciences with an emphasis in Nutrition and Fitness. She is a certified Wellness Practitioner through the National Wellness Institute and a certified Personal Trainer through the National Strength and Conditioning Association.  Jaclyn is certified as a Healthy Behaviors Coach from the Cooper Institute and she has earned WELCOA Faculty Status for extensive education through the Wellness Council of America.  She is CPR and AED-certified from the American Heart Association for Basic Life Support for Healthcare Providers.  Jaclyn has been promoting corporate and workplace wellness for over 5 years and is privileged to educate and motivate change to a higher level of well-being.\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4><strong>Summer James</strong></h4>\r\nis a graduate of Murray State University where she earned a Bachelor of Science in Exercise Science with an emphasis in Therapeutic Wellness.  Summer is a certified Healthy Behaviors Coach by the Cooper Institute. Other certifications include WELCOA Well Workplace University Level III, Exercise and Cancer Recovery Specialist. She is CPR and AED-certified from the American Heart Association for Basic Life Support for Healthcare Providers.  With nearly four years of experience in corporate wellness, she is passionate about promoting and motivating health and well-being in others.\r\n\r\n[/one_third]\r\n\r\n[one_third]\r\n<h4><strong>Marie Beechy</strong></h4>\r\nis a Registered Nurse who graduated from Indiana University, Kokomo. She has been in the healthcare industry for over 8 years and has been promoting preventive health and wellness for four years. Marie is certified as a Healthy Behaviors Coach from the Cooper Institute with experience in mental healthcare. Marie is currently pursuing her Master’s degree in Nursing.\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4><strong>Dawn Beverage</strong></h4>\r\nis a graduate of University of Louisiana at Lafayette where she earned a Bachelor of Science in Kinesiology with an emphasis in Health Promotion and Wellness. Dawn has received certifications from the Cooper Institute for Coaching Healthy Behaviors and the American Heart Association BLS for Healthcare Providers (CPR and AED).  She is also a member of The Wellness Council of America. She enjoys sharing her passion for health and wellness to help others achieve personal goals, healthy lifestyles, improve well-being and increase longevity.\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4><strong>René Broussard</strong></h4>\r\nis a graduate of Louisiana Technical College’s Licensed Practical Nurse program. She has been in the healthcare industry for 4 years and has a passion for health promotion and wellness. René is CPR and AED-certified in accordance with the American Heart Association for Basic Life Support for Healthcare Providers.  She is experienced in Long Term Acute Care nursing with strengths in the Occupational and Mental health fields.  She enjoys promoting healthy lifestyles with emphasis on safety and prevention to encourage overall well-being and increase longevity.\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4><strong>Janice Beard</strong></h4>\r\nis a graduate of the Nicholls State University nursing program. With nearly 40 years of nursing experience, Janice has been exposed to many areas of healthcare including positions as a Staff Nurse, Head Nurse, Director of Education, and a Director or Nursing. She brings an exceptional depth of knowledge and experience to Sterling’s team of Health Coaches. Janice enjoys  providing education through individual health coaching consultations on the preventative side of wellness.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[/one_third]\r\n\r\n[one_third]\r\n<h4><strong>Alyce DeGravelle</strong></h4>\r\nMS, LDN, RD, received her Master’s degree in Nutrition and Dietetics in 1999 from the University of New Mexico.  She is a Registered Dietitian and a Certified Personal Trainer with additional training from the Cooper Institute. Alyce is a member of the Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics, with experience working as a nutrition consultant for numerous employee wellness programs.  Alyce offers general nutrition counseling as well as Medical Nutrition Therapy for weight loss/gain, pre-diabetes and diabetes, cardiac rehab, sports nutrition and other nutrition-related conditions. Alyce offers personal nutrition assessments, research-based nutrition information and education to help individuals develop the skills necessary to improve their health and well-being and manage chronic conditions.\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4><strong>Selma Witcher</strong></h4>\r\nis a Registered Nurse who graduated with a Bachelor of Science in Nursing from Bethel University in St. Paul, MN. Proficient in Spanish, Selma has spent two years in Central America teaching Latino cultures about basic nutrition, medicine administration, and proper medical and hygiene care.  Selma holds a Public Health Nursing License and is CPR and PALS-certified. She is currently working toward becoming a Certified Diabetes Educator. Selma has a passion for Spanish speaking cultures and preventative health care education.\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4><strong>Tiffiany Cormier</strong></h4>\r\nis a Licensed Practical Nurse with six years of experience in the medical field. She has been coaching wellness participants for five years.  Tiffiany is CPR and AED-certified from the American Heart Association for Basic Life Support for Healthcare Providers.  She works closely with Sterling’s Medical Director to define high risk parameters and monitor participant results and health risks.\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4><strong>Allison Flynn</strong></h4>\r\nis a graduate of Nicholls State University where she earned a Bachelor of Science in Dietetics from the College of Nursing and Allied Health. While pursuing her degree, Allison was a part of the Colonel’s soccer team for 4 years.  She completed her dietetic internship in at Southern University A &amp; M College to become a registered and licensed dietitian.  Allison is a member of the Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics and the Bayou District Dietetic Association.  Allison is CPR and AED-certified through the American Heart Association.  Her passion is promoting proper nutrition practices and providing education on prevention and management of all diseases through nutrition.\r\n\r\n[/one_third]', 'Health Coach Profiles', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '97-revision-v1', '', '', '2012-10-17 14:43:06', '2012-10-17 14:43:06', '', '97', 'http://dev.sterling-wellness.com/97-revision-22/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1318', '14', '2012-10-25 12:58:54', '2012-10-25 12:58:54', '<h1>We Are Wellness</h1>\r\n<h3>As a provider of comprehensive corporate wellness programs for more than a decade, Sterling Wellness Solutions is a proven leader in the industry.</h3>\r\nWe work with clients to create a customized approach to building a culture of wellness within their organizations. Our fully integrated software program, Health Park, can provide a plan to fit the needs and budget of any size group. Utilizing our combined onsite, online and telephonic approach, we can provide health screenings and assessments, personal health coaching, educational support and incentive programs that can affect your bottom line.\r\n\r\nSterling’s mission is reflected in the commitment, passion and experience of our team.  Under the leadership of owner and president, Claire Kelbaugh, alongside our Medical Director, Dr. Stephen Cannon, our professionals include registered nurses, registered dietitians, fitness experts, personal trainers, certified wellness experts and health coaches, with the support of a complete administrative staff and communications team.  Our health coaches are degreed professionals with additional certifications from the Cooper Institute, a nationally recognized training program based on research in the areas of health and fitness best-practices.  Members of our team also have certifications from WELCOA, National Wellness Institute, NSCA, ACSM and more. Our commitment to service and our goal to provide a professional and positive experience for every participant remains a part of our daily operations.\r\n<h2>Our Mission</h2>\r\n<h5>Sterling Wellness Solutions is committed to positively affecting the health and well-being of workplace populations to impact the productivity and success of our client companies.  Our dedicated team of practitioners serves to deliver comprehensive wellness services to our client partnerships and their employees to reduce health risk factors and decrease health care expenditures.</h5>', 'Who We Are', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '13-revision-35', '', '', '2012-10-25 12:58:54', '2012-10-25 12:58:54', '', '13', 'http://dev.sterling-wellness.com/13-revision-35/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1319', '14', '2012-10-04 13:33:45', '2012-10-04 13:33:45', '<h2>An in depth look to your\r\npopulation\'s health.</h2>\r\nSimply completing a wellness screening is not enough. It’s how you use the comprehensive information you receive from the screenings and HRAs that makes the change. Our aggregate reports provide an in-depth look at your population’s overall health.\r\n\r\nEmployers groups of 50 or more will receive a confidential aggregate summary report with an analysis of health risks including population profiles, identification of high risk participants, year-to-year comparisons, and participation tracking. Sterling’s confidential aggregate reporting respects the privacy of participants and follows HIPAA disclosure regulations. Reports can be broken down by location, job status and demographics.\r\n<h2><strong>Comprehensive aggregate reporting includes:</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Population and demographic report<ins cite=\"mailto:Kayla%20Link\" datetime=\"2012-08-10T16:27\"></ins></li>\r\n	<li>Biometric and lab results</li>\r\n	<li>Lifestyle results</li>\r\n	<li>Readiness to change</li>\r\n	<li>Health status by risk group</li>\r\n	<li>Preventive exam compliance</li>\r\n	<li>Chronic disease impact</li>\r\n	<li>Future disease risk and predictive modeling</li>\r\n	<li>Trend reporting</li>\r\n	<li>Quarterly health coaching reports and utilization</li>\r\n	<li>Physician referral reports</li>\r\n	<li>Incentive tracking report</li>\r\n	<li>Participation report</li>\r\n	<li>Daily activity reports for screenings</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<blockquote>Sterling will also facilitate satisfaction surveys either through online survey tools or paper surveys at the completion of the screening process or the contract year.  This helps identify areas for improvement and gives participants a voice in the process.</blockquote>\r\nA Return on Investment (ROI) depends greatly on the type and quality of wellness programs being implemented. Health management style programs, such as those Sterling offers, can experience up to a 3:1 return on investment.  True tracking of ROI requires that companies release or obtain figures for healthcare expenditures before, during and after a program.\r\n\r\n<strong><em> </em></strong>', 'Benchmarking & Reporting', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '67-revision-13', '', '', '2012-10-04 13:33:45', '2012-10-04 13:33:45', '', '67', 'http://dev.sterling-wellness.com/67-revision-13/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1320', '14', '2012-09-25 18:57:30', '2012-09-25 18:57:30', '<blockquote>Health screenings are an essential step in a comprehensive wellness program. Lab work and biometric screenings can provide accurate data for participants and employers to create a benchmark to measure improvement and success.</blockquote>\r\nCoupled with our Health Park program and HRA’s, lab and biometric screenings create the basis for a wellness initiative focused on results. Sterling feels strongly that every program participant should “know their numbers” and gain a better understanding of how to affect lifestyle changes based on identified risk factors.\r\n\r\nSterling specializes in comprehensive testing that focuses on complete health management. Screening packages, including finger stick and venipuncture options, can be customized to fit the needs of your company.  Our friendly and certified screening technicians can conduct screenings at your business to reduce lost time and ensure accurate reporting. Our team will load all results into the individual’s Health Risk Assessment and Electronic Personal Health Record.  Employers have the benefit of accurate screening data through our comprehensive aggregate reports.  These blind reports provide a better understanding of the overall health of your workforce, giving the information needed to target risk areas while respecting the privacy of individual participants. Offsite screening options are also available.\r\n\r\nAs with all results gathered by Sterling, responses are strictly confidential. Our experienced screening technicians place priority on respecting the privacy and confidentiality of each participant. Results are processed in CLIA-certified laboratories, providing results that are respected by doctors.  As an advocate of physician/patient relationships, participants can authorize Sterling to share results with a personal healthcare provider.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Health Screenings', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '31-revision-8', '', '', '2012-09-25 18:57:30', '2012-09-25 18:57:30', '', '31', 'http://dev.sterling-wellness.com/31-revision-8/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
