INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1462', '14', '2012-10-20 22:00:28', '2012-10-20 22:00:28', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/spinach.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-1463 alignright\" title=\"spinach\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/spinach.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"175\" height=\"175\" /></a>\r\n\r\nReferred to by dietitians as a super-food, spinach is home to a host of disease prevention properties. Popeye made this leafy green famous to children, and his nutrition advice was worthy of following. This vegetable contains a rich source of phytochemicals, antioxidants, and vitamins necessary for healthy vision, muscle building, and disease fighting power. It is also high in potassium, a nutrient that helps control heart rate and blood pressure.  Spinach is known for its high iron content, which is beneficial to those with iron deficiency anemia.\r\n\r\nSpinach can be eaten raw, steamed, cooked, or sauteed. Wash leaves in cold water before use, and freeze for later use in casseroles and soups. Enjoy it fresh in salads and on sandwiches. Disguise spinach to the picky eater by adding finely chopped spinach to pasta dishes, smoothies, and even sweets like brownies! For more healthy recipes and cooking tips, visit <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?t=a4k7f9kab.0.mv4vc7kab.otbu8wdab.2757&amp;ts=S0818&amp;p=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.eatingwell.com%2Frecipes_menus%2Fcollections%2Fhealthy_spinach_recipes\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">EatingWell</a>\'s collection of spinach recipes.', 'Nutrition Advice from Popeye', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '1462', '', '', '2012-12-06 22:06:13', '2012-12-06 22:06:13', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1462', '0', 'post', '', '0');
