uits and vegetables. To protect yourself from non-organic foods, always wash produce in clean water and eat fruits and vegetables in season.', 'Ask the Expert- Organic Foods', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1490-revision', '', '', '2012-12-06 22:31:09', '2012-12-06 22:31:09', '', '1490', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/1490-revision/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1493', '14', '2012-12-01 22:31:35', '2012-12-01 22:31:35', '[caption id=\"attachment_1494\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"175\"]<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/Brussels-Sprouts.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-1494 \" title=\"Brussels Sprouts\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/Brussels-Sprouts.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"175\" height=\"175\" /></a> Roasted Brussels sprouts from <a href=\"http://allrecipes.com/recipe/roasted-brussels-sprouts/\">AllRecipies</a>[/caption]\r\n\r\nNamed after the city in Belgium where they originated, Brussels sprouts are one of the most powerful disease fighting foods. As a cruciferous vegetable, Brussels sprouts are in the same family as broccoli, cauliflower, and cabbage. This group of vegetables contains sulforaphane, a compound believed to have potent anticancer properties. Brussels sprouts have been shown to provide protection against colon, lung, prostate, and endometrial cancers. Other studies show these miniature cabbages can suppress the growth of breast cancer cells and detoxify the body of cancer-causing chemicals.\r\n\r\nWith only 60 calories in 1 cup of cooked sprouts, this veggie is also loaded with vitamin C, iron, and vitamin K. Drizzle a little olive oil over your sprouts and try them steamed, roasted, or grilled as kabobs.', 'Cancer Fighting Brussels Sprouts', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'cancer-fighting-brussels-sprouts', '', '', '2012-12-06 22:33:45', '2012-12-06 22:33:45', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1493', '0', 'post', '', '0');
