INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1514', '14', '2012-11-16 16:49:25', '2012-11-16 16:49:25', '<h2>Meet the Health Coaches</h2>\r\n<blockquote>Sterling’s degreed team of health and wellness practitioners focuses on lifestyle coaching through a positive, participant-led approach. Our health coaches have additional training from the Cooper Institute, a nationally recognized training program based on research in the areas of health and fitness best-practices.  Members of our team also have certifications from WELCOA, National Wellness Institute, NSCA, ACSM and more. <a title=\"Contact a Health Coach\" href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/worksite-wellness-programs/health-management-solutions/health-coaching/contact-a-health-coach/\">Contact a Health Coach!</a></blockquote>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n[one_third]\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4><strong>Heather Hedrick</strong></h4>\r\nis a graduate of the University of Louisiana at Lafayette where she majored in Health Promotion and Wellness. Heather is certified as a Healthy Behaviors Coach by The Cooper Institute.  She also holds certifications as a Youth Adolescent Fitness Instructor, Medic First Aid CPR/AED Instructor, and Licensed Massage Therapist. She has been working in the corporate health field for 5 years and is a member of WELCOA. Heather has a passion for health education and promotion, and is honored to educate her clients on the importance of health and wellness.\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4><strong>Jaclyn Beaty</strong></h4>\r\nis a graduate of the University of Missouri where she earned a Bachelor’s in Nutritional Sciences with an emphasis in Nutrition and Fitness. She is a certified Wellness Practitioner through the National Wellness Institute and a certified Personal Trainer through the National Strength and Conditioning Association.  Jaclyn is certified as a Healthy Behaviors Coach from the Cooper Institute and she has earned WELCOA Faculty Status for extensive education through the Wellness Council of America.  She is CPR and AED-certified from the American Heart Association for Basic Life Support for Healthcare Providers.  Jaclyn has been promoting corporate and workplace wellness for over 5 years and is privileged to educate and motivate change to a higher level of well-being.\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4><strong>Summer James</strong></h4>\r\nis a graduate of Murray State University where she earned a Bachelor of Science in Exercise Science with an emphasis in Therapeutic Wellness.  Summer is a certified Healthy Behaviors Coach by the Cooper Institute. Other certifications include WELCOA Well Workplace University Level III, Exercise and Cancer Recovery Specialist. She is CPR and AED-certified from the American Heart Association for Basic Life Support for Healthcare Providers.  With nearly four years of experience in corporate wellness, she is passionate about promoting and motivating health and well-being in others.\r\n\r\n[/one_third]\r\n\r\n[one_third]\r\n<h4><strong>Marie Beechy</strong></h4>\r\nis a Registered Nurse who graduated from Indiana University, Kokomo. She has been in the healthcare industry for over 8 years and has been promoting preventive health and wellness for four years. Marie is certified as a Healthy Behaviors Coach from the Cooper Institute with experience in mental healthcare. Marie is currently pursuing her Master’s degree in Nursing.\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4><strong>Dawn Beverage</strong></h4>\r\nis a graduate of University of Louisiana at Lafayette where she earned a Bachelor of Science in Kinesiology with an emphasis in Health Promotion and Wellness. Dawn has received certifications from the Cooper Institute for Coaching Healthy Behaviors and the American Heart Association BLS for Healthcare Providers (CPR and AED).  She is also a member of The Wellness Council of America. She enjoys sharing her passion for health and wellness to help others achieve personal goals, healthy lifestyles, improve well-being and increase longevity.\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4><strong>René Broussard</strong></h4>\r\nis a graduate of Louisiana Technical College’s Licensed Practical Nurse program. She has been in the healthcare industry for 4 years and has a passion for health promotion and wellness. René is CPR and AED-certified in accordance with the American Heart Association for Basic Life Support for Healthcare Providers.  She is experienced in Long Term Acute Care nursing with strengths in the Occupational and Mental health fields.  She enjoys promoting healthy lifestyles with emphasis on safety and prevention to encourage overall well-being and increase longevity.\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4><strong>Janice Beard</strong></h4>\r\nis a graduate of the Nicholls State University nursing program. With nearly 40 years of nursing experience, Janice has been exposed to many areas of healthcare including positions as a Staff Nurse, Head Nurse, Director of Education, and a Director or Nursing. She brings an exceptional depth of knowledge and experience to Sterling’s team of Health Coaches. Janice enjoys  providing education through individual health coaching consultations on the preventative side of wellness.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[/one_third]\r\n\r\n[one_third]\r\n<h4><strong>Alyce DeGravelle</strong></h4>\r\nMS, LDN, RD, received her Master’s degree in Nutrition and Dietetics in 1999 from the University of New Mexico.  She is a Registered Dietitian and a Cooper Institute Certified Personal Trainer. Alyce is a member of the Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics, with experience working as a nutrition consultant for numerous employee wellness programs.  Alyce offers general nutrition counseling as well as Medical Nutrition Therapy for weight loss/gain, pre-diabetes and diabetes, cardiac rehab, sports nutrition and other nutrition-related conditions. Alyce offers personal nutrition assessments, research-based nutrition information and education to help individuals develop the skills necessary to improve their health and well-being and manage chronic conditions.\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4><strong>Selma Witcher</strong></h4>\r\nis a Registered Nurse who graduated with a Bachelor of Science in Nursing from Bethel University in St. Paul, MN. Proficient in Spanish, Selma has spent two years in Central America teaching Latino cultures about basic nutrition, medicine administration, and proper medical and hygiene care.  Selma holds a Public Health Nursing License and is CPR and PALS-certified. She is currently working toward becoming a Certified Diabetes Educator. Selma has a passion for Spanish speaking cultures and preventative health care education.\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4><strong>Tiffiany Cormier</strong></h4>\r\nis a Licensed Practical Nurse with six years of experience in the medical field. She has been coaching wellness participants for five years.  Tiffiany is CPR and AED-certified from the American Heart Association for Basic Life Support for Healthcare Providers.  She works closely with Sterling’s Medical Director to define high risk parameters and monitor participant results and health risks.\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4><strong>Allison Flynn</strong></h4>\r\nis a graduate of Nicholls State University where she earned a Bachelor of Science in Dietetics from the College of Nursing and Allied Health. While pursuing her degree, Allison was a part of the Colonel’s soccer team for 4 years.  She completed her dietetic internship in at Southern University A &amp; M College to become a registered and licensed dietitian.  Allison is a member of the Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics and the Bayou District Dietetic Association.  Allison is CPR and AED-certified through the American Heart Association.  Her passion is promoting proper nutrition practices and providing education on prevention and management of all diseases through nutrition.\r\n\r\n[/one_third]', 'Health Coach Profiles', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '97-revision-v1', '', '', '2012-11-16 16:49:25', '2012-11-16 16:49:25', '', '97', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/97-revision-26/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1516', '14', '2013-01-03 18:36:17', '2013-01-03 18:36:17', 'Sterling Wellness Solutions is looking for the best and brightest individuals to join a dynamic and talented team. Our multi-dimensional approach to wellness requires creative thinking, industry knowledge, and a unified mission of introducing wellness in an exciting new light. Please use the form below to contact us if you are interested in employment with our team.\r\n<h4><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Current positions available</strong></span>:</h4>\r\n<strong>Fitness Expert</strong> (Part-Time/PRN)- Must be proficient at conducting step test and sit-and-reach, and knowledgeable with other general health and fitness information. Ability to take manual blood pressure is preferred. Early mornings and local travel throughout Lafourche and Terrebonne Parish required. Please submit resume below.\r\n\r\n[gravityform id=\"1\" name=\"Careers\" title=\"false\" description=\"false\" ajax=\"true\"]', 'Careers', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-01-03 18:36:17', '2013-01-03 18:36:17', '', '8', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/8-revision-5/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1517', '14', '2013-01-06 17:39:08', '2013-01-06 17:39:08', '<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\r\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\r\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\r\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\r\n <v:formulas>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\r\n </v:formulas>\r\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\r\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\r\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1026\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\r\n margin-left:337.3pt;margin-top:208.5pt;width:165pt;height:108.75pt;z-index:251658240;\r\n mso-wrap-distance-left:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:3.75pt;\r\n mso-wrap-distance-right:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:3.75pt;\r\n mso-position-horizontal:right;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\r\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\r\n <v:imagedata src=\"https://imgssl.constantcontact.com/ui/stock1/old-man-woman.jpg\"/>\r\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\r\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"https://imgssl.constantcontact.com/ui/stock1/old-man-woman.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"220\" height=\"145\" align=\"right\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /><!--[endif]-->Receiving a compliment can have a powerful effect to your self-esteem, but giving compliments can also be a beneficial boost to your health. Giving or receiving, it\'s fair to say both sides benefit from a compliment. Smiling, laughter, and praise all release endorphins and serotonin - feel good chemicals that can decrease stress and anxiety.\r\n\r\n<strong><em>\"Particularly in the workplace, compliments can have a contagious effect. The sense of positivity empowers optimism and optimism helps us to live in a better way.\" </em></strong><em>National Compliment Day, 2013</em>\r\n\r\nCelebrate Compliment Day on January 24 by setting a goal to lift the spirit of at least one person every day. Many people are motivated and valued by genuine praise. It just may be what they need to hear to get through a difficult situation.', 'A Compliment a Day Goes a Long Way         ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-compliment-a-day-goes-a-long-way', '', '', '2013-02-06 17:40:10', '2013-02-06 17:40:10', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1517', '0', 'post', '', '0');
