otassium, vitamin E, and iron. The small green package is also home to antioxidants and phytochemicals that destroy free radicals and offer protection from diseases.\r\n\r\nThe pistachio is a great weight-friendly food, thanks to its high source of fiber and protein to keep you feeling full. Taking time to peel the shell slows the speed at which you can eat the nut. Additionally, seeing your pile of shells offers a visual cue as to how much you\'ve consumed. A handful of pistachios, about thirty nuts, offers a crunchy 100-calorie snack. More than just a snack food, pistachios can also be incorporated into baking, pestos, and marinades. Find recipes and snack ideas from <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001qel0SAE1-vKA0YqRxeaAvbPC4iyN4w25k1-KcuevIVFpa8gUFgzYlCeQiAe2hXVmi2fG7dsGFVWeBNn0nwXHlezoXvPm9TAKpqHHMXUYbuN7IOE8aVnUBAO9hGQjQTxV\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">AmericanPistachioNuts.org.</a>', 'Nuts for Pistachios  ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'nuts-for-pistachios', '', '', '2013-02-06 17:47:09', '2013-02-06 17:47:09', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1529', '0', 'post', '', '0');
