INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1583', '14', '2013-03-06 19:16:30', '2013-03-06 19:16:30', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/certified_gluten.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-1584\" title=\"certified_gluten\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/certified_gluten-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>Gluten-free diets are causing quite a stir these days. Celebrities are tweeting about them, fitness trainers are praising them, and consumers are downright confused by them. In recent years, attention has been drawn to gluten as increasingly more people are diagnosed with Celiac Disease, gluten sensitivity, and Irritable Bowel Syndrome (IBS).\r\n\r\nGluten is a protein found in many grains and acts as a glue to bind ingredients together. When identifying foods that contain gluten, remember the acronym BROWS; <strong>b</strong>arley, <strong>r</strong>ye, <strong>o</strong>ats, <strong>w</strong>heat, and <strong>s</strong>pelt. Gluten is not naturally occurring in oats, however they are often harvested and processed along with wheat, contaminating them with gluten proteins. Although these grain products have been in the food supply for thousands of years, modern food processing has hybridized these grains to create a product with higher gluten content. This process could explain the sharp increase in gluten sensitivity in recent years.\r\n\r\nThose with gluten intolerance often experience serious gastrointestinal changes, inflammation, or bloating. Do not attempt to diagnose yourself without seeking the expert opinion of a physician. These grains are an essential source of fiber, B vitamins, and minerals and shouldn\'t be avoided unless advised by a medical professional. Visit these links for more information on <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=0013vIR_kJ1jqWHFjn4IUtp2RxP4-JV2iYbPYBTwkgQklMq5qNO1xXaoJBmPcPr132zRi-n5jHGNMj_VXz2jMBeRhaobOCNB7Yd0SstHsB_mzWOoMQ7KjKCRA==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">gluten</a> and <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=0013vIR_kJ1jqVs1MK0ckkzQtaWtMcOXey2DPMg9tNSGYNKMXpDPjoyMmteyf3_IjgMNm8ufqEiDZwYCPRG4I0arfxeavL0cSSRkdavQbge_bBZaG0MoAtuU2LLqoYyAvd4UW1dWwzd0HlYr_Meo5bOizL1hwSxqVI5\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">gluten-free diets</a>.', 'Is Gluten-Free Right for Me?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'is-gluten-free-right-for-me', '', '', '2013-03-06 19:16:30', '2013-03-06 19:16:30', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1583', '0', 'post', '', '0');
