INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1596', '14', '2013-03-21 19:48:13', '2013-03-21 19:48:13', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/kale.jpg\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-1597 alignleft\" title=\"kale\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/kale-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>Few foods can rival the super nutrition of kale. From the same family as broccoli, Brussels sprouts, and cabbage, kale contains a whopping 45 different flavonoids. These disease fighting compounds have risk-lowering powers against colon, breast, bladder, and prostate cancers. According to WebMD, one cup of chopped raw kale provides more than 100% of the daily value of vitamins A, C, and K. This leafy green also contains lutein, a carotenoid essential for healthy vision. Kale is also a good source of iron and fiber.\r\n\r\nWhen preparing, cut the center stem out to remove some bitterness and toughness. Kale can be sauteed, steamed, or baked in the form of chips. Try replacing spinach in recipes with this superior rival, or use chopped kale in soups and casseroles. Although kale can be purchased year round, its peak season is middle of winter through spring. If you want to get really adventurous, try different varieties such as purple or white.', 'Kale\'s Incredible Nutrition', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'kales-incredible-nutrition', '', '', '2013-03-06 19:52:40', '2013-03-06 19:52:40', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1596', '0', 'post', '', '0');
