INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1620', '14', '2013-04-22 21:42:34', '2013-04-22 21:42:34', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/garlic1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-1621\" title=\"garlic\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/garlic1-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>The tiny garlic clove is widely recognized as one of the most powerful flavor enhancers of food and most potent home remedy for illness. Often linked to folklore claiming it\'s pungent enough to scare vampires away, garlic\'s potency can also enhance the immune system, improve blood pressure, fight allergies, and detoxify the system from contaminants.\r\n\r\nGarlic belongs to the allium family which is also home to onions, chives, and leeks. The potent sulfur compound allicin can act as a powerful antibiotic against germs. Garlic\'s compounds also have the ability to fight off cancer, particularly breast, prostate, and colon cancers.\r\n\r\nTry minced garlic in soups and casseroles, or <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001aFzMCgwQ4dVnuWJ8dzLF8GOfxuAIdQ0SEYXnUYjnaRJEWKIEMpaJFdrtNG6rQUnJp_gurzJDSe7_0DYqCJOWSsbFaOotNm1apnN2QWXzrMyfPvMsx9SjIGs3BPaPk4jKm6qL_uF4mQZqFC2m7idWpn0FEugI_Rpz\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">roast garlic</a> with olive oil for a more mild flavor. Use moderation when eating garlic, as excess can cause heartburn and leave a distinct odor on the skin and breath.', 'Thank Goodness for Garlic   ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'thank-goodness-for-garlic', '', '', '2013-04-05 21:43:32', '2013-04-05 21:43:32', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1620', '0', 'post', '', '0');
