INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1634', '14', '2013-04-17 01:38:37', '2013-04-17 01:38:37', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Rachel-Garrison1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1637\" title=\"Rachel Garrison\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Rachel-Garrison1-300x233.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"233\" /></a>A NEW LEASE ON LIFE is how Rachel Garrison would describe her recent weight loss success.  As a participant of Sterling’s weight loss program, Rachel checks in weekly with Marie Beechy, RN, a Sterling health coach, for progress tracking and motivation. “I love the accountability of checking in with Marie. I want to be able to tell her something positive,” she states.\r\n\r\nRachel started her weight loss journey shortly after New Year’s Day in 2010. She was shopping for new clothes and became quickly discouraged when size 18 pants were all that fit. Within a year, she had dropped 45 lbs and started tracking her calorie intake and physical activity on MyFitnessPal. She was exercising regularly and still hit a weight loss plateau. “Marie gave me the best tip ever,” she proclaims. “Add strength training!” On top of her typical cardiovascular regimen at the gym, Rachel has included her own strength training circuit 4-5 days a week. Rachel admits getting to the gym is the hardest part, but then once she’s there, she makes every minute count.\r\n\r\nExercising was never as big of a struggle as eating in moderation. “I’ve always struggled with portion control,” she confesses. Rachel’s typical lunch is a deli style sandwich with as many veggies as one can stack on top; beets, carrots, spinach, tomatoes just to name a few. She’s not ashamed to admit she has a vice for chocolate and ice cream. She allows herself 1 snack size of hershey’s chocolate or a sugar free jello cup to satisfy her sweet tooth.\r\n\r\nHer biggest hurdle to overcome was to stop making excuses. With two kids, a husband, and a dog at home, Rachel had to make her health a priority. Although she has not hit her goal weight yet, she is more motivated and confident. Rachel states, “I will never go back to my original weight again.”', 'A New Lease on Life', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-new-lease-on-life', '', '', '2013-04-15 18:42:24', '2013-04-15 18:42:24', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1634', '0', 'post', '', '0');
