INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1649', '14', '2013-04-30 18:59:45', '2013-04-30 18:59:45', 'Barriere Construction Co entered a team of 11 riders for the annual American Diabetes Association Tour de Cure bike race on Saturday, April 20. The event kicked off in Mandeville and offered 10, 25, 50, 62, and 100 mile route distances for various levels of cyclists. Over 530 riders participated from across the state.\n\nThe Tour de Cure is an annual event held in 44 states across the nation.  Riders are encouraged to raise funds toward educational outreach, advocacy efforts, and research for diabetes.  Barriere’s team raised an impressive grand total of $12,000 to earn second place out of 60 teams. Furthermore, three of the top five individual fundraisers were from Barriere’s team; 2<sup>nd</sup> Place Craig Clark, 3<sup>rd</sup> Place Tiffany Clark, and 5<sup>th</sup> Place Pete Boiling.\n\nBarriere’s team captain, Craig Clark, said this was his first year to participate in the Tour. Clark has only been cycling since last June and completed the 100 mile century ride. Clark is motivated to ride to fight diabetes because he has several friends and family members who have been diagnosed with diabetes. Next year the team hopes to rally together to host a crawfish cook-off with the goal of raising $20,000 for the American Diabetes Association.\n\nCongratulations to all of the riders of the Barriere Tour de Cure team: Eric Amerland, Pete Boiling, Shannon Brayden, Charlie Cassreino, Craig Clark, Tiffany Clark, Gideon LeBerton, Brad Leckert, Michelle Lignieres, Doug Olsen, and Lisa Kirwin. Together this team rode over 713 miles and burned around 24,000 calories, equivalent to almost 15lbs of fat!\n\nFor more information about the American Diabetes Association or the annual Tour de Cure race, visit <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">tour.diabetes.org</span>', 'Barriere Team Conquers Tour de Cure', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1645-revision', '', '', '2013-04-30 18:59: