ient in soft drinks, cereal, yogurt, canned soups, and condiments.\r\n\r\nAlthough the US Food and Drug Administration has classified HFCS with the label \"generally recognized as safe,\" others argue that the ingredient is harmful to humans. Some researchers believe the inception of HFCS into the food supply has a direct correlation to the increase in obesity, type II diabetes, and metabolic syndrome. Furthermore, studies have found that HFCS can alter the appetite-regulating hormones Leptin and Ghrelin causing your brain and stomach to think you are still hungry even after a big meal.\r\n\r\nHigh Fructose Corn Syrup and table sugar both contain 4 calories per gram. Doctors and Dietitians agree that too much sugar in any form can be harmful. Since studies are still inconclusive about the direct effects of HFCS, limit processed foods that contain the sweetener and stick to fruits, vegetables, whole grains, and lean meats. Learn more about the controversy surrounding this ingredient from <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001tCiLIb5gR23e6kby86Qr16Uau6EMz92t4sZ2_hP3n6YflL6RWEjr3af-Xhn1Bea1fRFq_wAVT4Z8wQCDgVoRD2JewsXlXcS896LdnEhTgMVWhDQ0h_l8ASkPR7g-FQ80H40MEZnmX8pVw_zC3-m4U63UZMS6AA2lCLrneGr1BnTSqn8Bx_bRBw==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">WebMD</a> and the <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001tCiLIb5gR225MRqfUn9WH5M45oU8OILU6inpyYKC_qK76wXRwbDinExH9a1i-difHwrXNHvSbv6s7OvMDHJpNVc8F3pkc8U8s2qjE8ywjQE_claZP8ZuKELnkzAqPLkh1R7EnS7VsVz0agUNgAXj9h1qXZury2swhq_Aamsm5Aw=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Mayo Clinic</a>.', 'The Controversy Over Corn Syrup', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-controversy-over-corn-syrup', '', '', '2013-05-01 21:03:58', '2013-05-01 21:03:58', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1662', '0', 'post', '', '0');
