 and beverages. Lemons, like most citrus fruits, contain a significant amount of vitamin C. This nutrient helps fight colds, boost immunity, and even detoxify the liver. It\'s flavonid and antioxidant compounds have anti-cancer properties against breast, colon, and lung cancer.\r\n\r\nAside from culinary uses, lemons can also be used as a natural remedy for cleaning, beauty, and alternative medicine. The acid in lemons can dissolve stains and act as a deodorizer. For a daily boost of the benefits of lemon, add sliced lemon to your ice water. Learn more ways to incorporate fresh lemon into your diet with these <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001tCiLIb5gR23VxNOE_Ei2TbcWxgICRYK7wumgLi9czTug1p_f88HiYgMsHluMOm7jbusKzN3yFAz9Tma4iwd1zbfYC01YhGCxQkhmDa47w8kRsqBhFWTLSLJG1WIVIIoZeuufHsgieUUjyKEUXrSD0kH4uev1-ehlX-tLBFCsBujVrjkZMuy_C9-VeZGxCwK-txNX5K5dYzWmvR-Uw0TmabiH18WfFDtw\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">lemon recipes</a>.', 'From Lemons to Lemonade   ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'from-lemons-to-lemonade', '', '', '2013-05-01 21:07:06', '2013-05-01 21:07:06', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1667', '0', 'post', '', '0');
