kC3kKhWfI2Hhm6M0LP-j_CsMxn_MT73KIx-JyiBNvKyhr3tnItBBKlwW2f_b883FiJvCriUCEEMWGraki9ODS4j8ZeR3OKCHoU7M2QL6qw02u3Bk0EVNLgxrtFq8ZAqPMZOiVKEoEvTaEc-BZzwrfbuafFnOP0fguZ1tE1IMy1WhCIELnBo1W0y3Z5p9T\" target=\"&quot;_blank&quot;\"><img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs196/1103500019310/img/557.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.557\" width=\"112\" height=\"167\" align=\"left\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></a><!--[endif]-->It\'s easy to eat healthy during the summer when so many brightly colored fruits and vegetables are in season. Most people, especially children, are more likely to try new foods or eat healthy foods when it is presented to them in a visually appealing manner. Make a boom at your Independence Day gathering with a patriotic red, white, and blue dish.\r\n\r\nTry a patriotic parfait by layering blueberries and strawberries with Greek vanilla yogurt and top with granola. Serve up a flag-shaped fruit salad using banana slices and strawberries for the stripes and blueberries for the stars. Have kids help you make star-shaped watermelon pieces to stick on skewers.\r\n\r\nFind these and more patriotic recipes on Sterling\'s <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=0016Gr8PS3I5r10_BLF3iq7HuzzW_1wJPR_VIlFcPwZIlj4-CM74UZpYUAsE-I6dIi5Zn1Cr3QCzwhZ6XRLcFnCDxXmBpG2xoH9soFSx4DI0ycvOSn7au9XrwF11m6v5aBU5SU7tegF6Njv4ZlleyM5-3FH4mjfwMpF\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Festive Fourth Pinterest board.</a>', 'Patriotic Picnic Recipes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'patriotic-picnic-recipes', '', '', '2013-07-03 16:21:55', '2013-07-03 16:21:55', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1730', '0', 'post', '', '0');
