 isn\'t required, much of the controversy surrounding GMOs involves consumer interest groups and advocates at least requiring labeling so consumers can make the choice. America is the leading producer of GMOs, with 68% of all GMO products being grown in the US. Soybeans and corn are the two most widely grown crops, with most being modified for herbicide tolerance.\r\n\r\nIn third world countries, GMO foods have been altered to be more nutrient dense to minimize nutrient deficiencies, and can also be made to withstand drought and disease. However, there are human risks such as increases in allergies and chronic disease and many of the effects of GMOs are still unknown. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=0016Gr8PS3I5r3HHfpiH3u2LxGqJ2cJ5Zm070igWXYrV5_rJptVTL0cRiejhIRQ_lu-nYpb20tnP8jOQqQNzL8cVrl5wqV-DtO1KgVLScyoFm9iU85h0RFc0Dw3w_D684jmdtmdBWkw27Kid2IGOQNekcXaCOXSPvD5k8FFax9-_bmrohkAxTTmUfIkhqRp3Jhz\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to read WebMDs take</a> on GMOs or <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=0016Gr8PS3I5r20RXZdnw7X8xskbhPHsYOzK8EWxAD_oURl-Rggtqy9L4rTjbKMS66sGrr5CU2kZ6n0ejIrz1dkcKmhrzbFLu53VV6iulDI2q-1OOkjzTohuvkDE5RzPYJNHCvjSFnmidt9KWmJr80CqPfDsYEXLVXAY9RMgpSTXDq6G0BWynt2iov73U3OYSht\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">search non-GMO foods</a>. To select foods free of bio-engineering, choose organic, locally grown, or look for this label <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=0016Gr8PS3I5r0G5E3x0uTm35GQtzmMSy86HJWwDL9n_YA0DyEGM_3gp6enoNKTcz5E38EVu_fAhiCsv3SW21285M3HDZoSCG9ygfwaV8qYWBcSAY00feByzFQ3Jcw95XN8\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">verified by the non-GMO project</a>.', 'In the Know about GMOs ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'in-the-know-about-gmos', '', '', '2013-07-03 16:23:34', '2013-07-03 16:23:34', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1734', '0', 'post', '', '0');
