Os involves consumer interest groups and advocates at least requiring labeling so consumers can make the choice. America is the leading producer of GMOs, with 68% of all GMO products being grown in the US. Soybeans and corn are the two most widely grown crops, with most being modified for herbicide tolerance.\n\nIn third world countries, GMO foods have been altered to be more nutrient dense to minimize nutrient deficiencies, and can also be made to withstand drought and disease. However, there are human risks such as increases in allergies and chronic disease and many of the effects of GMOs are still unknown. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=0016Gr8PS3I5r3HHfpiH3u2LxGqJ2cJ5Zm070igWXYrV5_rJptVTL0cRiejhIRQ_lu-nYpb20tnP8jOQqQNzL8cVrl5wqV-DtO1KgVLScyoFm9iU85h0RFc0Dw3w_D684jmdtmdBWkw27Kid2IGOQNekcXaCOXSPvD5k8FFax9-_bmrohkAxTTmUfIkhqRp3Jhz\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to read WebMDs take</a> on GMOs or <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=0016Gr8PS3I5r20RXZdnw7X8xskbhPHsYOzK8EWxAD_oURl-Rggtqy9L4rTjbKMS66sGrr5CU2kZ6n0ejIrz1dkcKmhrzbFLu53VV6iulDI2q-1OOkjzTohuvkDE5RzPYJNHCvjSFnmidt9KWmJr80CqPfDsYEXLVXAY9RMgpSTXDq6G0BWynt2iov73U3OYSht\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">search non-GMO foods</a>. To select foods free of bio-engineering, choose organic, locally grown, or look for this label <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=0016Gr8PS3I5r0G5E3x0uTm35GQtzmMSy86HJWwDL9n_YA0DyEGM_3gp6enoNKTcz5E38EVu_fAhiCsv3SW21285M3HDZoSCG9ygfwaV8qYWBcSAY00feByzFQ3Jcw95XN8\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">verified by the non-GMO project</a>.', 'In the Know about GMOs ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1734-revision', '', '', '2013-07-03 16:23:14', '2013-07-03 16:23:14', '', '1734', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/1734-revision/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1736', '14', '2013-07-15 16:23:44', '2013-07-15 16:23:44', '<strong><em>Q: \"Are sports drinks good for you?\"</em></strong>\r\n<table style=\"width: 115px;\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"right\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"115\"> <a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Summer-James-160x160.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-1737\" title=\"Summer James 160x160\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Summer-James-160x160-130x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"130\" height=\"150\" /></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><em>Summer James, Health &amp; Wellness Advisor, Certified Health Coach</em></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\nA: While sports drinks such as Gatorade and Powerade serve an essential purpose for highly active athletes, many people don\'t realize that they are designed for just that: athletes. When working out at very high levels or when exercising in hot and humid conditions, your body becomes depleted of key nutrients such as potassium, magnesium and sodium, also known as electrolytes - all of which help prevent muscle fatigue and cramping.  When your body is low in these nutrients, you are more prone to weakness and heat related injuries. Sports drinks can help replenish electrolytes, fluids and carbohydrates giving you energy during and after your workout.\r\n\r\nBut what about those of us who aren\'t engaging in high intensity workouts? When exercising for 60 minutes or less at moderate levels, sports drinks can actually add an abundance of unnecessary calories and sugar. One 20 ounce bottle of Gatorade contains 34 grams of sugar - the equivalent of 9 teaspoons! These high levels of sugar can lead to unwanted weight gain, especially when consumed with moderate to low exercise. Many sports drinks also contain artificial coloring and high fructose corn syrup, both of which should be limited.\r\n\r\n<em>Bottom line</em>: Sports drinks can be essential for people engaging in prolonged periods of vigorous activity, but for everyone else the better solution is to stay hydrated with water before, during and after your workout!', 'Ask the Expert- Sports Drinks', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ask-the-expert-sports-drinks', '', '', '2013-07-03 16:25:10', '2013-07-03 16:25:10', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1736', '0', 'post', '', '0');
