istinguished by its star shape when cut in cross sections.\r\n\r\nOne small Carambola contains a mere 30 calories and is a good source of vitamin C and fiber. The exotic looking fruit is also rich in antioxidants quercetin and epicatechin which help protect the body from free radical damage and aging. Minerals and electrolytes like potassium, zinc, and iron are abundant in star fruit, making it a good choice for heart health and blood pressure.\r\n\r\nSelect fruits with a waxy, firm feel and bright orange or yellow hue. Carambola are great eaten raw, but can also be used as a garnish in salads, drinks, or to add a tart flavor to meat and seafood.', 'Star Grazing', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'star-grazing', '', '', '2013-07-03 16:26:42', '2013-07-03 16:26:42', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1741', '0', 'post', '', '0');
