 (good) cholesterol &lt;40 mg/dL for men or &lt;50 mg/dL for women</li>\n	<li>Blood pressure above 130/85 mm/Hg</li>\n	<li>Glucose 110 mg/dL or higher</li>\n</ul>\nHaving metabolic syndrome can increase your risk of diabetes and cardiovascular disease. Just 5-10% of weight loss can help restore the body\'s ability to recognize insulin and reduce the risk of metabolic syndrome. Furthermore, staying physically active and eating a healthy diet will reduce your risk of metabolic syndrome and its complications. <em><a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001zd3av7FYBkEKki7UuyEid3otfVrcwp35WH-1BhtvPti9gDj39FeBpqcX4mZ7H7kiIVaPqrJywZd_0SHKTeyr0FvMnD_JHVEh5L39xP1S336TJLWWHFsqi18X_WfpM6dlDMrho8icCUM_VgeG7k8bln3XJvM4Bjy36Vgpu-gPJe3uvuYWKxaJHj8vY7wHIr-K\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">More</a></em>', '', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1784-revision', '', '', '2013-08-08 20:54:36', '2013-08-08 20:54:36', '', '1784', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/1784-revision/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
