 fermented foods such as yogurt, sauerkraut, kefir, and in supplement form. Look for the Live and Active Cultures symbol to ensure the cultures are living organisms.\r\n\r\nPeople with intestinal sensitivities such as Irritable Bowel Syndrome (IBS), and Inflammatory Bowel Disease (IBD) including Chron\'s and Colitis can greatly benefit from regulating their gut with friendly flora. Furthermore, probiotics have been shown to be beneficial against gingivitis, eczema, and respiratory infections. <em><a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001JGKmMgyFFV7cnIWXbCCGX0q1pxClbkXHuOT2xkiX6WTU4ELsekf_Dkwr6HqSpGxtcAPzc-hrn9BgnCwgj7Yi61-O8kSvgG6qQcty1dgDT5zPuwqypY3dIJp4jKpjR7XqZH_i91e4JnopO8mSBW99Z8lmKJ26XIrPNjbyQ9-1ahhEExQehiUbzg==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">More</a></em>', 'The Power of Probiotics ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-power-of-probiotics', '', '', '2013-10-02 18:51:20', '2013-10-02 18:51:20', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1820', '0', 'post', '', '0');
