INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1826', '14', '2013-10-02 18:52:27', '2013-10-02 18:52:27', '<em>October is Breast Cancer Awareness Month </em>\r\n\r\nTo show support, people attend races and wear pink ribbons, but what if you have a co-worker, friend, or loved one who is battling the disease? What can you do on a more personal level to help?\r\n\r\n<strong>Do</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Admit if you might not know just what to say. Say you\'re willing to do anything needed, even if it\'s just listening.</li>\r\n	<li>Ask about family and activities - anything that brings the person joy.</li>\r\n	<li>Invite the person to lunch, a funny movie, or to go shopping.</li>\r\n	<li>Talk about the cancer, but follow the person\'s lead.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Don\'t</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Tell the person you know someone who just died or recently had a scare.</li>\r\n	<li>Say you know how she or he feels (unless you\'ve also gone through a similar experience).</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;\">Drop out of sight or stay away.</span></li>\r\n</ul>', 'Being There for Someone with Breast Cancer', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1822-revision-2', '', '', '2013-10-02 18:52:27', '2013-10-02 18:52:27', '', '1822', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/1822-revision-2/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1827', '14', '2013-10-24 18:53:57', '2013-10-24 18:53:57', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/pumpkin-seeds.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-1828\" title=\"pumpkin seeds\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/pumpkin-seeds-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>Healthy homemade snacks don\'t get much easier than this! Rinse the seeds from your carved pumpkin and lay them on a cookie sheet to dry. Toss the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>1 1/2 cups of raw whole pumpkin seeds</li>\r\n	<li>1 pinch of salt</li>\r\n	<li>2 teaspoons butter, melted</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nToast your seeds in a 300°F preheated oven for 30 minutes or until toasted brown. As an alternative to salt, try your own variation of flavors like cinnamon, herbs, or garlic.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001JGKmMgyFFV7myb8EmE7YNHMkDb6-gxdBENuPGMiyv85yhcNZ_lIHr7wuT4EPN1YindsmL2Nb6P81HM8zUNbRIiW3uUsusAMglaZVy5MzM-9ESwZogp8AoBPeyuYayxCeLAEP_ofSZJ3O7rpJuVr5dqAHYQ13Q2-r\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Visit AllRecipes Roasted Pumpkin Seed recipe for complete recipe and reviews.</a>', 'Recipe of the Month- Roasted Pumpkin Seeds  ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '1827', '', '', '2013-10-02 18:56:22', '2013-10-02 18:56:22', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1827', '0', 'post', '', '0');
