ough food prepared with contaminated hands.\r\n\r\n<strong>The single most important thing you can do to keep from getting sick is to wash your hands. -Centers for Disease Control</strong>\r\n\r\nAlcohol-based hand sanitizers work when a sink isn\'t available, but make sure they contain at least 60% alcohol and rub vigorously for 25 seconds. To respect others, sneeze into your elbow, and please stay home if you are sick to prevent the further spread of germs. <em><a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001luKPARjM_VY_gxvUX4AVSIBHD9HkG4kJuveNpWQLOFCE6bgvBI8oooW50pnke7-nc9wVUB_17H_XFHVJtxy9zliAziJa5D25cX3USN3Dl4ajMbTyck5g_iMjL3Lgn0Xm\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">More</a></em>', 'Spread Cheer, Not Germs ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'spread-cheer-not-germs', '', '', '2013-12-06 16:12:02', '2013-12-06 16:12:02', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1863', '0', 'post', '', '0');
