\n\r\n2. Limit carbonated drinks that can trap gas in your stomach.\r\n\r\n3. Avoid sugar-free foods containing sugar alcohols like mannitol and sorbitol.\r\n\r\n4. Include soluble fiber from oatmeal or fruit, but limit gassy vegetables like broccoli.\r\n\r\n5. Limit salt. Excess sodium results in fluid retention and water weight.\r\n\r\nResearch suggest home remedies such as peppermint tea, ginger, and probiotics can help relieve stomach discomfort. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001luKPARjM_VbSqMbMjBRL7cwosW4fgOetRQONXBj9yuCiFQqZwv8uDZMGd7BVz_517wjtShhy5CzbGmpIVbiBD25bdGiMsZOIAA-v7ts3mklO0ykv212PygbQvinuebX3ke5MNw6PYa09FYKdaOXUXX6WdJI5I5pAEqpr6m8QKMRhsx5jJT3RQw==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><em>More</em></a>\r\n\r\n<!--[endif]-->', '5 Tips to Relieve a Bloated Stomach', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1869-revision-2', '', '', '2013-12-06 16:14:50', '2013-12-06 16:14:50', '', '1869', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/1869-revision-2/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1872', '14', '2013-12-02 16:15:05', '2013-12-02 16:15:05', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/vegetable-lovers-soup.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-1873\" title=\"vegetable lovers soup\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/vegetable-lovers-soup-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>Warm up with this classic soup with a twist. Broth-based soups are lower in calories and fat than a cream-based option. Experiment with your own combinations of vegetables, pasta, or lentils.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Vegetables include zucchini, shallots, tomatoes, and spinach</li>\r\n	<li>Bite-sized chunks of chicken add protein</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFollow this <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001luKPARjM_Va_zZPen7ZCom4eErEVjkDue8wtRnBdH2zmP-aJ6YXyJRyxZPYbLVMdC85qIvzyKrjuuShROoIq7LaIbs-PGI0LVDP6u1lpvqHh6DH_Kuz2YKaav7QoFsNNbLDpMCUGbd9JO-Gp1_1NWt7ETejab-gQNhmJM-IergpecSlNeOd64A==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Vegetable Lover\'s Chicken Soup recipe from EatingWell</a> for the complete list of ingredients and instructions. Total prep time is 40 minutes. Recipe makes four cups, and can be made up to 3 days ahead or frozen for up to 3 months.', 'Recipe of the Month- Vegetable Lover\'s Chicken Soup ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'recipe-of-the-month-vegetable-lovers-chicken-soup', '', '', '2013-12-06 16:17:24', '2013-12-06 16:17:24', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1872', '0', 'post', '', '0');
