s of breath are also common symptoms. If you think you or someone around you is experiencing a heart attack, follow these steps:\r\n<ol start=\"1\">\r\n	<li>Contact 9-1-1</li>\r\n	<li>Push hard and fast in the center of the chest to the beat of \'Stayin\' Alive\'</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nYou don\'t have to be certified in CPR/AED to save a life. Simply providing chest compressions to someone in cardiac arrest is a safe and effective way for a bystander to double or triple a person\'s chances of survival. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001kCurY-oSC7Z7Syub2HDvhW5MXYQJobYCsSyBVP6Cy36KwvKWC7yVWPWjnkHhwKaLUN5XIdtuQ5rC0UlWFLoQ42XSVokiUbrDKPviGkSML4jaWpHGGRXxJ1JRgJO1zcygmHiYz11NMY7kbREJzO1_C2BLFEZZaj76_Js5qIyc7NkM_3J8JbRIzLElEAFW5uC_XAK1-AqXLYU5QSM1DR15iXBlTQadFeUo\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><em>More</em></a>', 'Save a Life with Hands-Only CPR', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'save-a-life-with-hands-only-cpr', '', '', '2014-02-06 22:20:58', '2014-02-06 22:20:58', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1926', '0', 'post', '', '0');
