INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1952', '14', '2014-03-02 19:40:48', '2014-03-02 19:40:48', '<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\r\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\r\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\r\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\r\n <v:formulas>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\r\n </v:formulas>\r\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\r\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\r\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1027\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\r\n margin-left:0;margin-top:502.5pt;width:83.25pt;height:124.5pt;z-index:251658240;\r\n mso-wrap-distance-left:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:3.75pt;\r\n mso-wrap-distance-right:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:3.75pt;\r\n mso-position-horizontal:left;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\r\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\r\n <v:imagedata src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs196/1103500019310/img/873.jpg\"/>\r\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\r\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs196/1103500019310/img/873.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.873\" width=\"111\" height=\"166\" align=\"left\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /><!--[endif]-->Trying to limit sugar in your diet? Even the savviest label reader can be tricked by added sugars under the disguise of another name. There are over 50 different names for sugar including maltodextrin, cane crystals, malt syrup, high-fructose corn syrup, saccharose, sorghum, treacle, mannitol and xylose just to name a few. Roughly 80% of packaged and processed foods contain added sugars.\r\n\r\nSugar increases the risk for <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001Hixvu_vlsElc2evj7ZbYkqq1KPxKcz9FFJDo4RvDOUAzjcBk-gLMcWY-zby1-7i4-bRtocnfexFfgWnMYWJlKJwzl9DhVoTrFdh7PlY0I-8CuA5TZhiSCV5QJxnPDThVrgHdhhSr67p6PZKeuKTJYAsx-ibQImI3ANfeSg4ajMJemtorBF6_cA==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">type II diabetes</a>, certain cancers, weight gain, and cardiovascular disease. The current American Heart Association guidelines limits sugar to 6 teaspoons for women and 9 teaspoons for men. Compare that to the average consumption of 22 teaspoons for most Americans and the consumption of sugar becomes a widespread issue. To limit sugars, stick to a plant based diet and limit packaged foods. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001Hixvu_vlsEmGsgy1VEBCnP4s4lqEpjopI_q5n6R9E1dfl-PbvZU8-Vh-IFz0dT45exdee_kiacEWDDoS7QVBwdg23TP_WJNkNl5xyGe91_IDuYTePqjsIgA2MwhE-F0xYD9DH-PsKZBLNUyPsfPXkNXP4f6gwOW2HYFFZ7vO8gTBdWgQrM-sRltVzWdrjmUi2k9GHJOHpGzptI1JO_nhmRK3uKhCsmsL\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><em>More</em></a>', 'The Not-So-Sweet Side of Sugar', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-not-so-sweet-side-of-sugar', '', '', '2014-04-09 19:41:24', '2014-04-09 19:41:24', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1952', '0', 'post', '', '0');
