de-stem one bunch of kale, tearing into bite-sized pieces.</li>\r\n	<li>Toss kale leaves in a bowl or zip tight bag with 1-2 Tablespoons of olive oil, dash of garlic powder and salt until thoroughly coated.</li>\r\n	<li>Spread coated kale onto cookie sheet and bake until crisp but not brown, about 15-20 minutes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nExperiment with different flavors of kale chips by trying garlic infused olive oil, onion or cayenne powder, or seasonings of your choice.', 'Recipe of the Month- Kale Chips ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'recipe-of-the-month-kale-chips', '', '', '2014-04-09 19:44:00', '2014-04-09 19:44:00', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1959', '0', 'post', '', '0');
