processed foods can be the medicine required to prevent and treat illnesses.\n\n<strong style=\"font-size: 13px;\">Medicine is not healthcare. Food is healthcare. Medicine is sickcare.   </strong><span style=\"font-size: 13px;\">-Wendell Barry, Author</span>\n\nModern-day diets are causing us to be over-fed but under-nourished. Replacing high-sugar, high-fat foods with antioxidant rich fruits, vegetables, and whole grains can offer the anti-inflammatory compounds and nutrients for optimal health. Replace your packaged foods with a variety of disease fighting whole foods. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001_hssVjiVfu3cgzF7pOZtxB2OpzMfzqqmBnFGbSg6Hij07Qxzy2A-KkbReuDQ3rIxbHLKEyHX3o9Oumy71In6DMEUAhuyMjzbXZbI64TMWvgPA02-VpzyeiQjwE331lZlVFHlH0hSOqiFI0TCp5PwRa3CNF6reVeYa3YFpVJx4B0kuklwKtgpbw==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><em>More</em></a>', 'Let Food Be Your Medicine', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1964-revision', '', '', '2014-04-09 19:45:39', '2014-04-09 19:45:39', '', '1964', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/1964-revision/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1966', '14', '2014-04-15 19:45:53', '2014-04-15 19:45:53', '<img src=\"https://origin.ih.constantcontact.com/fs196/1103500019310/img/898.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.898\" width=\"145\" height=\"183\" align=\"right\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /><!--[endif]-->A naturally clean home is not just better for your health and the environment, it can be better on your pocketbook as well. Using simple non-toxic cleaning products can leave your house clean and chemical-free.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Vinegar</strong>- Removes soap scum on bathroom tile and shower heads and dissolves lime from hard water and coffeemakers. Shines mirrors and glass.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Borax</strong>- Kills mold and fungus. Can be added to laundry and dishwashing detergent.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Baking Soda</strong>- Absorbs orders in furniture, carpet, refrigerators and garbage cans.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Hydrogen peroxide</strong>-Works on solid surfaces like tubs and showers in place of bleach.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Lemon</strong>- Cleans cutting boards, breaks down grime, and leaves citrus scent.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nYou may choose to add essential oils like mint, lemon, and citronella to your cleaning products. Dried herbs such as rosemary, lavender, and sage can add a pleasant scent to your chemical-free cleaners as well. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001_hssVjiVfu3cgzF7pOZtxB2OpzMfzqqmBnFGbSg6Hij07Qxzy2A-KkbReuDQ3rIxbHLKEyHX3o9Oumy71In6DMEUAhuyMjzb-jjVc6qGtEe_PJOy4_9W3Xo2WfNl50PAEqcv-vfWnvCNW-j7n_dtsg==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><em>More</em></a>', 'Spring Cleaning the Natural Way', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'spring-cleaning-the-natural-way', '', '', '2014-04-09 19:46:41', '2014-04-09 19:46:41', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1966', '0', 'post', '', '0');
