 rate elevated and creates an oxygen shortage causing your body to require more oxygen during recovery, leading to a greater fat and calorie burn.\r\n\r\nSome HIIT sessions can leave your metabolism elevated for 24-48 hours after a workout so you burn calories long after you\'ve left the gym. Even home workout routines can be quick and require little equipment. Use your own body weight to do interval repetitions of push-ups, plyometrics, sit-ups, jump squats, and jump-roping. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001_hssVjiVfu3cgzF7pOZtxB2OpzMfzqqmBnFGbSg6Hij07Qxzy2A-KkbReuDQ3rIxbHLKEyHX3o829AwII52j4Yyo5oBbtrUWjRuJcueYKrO8x4F9goqCHI12BYf2r-oGAEoak3E1AH5p5rHnLIp6iE2c-EEnMi9oO_IDLEfOoVw=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><em>More</em></a>', 'Get Fit with HIIT', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'get-fit-with-hiit', '', '', '2014-04-09 19:47:11', '2014-04-09 19:47:11', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1969', '0', 'post', '', '0');
