ur body to require more oxygen during recovery, leading to a greater fat and calorie burn.\n\nSome HIIT sessions can leave your metabolism elevated for 24-48 hours after a workout so you burn calories long after you\'ve left the gym. Even home workout routines can be quick and require little equipment. Use your own body weight to do interval repetitions of push-ups, plyometrics, sit-ups, jump squats, and jump-roping. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001_hssVjiVfu3cgzF7pOZtxB2OpzMfzqqmBnFGbSg6Hij07Qxzy2A-KkbReuDQ3rIxbHLKEyHX3o829AwII52j4Yyo5oBbtrUWjRuJcueYKrO8x4F9goqCHI12BYf2r-oGAEoak3E1AH5p5rHnLIp6iE2c-EEnMi9oO_IDLEfOoVw=\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><em>More</em></a>', 'Get Fit with HIIT', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1969-revision', '', '', '2014-04-09 19:47:06', '2014-04-09 19:47:06', '', '1969', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/1969-revision/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1971', '14', '2014-04-27 19:47:20', '2014-04-27 19:47:20', 'April is the peak season for asparagus and this easy recipe will leave you wanting more! Asparagus is heralded for its anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties against chronic conditions like type 2 diabetes, heart disease, and digestive disorders.\r\n<table style=\"width: 250px;\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"right\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"250\"> <a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/1104p36-sesame-ginger-glazed-asparagus-l.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright  wp-image-1972\" title=\"1104p36-sesame-ginger-glazed-asparagus-l\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/1104p36-sesame-ginger-glazed-asparagus-l-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" /></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><em><a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001_hssVjiVfu3cgzF7pOZtxB2OpzMfzqqmBnFGbSg6Hij07Qxzy2A-KkbReuDQ3rIxbHLKEyHX3o-l7ukdf7O6caa0oC32P-ecMg6jRe9o_5zgmXOHwXfx5l4UWHvdVAVg7eT4f54s0dAEEimfAGLi9_6DavBxEGDCbFC6B8APNf_UPU2qK3Q08Q==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Sesame-Ginger Glazed Asparagus from CookingLight</a></em></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Clean and trim 1 pound of fresh asparagus.</li>\r\n	<li>Cook asparagus in boiling water until crisp-tender. Drain.</li>\r\n	<li>Microwave soy sauce, honey, lime juice, ginger, and garlic on high for 2 minutes. Drizzle over asparagus.</li>\r\n	<li>Sprinkle with toasted sesame seeds and serve with lime wedges.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001_hssVjiVfu3cgzF7pOZtxB2OpzMfzqqmBnFGbSg6Hij07Qxzy2A-KkbReuDQ3rIxbHLKEyHX3o-l7ukdf7O6caa0oC32P-ecMg6jRe9o_5zgmXOHwXfx5l4UWHvdVAVg7eT4f54s0dAEEimfAGLi9_6DavBxEGDCbFC6B8APNf_UPU2qK3Q08Q==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">View the complete ingredient list from CookingLight</a>. Total prep time is 20 minutes. Each serving contains approximately 40 calories and is high in vitamin K, folate, fiber, and B vitamins.', 'Recipe of the Month- Sesame-Ginger Glazed Asparagus ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'recipe-of-the-month-sesame-ginger-glazed-asparagus', '', '', '2014-04-09 19:48:29', '2014-04-09 19:48:29', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1971', '0', 'post', '', '0');
