n close to home. Since it doesn\'t need to travel as far, locally grown produce is usually fresher and has been handled less.</span>\r\n\r\nLocally grown options not only create sustainable food systems that protect the environment by reducing freight and travel, but they also keep food dollars in your local economy.\r\n\r\nWhile there are no regulations as to what can be labeled locally grown, many producers use the 100 mile rule. Locally grown food can extend past fruits and vegetables to include meat and dairy products as well. Produce managers will be able to tell you where the fruits and vegetables come from, and often labels on some produce indicate where it was grown. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001Ywe8N9ZzTwJwG0to7lzynpydEQt00js0Oa88RXahARubKFr932nyQwtS9xLmjCE0otBBFN0nBEvtztKqlIHnldJBqdVJMWFZjN4VLxABnpZlaf4gGStfUQpU9Wg_3RTpAiCOFtLk8_p2qhQYL7D6GKzTMgClpcHyAAEu4kRJw94EN0VmjneJ6A==&amp;c=AeyPheMxmNwwU9wiONArMgcpmTzz69pVIwDHHMKlhLO3eOK0LxsRLw==&amp;ch=9VhzzZMODbeFIBBJg_2DGfFC6iGXIuQ--FP8cpzEO67TozoWNwN7BA==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><em>More</em></a>', 'Eating Close to Home ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'eating-close-to-home', '', '', '2014-05-08 18:49:24', '2014-05-08 18:49:24', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=1992', '0', 'post', '', '0');
