etermine your target heart rate:\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> <strong style=\"font-size: 13px;\">Maximum Heart Rate = 220-Age </strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"center\"><strong>Moderate Intensity: 50-70% of your maximum heart rate</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"center\"><strong>Vigorous Intensity: 70-85% of your maximum heart rate</strong></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTo tell if you are hitting the target heart rate zone during exercise, take your pulse on your carotid artery (neck) or radial artery (wrist) for 30 seconds and multiply it by 2. This number indicates beats per minute, or BPM. If you can carry on a conversation during exercise, try increasing the intensity to a greater percentage of your maximum heart rate. Talk to your doctor if you are on certain medications including beta blockers which can lower your maximum and target heart rate. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001Ywe8N9ZzTwJwG0to7lzynpydEQt00js0Oa88RXahARubKFr932nyQwtS9xLmjCE0oQUexlqD_xynWxpCMWtpLdejgCif8gHw4ctK67zs6ks6djubGAiUkxgdkQfT_PtXxfD905EhLsqJdPrH0wVIPkzxNBbjQOtkKznvJ82ThXeo0PUcDQbHi8svxhQJM2NFaUYV7mRuaI0-pK4jMwBghNoa9Iin64Drhzx-o17wAflfLbvu5zDam8G99mt_xmz2prTxwtEp272zOjc-PgHQt1xeCOF7-Uif&amp;c=AeyPheMxmNwwU9wiONArMgcpmTzz69pVIwDHHMKlhLO3eOK0LxsRLw==&amp;ch=9VhzzZMODbeFIBBJg_2DGfFC6iGXIuQ--FP8cpzEO67TozoWNwN7BA==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><em>More</em></a>', 'What\'s My Target Heart Rate?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2001-revision-2', '', '', '2014-05-08 18:57:43', '2014-05-08 18:57:43', '', '2001', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/2001-revision-2/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
