 of studies that BPA is safe at very low levels, the National Toxicology Program raised concern in 2008 about about possible health effects of BPA on the brain, behavior, prostate gland in fetuses, infants, and children exposed to the chemical.\r\n\r\nThe FDA is continuing to review and support ongoing studies about the effects of this chemical, and is working with food manufacturers to encourage the demand of BPA-free products. If you are concerned about BPA, look for BPA-free products, avoid canned foods since most contain BPA lining, and avoid heating plastics in the microwave or dishwasher as this may cause the plastic to breakdown and leach into the food. Using glass, ceramic, aluminum, or stainless steel can avoid exposure to BPA. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=0018BxFD73nH2sMuT5Sqi0JD5GHovIi3AMZ1mLmOyraUghOOTc-J7Ryavp3aL8MVDQ3l6azmRdm7O7r6xmelgEMX2mthJQbeZ8GWtjcKP0dccMHiFiRmHKMjyvLH3-1PD13E45e4B-IbB_uP0oJ5ybIwAvGeZtauXRbQ6TySPV6KldnL20eMXG6zI0RNQp0b9frT9RbVricjrRAMaphveIzJ47Qp0y2rMHSEbZsUnnlFq9YVzvllGl7QxEBWCV39a51PsxiZFrMIztMv4fxIk9MiBa6J1-e0AgU&amp;c=3OCuyNg9dPUZ5c5tba2NwtrfuYQgGKPb2f8FIu9Ycy3440zzpdI_JA==&amp;ch=sNAvtMW6cR7Jiifwc9B7mTsIyqTdshBrGsu6f3oWjDQI8bVVgOCUOw==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><em>More</em></a>', 'Should I Worry about BPA?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'should-i-worry-about-bpa', '', '', '2014-06-11 19:07:21', '2014-06-11 19:07:21', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2033', '0', 'post', '', '0');
