or Healthcare Providers.  With nearly four years of experience in corporate wellness, she is passionate about promoting and motivating health and well-being in others.\r\n<h4><strong>Brittany Inlow</strong></h4>\r\nis a graduate of Louisiana State University where she earned a Bachelor’s of Science in Nutritional Sciences with a concentration in Dietetics and a Master’s of Science in Exercise Physiology. She has five years of clinical research through Pennington Biomedical Research Center. Brittany is a certified Healthy Behaviors Coach from the Cooper Institute and CPR and AED-certified from the American Heart Association for Basic Life Support for Healthcare Providers. She is a professional member of the American College of Sports Medicine and Wellness Council of America. Brittany has a passion for promoting and motivating positive behavior changes in order to achieve health and well-being.\r\n<h4><strong>Brittany Smith </strong></h4>\r\nis a graduate of Louisiana Tech University where she received her Bachelor’s in Nutrition and Dietetics and completed a Dietetic Internship through Louisiana Tech University in Shreveport, La. She is ServSafe Certified in food safety and sanitation and is CPR and First Aid Certified. Brittany is a member of the Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics and the Louisiana Dietetics Association. Brittany is currently pursuing her Master’s Degree in Nutrition and Dietetics through Louisiana Tech University and is passionate for health promotion and nutrition education.\r\n<h4><strong>Janice Beard</strong></h4>\r\nis a graduate of the Nicholls State University nursing program. With nearly 40 years of nursing experience, Janice has been exposed to many areas of healthcare including positions as a Staff Nurse, Head Nurse, Director of Education, and a Director or Nursing. She brings an exceptional depth of knowledge and experience to Sterling’s team of Health Coaches. Janice enjoys  providing education through individual health coaching consultations on the preventative side of wellness.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[/one_third]', 'Health Coach Profiles', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '97-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-23 20:02:56', '2014-07-23 20:02:56', '', '97', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/97-revision-37/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2059', '14', '2014-03-19 20:55:21', '2014-03-19 20:55:21', 'Sterling Wellness Solutions is looking for the best and brightest individuals to join a dynamic and talented team. Our multi-dimensional approach to wellness requires creative thinking, industry knowledge, and a unified mission of introducing wellness in an exciting new light. Please use the form below to contact us if you are interested in employment with our team.\r\n<h4><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Current positions available</strong></span>:</h4>\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>RN/Nurse Practitioner</strong></span>- Seeking an ambitious Primary Care Nurse to serve the greater New Orleans area. Must be a degreed and licensed professional with 3-5 years of experience as a Registered Nurse or Nurse Practitioner. Early mornings and significant local travel required. Requires motivational health coaching, clinical biometric knowledge, and computer proficiency. Responsible for engaging and positively impacting individuals and groups through preventive wellness programs including diabetes, weight management, and smoking cessation. Requires scheduling and facilitating wellness screenings, providing intensive onsite and telephonic health coaching, and overseeing wellness incentive program. Serious and qualified inquires only. Submit cover letter, resume and references.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Health Coach-</strong></span> Seeking an enthusiastic and motivated LPN for a Health Coaching position in Crowley, LA. Must have  2-3 years of experience in health promotions, nursing, dietetics, or an allied health field. Early mornings and significant state-wide travel required. Responsible for reviewing abnormal lab results and addressing risk factors, developing and promoting wellness programs, motivating healthy lifestyle change, and providing intensive onsite and telephonic health coaching.  Requires excellent presentation skills, interpersonal communication, and computer proficiency.  Serious and qualified inquires only. Submit cover letter, resume, and references.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Fitness Expert</strong></span>- Must be proficient at conducting step test and sit-and-reach, and knowledgeable with other general health and fitness information. Ability to take manual blood pressure is preferred. Early mornings and local travel throughout Lafourche and Terrebonne Parish required. Please submit resume and references below.\r\n\r\n[gravityform id=\"1\" name=\"Careers\" title=\"false\" description=\"false\" ajax=\"true\"]', 'Careers', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-19 20:55:21', '2014-03-19 20:55:21', '', '8', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/8-revision-27/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
