llspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"227\"><strong>Abdominal obesity</strong></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"312\">&gt;40\" for men or &gt;35\" for women</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"227\"><strong>Triglycerides</strong></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"312\">at least 150 mg/dL</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"227\"><strong>Low HDL (good) cholesterol</strong></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"312\">&lt;40 mg/dL for men or &lt;50 mg/dL for women</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"227\"><strong>Blood pressure</strong></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"312\">above 130/85 mm/Hg</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"227\"><strong>Glucose</strong></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"312\">100 mg/dL or higher</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<em>\r\n</em> Having metabolic syndrome can increase your risk of diabetes and cardiovascular disease. Just 5-10% weight loss can help restore the body\'s ability to recognize insulin and reduce the risk of metabolic syndrome. Staying physically active and eating a healthy diet will reduce your risk of metabolic syndrome and its complications<em>. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001faST2-npQdIWHoHhVUqn8nrYcyj1Xp12KzkC12qNMSeCKKwZUA4xCD2VbjRiXqB503FPpu6Ng3lijrjMXhzWuP3fdGLs3yglDVhDter1PNaEVc8cyQgs9S6GWJliLQJypSmvuCLqCnMfFVE7tlSOOnTreGBh6MNGWZOzZFfVaNcUez14cpFCddtHfh3ARS0b0dMKcyUvxaX5cUzJP481hP29FjQJbg6itozEx4U8wGs4AQo4DPKc0w==&amp;c=cJsFEUnx96J6U561bIYsXKWgyNu_MhAgoWhjFzOUOQRqGyU586RI0A==&amp;ch=y7rWogukMK-b8iCn2XuS2HPo1B_dk5QVCFXqApnPX259OEZSxytYIw==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><em>More</em></a> </em>', 'Are You At Risk for Metabolic Syndrome?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'are-you-at-risk-for-metabolic-syndrome', '', '', '2014-08-08 16:40:28', '2014-08-08 16:40:28', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2068', '0', 'post', '', '0');
