=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001faST2-npQdIWHoHhVUqn8nrYcyj1Xp12KzkC12qNMSeCKKwZUA4xCBWiIskFtarpRDDsMaYkUVfL_Ns6s3iAGdS0uhefWkjo-7ORDrnptAqvz2FEiQp3XN2niA8YEkk7B8A74ll_Wxm6sSZUlGlKMtoAtuuTJovpLbH_vyj4_qUADpjZbt4-AqnWlmfBuPc6TtiUUjnrmEUmEit7yEkQGLHIazeGzB0Q&amp;c=cJsFEUnx96J6U561bIYsXKWgyNu_MhAgoWhjFzOUOQRqGyU586RI0A==&amp;ch=y7rWogukMK-b8iCn2XuS2HPo1B_dk5QVCFXqApnPX259OEZSxytYIw==\" target=\"&quot;_blank&quot;\"><img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs196/1103500019310/img/993.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.993\" width=\"244\" height=\"146\" align=\"right\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></a><!--[endif]-->After school, after work, or just an afternoon pick-me-up, these cold bananas will offer a fun way to get good nutrition!\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cut 2-3 bananas in half crosswise and insert wooden craft sticks into the large end of each banana.</li>\r\n	<li>In a small bowl, mix together plain Greek yogurt, vanilla, and stevia (optional).</li>\r\n	<li>Dip banana halves into yogurt mixture.</li>\r\n	<li>Roll coated bananas in low-fat granola until covered.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFreeze banana pops uncovered until solid, about 4 hours or overnight. Experiment with your own combinations of peanut butter, almond butter, or cinnamon in the yogurt mixture.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001faST2-npQdIWHoHhVUqn8nrYcyj1Xp12KzkC12qNMSeCKKwZUA4xCBWiIskFtarpRDDsMaYkUVfL_Ns6s3iAGdS0uhefWkjo-7ORDrnptAqvz2FEiQp3XN2niA8YEkk7B8A74ll_Wxm6sSZUlGlKMtoAtuuTJovpLbH_vyj4_qUADpjZbt4-AqnWlmfBuPc6TtiUUjnrmEUmEit7yEkQGLHIazeGzB0Q&amp;c=cJsFEUnx96J6U561bIYsXKWgyNu_MhAgoWhjFzOUOQRqGyU586RI0A==&amp;ch=y7rWogukMK-b8iCn2XuS2HPo1B_dk5QVCFXqApnPX259OEZSxytYIw==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><em>Click here to get the complete list of ingredients and directions from Relish.com.</em></a>', 'Frozen Yogurt-Dipped Banana Pops', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'frozen-yogurt-dipped-banana-pops', '', '', '2014-08-08 16:41:30', '2014-08-08 16:41:30', '', '0', 'http://www.sterlin