and shortness of breath may also indicate anemia.\r\n\r\nIron-deficiency anemia can be caused from blood loss due to injury, blood donation, or surgery. The best food sources for iron include red meat, poultry, and fish. Other foods high in iron include leafy green vegetables like spinach and kale, beans and lentils, and iron-fortified cereals. Eating foods high in vitamin C along with iron-rich foods can help your body absorb iron.\r\n\r\nA simple blood test can determine if you are anemic. Talk to your doctor about your symptoms and possible iron supplementation. Sterling Wellness offers discounted lab testing for anemia at a lab in your area. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001faST2-npQdIWHoHhVUqn8nrYcyj1Xp12KzkC12qNMSeCKKwZUA4xCBWiIskFtarpnvgS11RF2x9qCpKUdyrCM3PrntlnaNB1cYpyuXkobf47qmQ-aaqCXFdpAsxk-vXn59ppROz0y4EZ58aPm4raBbmtpqLAQ9bXZ-ZGNidaX4MZRnYeEZfW0UQWjSlccTPV6-flvc7eVanQnHPc9E89SA==&amp;c=cJsFEUnx96J6U561bIYsXKWgyNu_MhAgoWhjFzOUOQRqGyU586RI0A==&amp;ch=y7rWogukMK-b8iCn2XuS2HPo1B_dk5QVCFXqApnPX259OEZSxytYIw==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">Click here</a> or call our office at 1-800-838-0337 for more information. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001faST2-npQdIWHoHhVUqn8nrYcyj1Xp12KzkC12qNMSeCKKwZUA4xCBWiIskFtarpkbz0JmAXM61PzkKc_2vYPX5hh6iJnBmkha8BZSXbqrZm2gBOwghaAbh086c1QQP3HX8Lk8GMFDr5jmyCuyXqya2_tGOuMMm1mnyBtxcAEKTOs-3OO45ZjBsJkTrgURWy_OMBYtC2NizzRIa-JpcKvMgq3gqdSOfS&amp;c=cJsFEUnx96J6U561bIYsXKWgyNu_MhAgoWhjFzOUOQRqGyU586RI0A==&amp;ch=y7rWogukMK-b8iCn2XuS2HPo1B_dk5QVCFXqApnPX259OEZSxytYIw==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><em>More</em></a>', '', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2064-revision-2', '', '', '2014-08-08 16:38:12', '2014-08-08 16:38:12', '', '2064', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/2064-revision-2/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
