INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2076', '14', '2014-09-04 20:32:08', '2014-09-04 20:32:08', '<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\r\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\r\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\r\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\r\n <v:formulas>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\r\n </v:formulas>\r\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\r\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\r\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1026\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\r\n margin-left:311.05pt;margin-top:204pt;width:138.75pt;height:92.25pt;z-index:251658240;\r\n mso-wrap-distance-left:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:3.75pt;\r\n mso-wrap-distance-right:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:3.75pt;\r\n mso-position-horizontal:right;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\r\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\r\n <v:imagedata src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs196/1103500019310/img/777.jpg\"/>\r\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\r\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs196/1103500019310/img/777.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.777\" width=\"185\" height=\"123\" align=\"right\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /><!--[endif]-->Triglycerides are a type of fat found in your blood and are an important measure of heart health. When you eat, any unused calories are converted immediately to triglycerides and stored in your fat cells. Between meals, hormones release triglycerides for energy.\r\n\r\nA triglyceride level less than 150mg/dL is normal. Levels above that can increase the risk of heart disease, stroke, and metabolic syndrome. A healthy lifestyle is the most effective way to lower triglycerides:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Lose weight-</strong> Even a loss of 5-10 pounds can decrease triglycerides</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Avoid sugar-</strong> Simple refined carbohydrates increase triglycerides</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Limit alcohol-</strong> Even small amounts of alcohol can raise triglycerides</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Cut calories-</strong> Extra calories are stored as triglycerides in fat cells</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Exercise Regularly-</strong> Moderate-intensity activity lowers triglycerides</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAlthough both cholesterol and triglycerides circulate in the blood, cholesterol is used to build cells and hormones, where triglycerides are stored calories used for energy. <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/cholesterol-management/lowering-triglyceride-levels\" rel=\"nofollow\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\">More</a>', 'Triglycerides, Explained', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'triglycerides-explained', '', '', '2014-09-04 20:32:08', '2014-09-04 20:32:08', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2076', '0', 'post', '', '0');
