one fruits can be eaten fresh, dried, or cooked in a variety of ways. Their sweet juicy similarities allow most stone fruits to be used interchangeably in recipes. Peaches, nectarines, and apricots contain anthocyanin and quercetin. These flavonoids are known for preventing cardiovascular diseases and cancer. Stone fruits are low in calories high in vitamins A and C. One medium-sized peach or nectarine contains about 60 calories. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001mqpT30LjS0PvZXYpyrESPw8ALO1tSwDbFYVu4wxvn-eUH0A4E5kjZmrClFo9-anN9Zbh32wANv6xE0MDXUEL_AhN3MnAqzE6BVMkDJtwKS2QLOddqb8LIfDk89vXY3otbc5J4Lvc1P_-WUquZqJKDJeAVhnaRrugn7TIJtrfa52sVd6w3A1VbChrf-9M26lcnyN-77nQAQkAft0FqbFydCYh1_ZoOZaD&amp;c=Y6so3ePEoYCLKwKzG_9oihVFb0oHY07yf_5jxnN7Z9yVFywcCBnFmA==&amp;ch=FQMVJ-rUubFxc7mO267pJ9SlnOnW2h_dB_lJkMYLg2H-lrBSsD-fdQ==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><em>More</em></a>', 'The Sweetness of Stone Fruit', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-sweetness-of-stone-fruit', '', '', '2014-09-04 20:33:35', '2014-09-04 20:33:35', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2080', '0', 'post', '', '0');
