 grocers sell.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Nitrates </strong>are used as preservatives in processed and cured meats and are linked to leukemia, stomach, thyroid, and esophageal cancer.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>High Fructose Corn Syrup </strong>is a cheaper replacement to sugar which many researches believe is directly linked to the increase of obesity and diabetes.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Carrageenan</strong> is derived from seaweed and used to thicken many dairy products but prompts concerns about digestive inflammation and ulcers.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Monosodium Glutamate</strong> is a flavor enhancer in salty foods. The FDA has received reports of reactions from MSG including headache, nausea, heart palpitations, and chest pain.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Artificial coloring</strong> like Yellow 5, Red 40, and Blue 2 are made from petroleum and and pose risks, especially in children, including hyperactivity, allergic reactions, and cancer.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nShop the perimeter of the grocery store for the majority of your foods and look for ingredients with short lists. Avoid ingredients that you can\'t pronounce. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001flEtcTDLdOZcCASGWG2VlPx97V89fa9a8Y9fj5vfE-95eQU-99N_cxRgdmthzEcKv8MMJHzSzqEs0XuEiFo2TUr_GJYsyDWHVOUg67FZj9blXdLRgRVdobyonc77gWKNT_cdgUufN6545fo8UioOkYl5rOINRrnZ9_8ZQ7QzCC72hJL14UOR5atvkla7iq8COHk4WMXOpkgad1AYflKfq_simblLQ9RLhGOwKjYppvk=&amp;c=BQa7v_ihdbetQOubnidRuCxNBdY5cOYTZ-bKQPFWeEm78-8UCQbUZg==&amp;ch=ApL6b9g-7RJ41hLsF2jiTI6_uerR0NpJcT16c8eaiIyrSi1JNj6MBA==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><em>More</em></a>', 'What\'s In a Name?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'whats-in-a-name', '', '', '2014-10-09 16:08:46', '2014-10-09 16:08:46', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2099', '0', 'post', '', '0');
