Recruit the support of your doctor, pharmacist, and health coach. Your doctor can help determine if prescription medication or over the counter quit aids are best for you.\r\n\r\nJust one day after your last cigarette, your heart rate and blood pressure will drop back to normal and your risk for a heart attack begins to decrease. Although symptoms of nicotine withdrawal like headache and nervousness usually peak around 3 days after quitting, they usually go away within 2 weeks. Quitting smoking is not a one-size-fits-all solution, so choose the combination of methods that work best for you. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001Rdgex7ALekzV1tAuYiL5WobXkgB0JyvUbxz4FJYqM1yRWvO2STOOL95YNhwuNxyR-EgjAOmKSZ0ogHb-BNtF49bTAoiR_WygHrKZGuNnJaWYtnnjLT5N8OFIdVK6_vmjptF_GOUhvBTmj_wfYXmzDZ9ioVOFo6fFItqeSr1uAscmjxTLQb_Z_ctsmhc0FFIf2kZkZ3y7AvUy9jplTdXLSN8DJPh5G8RVM7nU-fTgTiK3s3dQy_b7N2LQqjKOPfKy&amp;c=k8qCW_O0LK017Lmbd1uBMgQ2Vrc8WraC_caY8_ohMRaoxyVrC0p3-Q==&amp;ch=TC-NnHouBrnyjjHrw13P2LRARXkFBdedGyDvRkOP2oF4TYz2-Gv8Ng==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><em>More</em></a>', 'Pick A Quit Date', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'pick-a-quit-date', '', '', '2014-11-19 21:24:57', '2014-11-19 21:24:57', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2127', '0', 'post', '', '0');
