o improve health. These devices vary in complexity and range in price to meet any budget and need. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001pYPOp9M7RW2Q2X14WGJEKb-S7KaaQlmJsZH1TY43F0MWb2L6nmpV68aqiCxBfTI2cLTHVfrZBk_dct99qCmvOj9aXhev6eAgHDj5jLes37uF9K5Z9UnuMcNGMIipPhmFf32pUYahFIGzR-Qxe_Lzf1-OrBn9BuoUICBHz5jLEDLUW9A6gxY87V3xa-koxZ8YrC5JR6Mj-3omQtdeUwU9jvY6qrg7NVXb&amp;c=F0iBj5wku9Rh1OVlgsK-srf9yu2cvUjYKjL9M4pZcQRj7-hpjOwwRA==&amp;ch=LtdIU694q0tfaLU5kzBvBEW-wk1VRnSMcVSwDWEPtNGQss4VF3tqSg==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><em>More</em></a>', 'Gift Trends in Wearable Wellness', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2138-revision', '', '', '2014-12-16 22:37:18', '2014-12-16 22:37:18', '', '2138', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/2138-revision/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2140', '14', '2014-12-05 22:37:38', '2014-12-05 22:37:38', '<em>Maintain, Don\'t Gain, this Holiday Season </em>\r\n\r\n<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\r\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\r\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\r\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\r\n <v:formulas>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\r\n </v:formulas>\r\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\r\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\r\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1029\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\r\n margin-left:0;margin-top:772.5pt;width:111.75pt;height:75.75pt;z-index:251658240;\r\n mso-wrap-distance-left:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:3.75pt;\r\n mso-wrap-distance-right:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:3.75pt;\r\n mso-position-horizontal:left;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\r\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\r\n <v:imagedata src=\"https://files.ctctcdn.com/e660abde001/8c2832c5-f9e9-4268-a660-4f6edcdae9ae.jpg\"/>\r\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\r\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"https://files.ctctcdn.com/e660abde001/8c2832c5-f9e9-4268-a660-4f6edcdae9ae.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.1161\" width=\"149\" height=\"101\" align=\"left\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /><!--[endif]-->Half of all annual weight gain occurs during the 6 week holiday period, but the sobering part is most of this weight gain is retained indefinitely. The science behind this is the body\'s control system called the set point. The body fat set point helped hunters and gatherers survive in periods of food scarcity and abundance and has evolved as a modern mechanism for our bodies to internally control the ideal set point by increasing or decreasing weight.\r\n\r\nSlow weight gain over time will override the body\'s ability to defend an ideal weight leading to a higher, less healthy, set point. The added weight will fool your body into thinking the set point is higher than it should be making it harder to lose weight. But take heart, just as it\'s possible to increase you set point, it\'s also possible to lower your set point by losing weight slowly and increasing physical activity. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001pYPOp9M7RW2Q2X14WGJEKb-S7KaaQlmJsZH1TY43F0MWb2L6nmpV6wTb8CdUtMswgmbymvHxPjAh4zeuOLYtHqCcY552FCifqDsYoQBa07sIRye4P5ennCJtb5UGTRPjpiheDHQq9C0Sxsb9Y1uTNa7Vui3XeVuBFmiUD0wvi7APdUfZ5lIE3fOOMjV2zithEnEzFTtCDGcq0bMeMrgQ8WCvBnAGK4N9YZ4auig8WxCGty-L3mHXVA==&amp;c=F0iBj5wku9Rh1OVlgsK-srf9yu2cvUjYKjL9M4pZcQRj7-hpjOwwRA==&amp;ch=LtdIU694q0tfaLU5kzBvBEW-wk1VRnSMcVSwDWEPtNGQss4VF3tqSg==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><em>More</em></a>', 'The Science Behind the Set Point ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-science-behind-the-set-point', '', '', '2014-12-16 22:38:22', '2014-12-16 22:38:22', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2140', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2141', '14', '2014-12-16 22:37:59', '2014-12-16 22:37:59', '&nbsp;\n\nHalf of all annual weight gain occurs during the 6 week holiday period, but the sobering part is most of this weight gain is retained indefinitely. The science behind this is the body\'s control system called the set point. The body fat set point helped hunters and gatherers survive in periods of food scarcity and abundance and has evolved as a modern mechanism for our bodies to internally control the ideal set point by increasing or decreasing weight.\n\nSlow weight gain over time will override the body\'s ability to defend an ideal weight leading to a higher, less healthy, set point. The added weight will fool your body into thinking the set point is higher than it should be making it harder to lose weight. But take heart, just as it\'s possible to increase you set point, it\'s also possible to lower your set point by losing weight slowly and increasing physical activity. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001pYPOp9M7RW2Q2X14WGJEKb-S7KaaQlmJsZH1TY43F0MWb2L6nmpV6wTb8CdUtMswgmbymvHxPjAh4zeuOLYtHqCcY552FCifqDsYoQBa07sIRye4P5ennCJtb5UGTRPjpiheDHQq9C0Sxsb9Y1uTNa7Vui3XeVuBFmiUD0wvi7APdUfZ5lIE3fOOMjV2zithEnEzFTtCDGcq0bMeMrgQ8WCvBnAGK4N9YZ4auig8WxCGty-L3mHXVA==&amp;c=F0iBj5wku9Rh1OVlgsK-srf9yu2cvUjYKjL9M4pZcQRj7-hpjOwwRA==&amp;ch=LtdIU694q0tfaLU5kzBvBEW-wk1VRnSMcVSwDWEPtNGQss4VF3tqSg==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><em>More</em></a>', 'The Science Behind the Set Point ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2140-revision', '', '', '2014-12-16 22:37:59', '2014-12-16 22:37:59', '', '2140', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/2140-revision/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2142', '14', '2014-12-11 22:38:37', '2014-12-11 22:38:37', '<!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t75\"\r\n coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\"\r\n filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\r\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\r\n <v:formulas>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\r\n </v:formulas>\r\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\r\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\r\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_s1030\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" alt=\"\" style=\'position:absolute;\r\n margin-left:335.05pt;margin-top:956.25pt;width:162.75pt;height:110.25pt;\r\n z-index:251658240;mso-wrap-distance-left:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:3.75pt;\r\n mso-wrap-distance-right:3.75pt;mso-wrap-distance-bottom:3.75pt;\r\n mso-position-horizontal:right;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;\r\n mso-position-vertical-relative:line\' o:allowoverlap=\"f\">\r\n <v:imagedata src=\"https://files.ctctcdn.com/e660abde001/df3422a5-fd63-4708-bbcb-a12abef64225.jpg\"/>\r\n <w:wrap type=\"square\"/>\r\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img src=\"https://files.ctctcdn.com/e660abde001/df3422a5-fd63-4708-bbcb-a12abef64225.jpg\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.1162\" width=\"217\" height=\"147\" align=\"right\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /><!--[endif]-->Protein is an important component in every process and cell of the body. This macronutrient is needed to make hormones, bones, hair, nails, muscles, skin, and blood. The FDA recommends adults get about 50g of protein daily, however that varies with age, gender, and daily caloric intake. The quality and source of protein is important, and protein from processed meats should be limited.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Animal protein from </strong>fish, eggs, and poultry are complete sources of protein and contain all the amino acids our bodies need to function properly.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Plant based protein </strong>from beans, nuts, and whole grains contain fiber and can lower the risk of heart disease and certain cancers.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Isolated protein powders </strong>like whey, soy, brown rice, and casein are found in powder form and used as supplemental nutrition in addition to a diet already containing high quality protein.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nProtein can aid in weight loss by helping you feel fuller longer and also help build muscle. Too much protein, however, may cause kidney and liver problems. Unlike fats and carbohydrates, protein is not stored in the body and must be replenished. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001pYPOp9M7RW2Q2X14WGJEKb-S7KaaQlmJsZH1TY43F0MWb2L6nmpV6wTb8CdUtMswwfadJoVBJZcONBdu9RQV19plT_b-OpKrx_d6s6m3OLt1D29F86JdWcEp-MCpG2AvrhJjMjbH3U5vx9J9eFcAIEFRV_088KXR1VFwqcPlNlI0WFw_emxeh_J2OcWSjV5hGccHhEI1VgtYGx4uf7aivw==&amp;c=F0iBj5wku9Rh1OVlgsK-srf9yu2cvUjYKjL9M4pZcQRj7-hpjOwwRA==&amp;ch=LtdIU694q0tfaLU5kzBvBEW-wk1VRnSMcVSwDWEPtNGQss4VF3tqSg==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><em>More</em></a>', 'The Power of Protein', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-power-of-protein', '', '', '2014-12-16 22:39:07', '2014-12-16 22:39:07', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2142', '0', 'post', '', '0');
