-><!--[if !vml]--><a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001pYPOp9M7RW2Q2X14WGJEKb-S7KaaQlmJsZH1TY43F0MWb2L6nmpV68aqiCxBfTI2c2fcie4AsyTigrXHbls9Iev9-alv3tTFhpUyondaOGkb3bwVDper-o5sB0wZLSXuNRybWlZxrAC-CSGLZmMPHD9zYGEvS_pwVe5me7cV3R5sy5Y8ILmz1F31t-iI_tj-dtzhLs2ZeTLl1Y_MDuOvAXzIaJxEIdhPmpv6p6xPJd0=&amp;c=F0iBj5wku9Rh1OVlgsK-srf9yu2cvUjYKjL9M4pZcQRj7-hpjOwwRA==&amp;ch=LtdIU694q0tfaLU5kzBvBEW-wk1VRnSMcVSwDWEPtNGQss4VF3tqSg==\" target=\"&quot;_blank&quot;\"><img src=\"https://files.ctctcdn.com/e660abde001/bdb455ff-4ba6-4e3a-bea1-c41efc1aa413.png\" alt=\"\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.1160\" width=\"204\" height=\"276\" align=\"right\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></a><!--[endif]-->This festive recipe sneaks protein and antioxidants into a sweet holiday treat. There is no right or wrong way to top the bark, so try creative combinations of your favorite nuts, seeds, and dried fruits.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>3/4 cup dried cherries</li>\r\n	<li>1/2 cup unsalted pistachios</li>\r\n	<li>1/4 cup crystallized ginger</li>\r\n	<li>7 ounces dark chocolate (60-70% cocoa), chopped into chunks</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nCombine nuts, dried fruit, and ginger in a medium bowl. Line baking sheet with foil and chill pan. Melt chocolate over double boiler and stir in half of the fruit mixture. Spread chocolate mixture over prepared pan, then quickly sprinkle remaining fruit mixture evenly over top. Let harden and break into pieces.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001pYPOp9M7RW2Q2X14WGJEKb-S7KaaQlmJsZH1TY43F0MWb2L6nmpV68aqiCxBfTI2c2fcie4AsyTigrXHbls9Iev9-alv3tTFhpUyondaOGkb3bwVDper-o5sB0wZLSXuNRybWlZxrAC-CSGLZmMPHD9zYGEvS_pwVe5me7cV3R5sy5Y8ILmz1F31t-iI_tj-dtzhLs2ZeTLl1Y_MDuOvAXzIaJxEIdhPmpv6p6xPJd0=&amp;c=F0iBj5wku9Rh1OVlgsK-srf9yu2cvUjYKjL9M4pZcQRj7-hpjOwwRA==&amp;ch=LtdIU694q0tfaLU5kzBvBEW-wk1VRnSMcVSwDWEPtNGQss4VF3tqSg==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><em>Click here to get the full recipe from Health.com.</em></a>', 'Recipe of the Month- Holiday Fruit and Nut Bark', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'recipe-of-the-month-holiday-fruit-and-nut-bark', '', '', '2014-12-16 22:39:56', '2014-12-16 22:39:56', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2144', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2145', '14', '2014-12-16 22:39:27', '2014-12-16 22:39:27', 'This festive recipe sneaks protein and antioxidants into a sweet holiday treat. There is no right or wrong way to top the bark, so try creative combinations of your favorite nuts, seeds, and dried fruits.\n<ul>\n	<li>3/4 cup dried cherries</li>\n	<li>1/2 cup unsalted pistachios</li>\n	<li>1/4 cup crystallized ginger</li>\n	<li>7 ounces dark chocolate (60-70% cocoa), chopped into chunks</li>\n</ul>\nCombine nuts, dried fruit, and ginger in a medium bowl. Line baking sheet with foil and chill pan. Melt chocolate over double boiler and stir in half of the fruit mixture. Spread chocolate mixture over prepared pan, then quickly sprinkle remaining fruit mixture evenly over top. Let harden and break into pieces.\n\n<a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001pYPOp9M7RW2Q2X14WGJEKb-S7KaaQlmJsZH1TY43F0MWb2L6nmpV68aqiCxBfTI2c2fcie4AsyTigrXHbls9Iev9-alv3tTFhpUyondaOGkb3bwVDper-o5sB0wZLSXuNRybWlZxrAC-CSGLZmMPHD9zYGEvS_pwVe5me7cV3R5sy5Y8ILmz1F31t-iI_tj-dtzhLs2ZeTLl1Y_MDuOvAXzIaJxEIdhPmpv6p6xPJd0=&amp;c=F0iBj5wku9Rh1OVlgsK-srf9yu2cvUjYKjL9M4pZcQRj7-hpjOwwRA==&amp;ch=LtdIU694q0tfaLU5kzBvBEW-wk1VRnSMcVSwDWEPtNGQss4VF3tqSg==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><em>Click here to get the full recipe from Health.com.</em></a>', 'Recipe of the Month- Holiday Fruit and Nut Bark', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2144-revision', '', '', '2014-12-16 22:39:27', '2014-12-16 22:39:27', '', '2144', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/2144-revision/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
