 exert maximum force in short intervals of time. These high intensity exercises involve repeated jumping and rebounding to improve explosive power and agility. When performed correctly, the stretching and contracting of muscles lead to increased vertical height jump, greater speed, and less risk of injury.\r\n\r\nPlyometric exercises are great for athletes who train for activities that use explosive movements like basketball, track &amp; field, or tennis. In children, games like hopscotch, skipping, and jumping rope qualify as plyometric exercise. For adults, emphasis is typically placed on lower body exercises like jump squats, box jumps, and agility drills. Upper body plyometrics typically include a medicine ball. Two to three days between plyometric exercises are essential to allow for recovery in the muscle tissue. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=0017mQ0Vc9mTDayFEc5IUUHkUY6YeDaODTbYps_BuCFoJMOHhp6JwtqYravzpza4PkSfD108zuvJuIgTVZ7kQ44yIIbKW85Hyfctd4snK2bgYAwEgk2JLBFLr-lNdz0kB2xE2-cU3N6-hX4cQpReG6alfLAIP4J201aSUROimv6mcTByZrXpR2QGSCS_yvGaR6boJhc1efkMBMEFrfF9JlUy9Cj8kpuCGJOpOQEahQtMTHlAVRknQ6sGEjFzi4Fa3VvXwtNT6N212s=&amp;c=7kuIi6nbcTS4KiiKEBSTgbdPa3ftbimuf4k16i1FNU9V3ULGVwbfYQ==&amp;ch=ozkcvucfpT9MG5m3KdXxOTGo7_ZcgY8FarDYLgtYwrTS_vtQouxHVQ==\" shape=\"rect\" target=\"_blank\"><em>More</em></a>', 'Jump into Plyometrics', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'jump-into-plyometrics', '', '', '2015-02-26 20:32:17', '2015-02-26 20:32:17', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2190', '0', 'post', '', '0');
