INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2213', '14', '2015-03-08 11:12:01', '2015-03-08 17:12:01', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Slow-Down.png\"><img class=\"  wp-image-2214 alignright\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Slow-Down.png\" alt=\"Slow Down\" width=\"125\" height=\"178\" /></a>Eating is not a race, nor will food run away if left unattended. Since it takes 20 minutes from the time you start eating for your brain to register fullness, eating quickly may not cue satiety, leading to overeating.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Mindfully recognize the texture, taste, smell, and look of food before eating.</li>\r\n	<li>Eat only at a table, not distracted while driving or in front of a TV or computer.</li>\r\n	<li>Set your fork down between bites so you aren\'t primed to quickly eat the next bite.</li>\r\n	<li>Sip on water throughout the meal. Hunger is often mistaken for thirst.</li>\r\n	<li>Take small bites and chew food thoroughly.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nEating slower can be learned. Practice rating your hunger on a scale from 1-10 where a 10 is uncomfortably stuffed. Keep your rating between a 5-6, neither too hungry nor too full. Listen to your body. It\'s okay to leave food on your plate. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001GHD60b0JLJrECcZUd6Uqyh_NkVZcld0iLkECO6b2h-ai5AkK4B0uUM9-0BvQjP80TjFPrinAJqLg8BNQn8iQt6gHfrYdY-1nzoh7tNsxhZH4se7LEX7gq8tfOTx5OdR8YqdRmPVPLhqTkEC3owL_zAujLpNbk4xvx5y1hcl7ownp7kxrIfBD6lA4Rn5huYTijagIForjOVns-QJYB48jWXIA5ezUeiKY&amp;c=6gutJPHZfMCRd0c6TfecsBIsnNxQDcLxVJd2uvxJlkoVXjJ6I-0k9g==&amp;ch=YCvv2OQhHU2nCD5xNj8fkRSXZ0UcqdWXZu3gDzDUB1x3Yh-jMVVC7A==\"><em>More</em></a>', 'Slow Down to Slow Overeating', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'slow-down-to-slow-overeating', '', '', '2015-03-20 11:14:44', '2015-03-20 17:14:44', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2213', '0', 'post', '', '0');
