INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2224', '14', '2015-03-18 11:20:17', '2015-03-18 17:20:17', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Carpal-Tunnel.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-2218\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Carpal-Tunnel-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"Carpal Tunnel\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>Carpal tunnel syndrome is a common yet painful condition caused by repetitive motions like typing and using hand tools. The carpal tunnel is an anatomical passageway for the nerve that controls feeling to the palm and fingers. When that nerve gets compressed due to inflammation, illness, or poor ergonomics, pain and numbness can occur. Symptoms of carpal tunnel syndrome usually start gradually with tingling and numbness in the index, middle, and ring fingers and hand.\r\n\r\nEarly diagnosis and treatment can prevent permanent damage. Many people who develop carpal tunnel syndrome can reverse the damage without surgery. Putting the wrist in a splint, over the counter anti-inflammatory drugs, and ice packs can help with inflammation and pain. Workers should take frequent breaks from repetitive activities to stretch the palms, fingers, and wrist often. Proper posture, ergonomics, rest, and maintaining a healthy weight can also improve symptoms. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001GHD60b0JLJrECcZUd6Uqyh_NkVZcld0iLkECO6b2h-ai5AkK4B0uUM9-0BvQjP804YiwA_YWPXeYQIwe7pLaUS82VuPvzWFOn-AVvSaiUWsdGGfTm9752UlVeOVIhjL_cLJWxeapDrAaW6FOi8U8Qc43IPTLVC58FXhur7nXyL9sKU6RN7_vgMKaYmhJ8k6Ds79Mp9U24cldRmX5reg6Bcw0yD3NqSuN0PclW-rpPsmqLM_N39_zIyegSokLHxQsUnhuaPXTJ8g=&amp;c=6gutJPHZfMCRd0c6TfecsBIsnNxQDcLxVJd2uvxJlkoVXjJ6I-0k9g==&amp;ch=YCvv2OQhHU2nCD5xNj8fkRSXZ0UcqdWXZu3gDzDUB1x3Yh-jMVVC7A==\"><em>More</em></a>', 'Stopping Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'stopping-carpal-tunnel-syndrome', '', '', '2015-03-20 11:21:14', '2015-03-20 17:21:14', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2224', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2225', '14', '2015-03-20 11:21:14', '2015-03-20 17:21:14', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Carpal-Tunnel.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-2218\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Carpal-Tunnel-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"Carpal Tunnel\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>Carpal tunnel syndrome is a common yet painful condition caused by repetitive motions like typing and using hand tools. The carpal tunnel is an anatomical passageway for the nerve that controls feeling to the palm and fingers. When that nerve gets compressed due to inflammation, illness, or poor ergonomics, pain and numbness can occur. Symptoms of carpal tunnel syndrome usually start gradually with tingling and numbness in the index, middle, and ring fingers and hand.\r\n\r\nEarly diagnosis and treatment can prevent permanent damage. Many people who develop carpal tunnel syndrome can reverse the damage without surgery. Putting the wrist in a splint, over the counter anti-inflammatory drugs, and ice packs can help with inflammation and pain. Workers should take frequent breaks from repetitive activities to stretch the palms, fingers, and wrist often. Proper posture, ergonomics, rest, and maintaining a healthy weight can also improve symptoms. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001GHD60b0JLJrECcZUd6Uqyh_NkVZcld0iLkECO6b2h-ai5AkK4B0uUM9-0BvQjP804YiwA_YWPXeYQIwe7pLaUS82VuPvzWFOn-AVvSaiUWsdGGfTm9752UlVeOVIhjL_cLJWxeapDrAaW6FOi8U8Qc43IPTLVC58FXhur7nXyL9sKU6RN7_vgMKaYmhJ8k6Ds79Mp9U24cldRmX5reg6Bcw0yD3NqSuN0PclW-rpPsmqLM_N39_zIyegSokLHxQsUnhuaPXTJ8g=&amp;c=6gutJPHZfMCRd0c6TfecsBIsnNxQDcLxVJd2uvxJlkoVXjJ6I-0k9g==&amp;ch=YCvv2OQhHU2nCD5xNj8fkRSXZ0UcqdWXZu3gDzDUB1x3Yh-jMVVC7A==\"><em>More</em></a>', 'Stopping Carpal Tunnel Syndrome', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2224-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-20 11:21:14', '2015-03-20 17:21:14', '', '2224', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/2224-revi