INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2242', '14', '2015-04-10 11:11:17', '2015-04-10 17:11:17', '<img src=\"http://files.ctctcdn.com/e660abde001/dccbda55-e609-40ba-a846-6e524a614522.jpg?a=1120545671013\" alt=\"Girl sitting in a meadow with dandelions and has hay fever or allergy\" width=\"144\" height=\"95\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.1325\" align=\"left\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" />\r\n\r\nPollen allergy, or hay fever, is the #1 cause of workplace absenteeism resulting in nearly 4 million missed workdays or lost productivity each year. Allergies are the body\'s way of over-reacting to an allergen through inflammatory responses such as sneezing, itching, or skin rashes. The best way to control seasonal allergies is to know and avoid the triggers that plague you. Your doctor can perform a quick and accurate skin test that identifies your allergens.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Be cautious of indoor/outdoor pets when pollen counts are high.</li>\r\n	<li>Avoid the outdoors in the morning when pollen counts are the highest.</li>\r\n	<li>Keep windows and doors shut in the home and cars.</li>\r\n	<li>Stay ahead of allergies by beginning an over-the-counter allergy regimen 1-2 weeks before the pollen season begins.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nRecognizing and avoiding allergens in asthmatics can prevent asthma attacks triggered from allergies. If you see early signs of an asthma attack when pollen counts are high, seek treatment as soon as possible to avoid a severe asthma attack. <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/allergies/features/severe-allergies\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" shape=\"rect\">More</a>', 'Controlling Seasonal Allergies', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'controlling-seasonal-allergies', '', '', '2015-04-23 11:12:05', '2015-04-23 17:12:05', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2242', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2243', '14', '2015-04-23 11:12:05', '2015-04-23 17:12:05', '<img src=\"http://files.ctctcdn.com/e660abde001/dccbda55-e609-40ba-a846-6e524a614522.jpg?a=1120545671013\" alt=\"Girl sitting in a meadow with dandelions and has hay fever or allergy\" width=\"144\" height=\"95\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.1325\" align=\"left\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" />\r\n\r\nPollen allergy, or hay fever, is the #1 cause of workplace absenteeism resulting in nearly 4 million missed workdays or lost productivity each year. Allergies are the body\'s way of over-reacting to an allergen through inflammatory responses such as sneezing, itching, or skin rashes. The best way to control seasonal allergies is to know and avoid the triggers that plague you. Your doctor can perform a quick and accurate skin test that identifies your allergens.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Be cautious of indoor/outdoor pets when pollen counts are high.</li>\r\n	<li>Avoid the outdoors in the morning when pollen counts are the highest.</li>\r\n	<li>Keep windows and doors shut in the home and cars.</li>\r\n	<li>Stay ahead of allergies by beginning an over-the-counter allergy regimen 1-2 weeks before the pollen season begins.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nRecognizing and avoiding allergens in asthmatics can prevent asthma attacks triggered from allergies. If you see early signs of an asthma attack when pollen counts are high, seek treatment as soon as possible to avoid a severe asthma attack. <a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/allergies/features/severe-allergies\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" shape=\"rect\">More</a>', 'Controlling Seasonal Allergies', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2242-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-04-23 11:12:05', '2015-04-23 17:12:05', '', '2242', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/2242-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2244', '14', '2015-04-15 11:12:18', '2015-04-15 17:12:18', '<div><img src=\"http://files.ctctcdn.com/e660abde001/6ef44ed8-7a8b-4aeb-94a0-2a7d7facc38a.jpg?a=1120545671013\" alt=\"\" width=\"173\" height=\"115\" name=\"ACCOUNT.IMAGE.1323\" align=\"right\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></div>\r\nVarieties of flour can range from exotic types like gluten-free chickpea flour and pumpernickel flour to the everyday enriched bleached flour found in much of our food supply. In general, refined white foods like white flour, white rice, pasta, and white potatoes should be limited or replaced with the whole grain option instead. While it\'s difficult to completely avoid foods containing flour, understanding the difference in nutrition can be helpful in making smarter decisions as a consumer:\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Whole Wheat Flour</strong> is made from the entire kernel of hard red wheat and is high in fiber and nutritional content. Whole wheat flours have a shorter shelf-life and should be stored in a fridge or freezer.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>White Whole Wheat Flour</strong> is made from hard white wheat and is paler than whole wheat. White whole-wheat and whole wheat flour have the same nutritional value.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Bleached vs unbleached flour </strong>can be used interchangeably in cooking and are typically no different in price. The bleaching comes from benzol peroxide or chlorine gas to create a bright white appeal. Unbleached flour is aged naturally, therefore is more tan in color and is a better source of nutrients like vitamin E.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>All-Purpose Flour </strong>can be bleached or unbleached and is the most commonly used flour. Because it doesn\'t contain the germ nor the bran of the wheat kernel, US law requires it be labeled \"enriched\" by adding back niacin, riboflavin, thiamine, folic acid, and iron that was removed during processing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAll wheat flours contain gluten, a protein that makes baked goods elastic. Those with Celiac disease or gluten sensitivities should opt for wheat-free flours like brown rice flour or corn flour.  <a href=\"http://www.mayoclinic.org/healthy-lifestyle/nutrition-and-healthy-eating/in-depth/whole-grains/art-20047826\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" shape=\"rect\">More</a>', 'Refining the Facts on Flour', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'refining-the-facts-on-flour', '', '', '2015-04-23 11:13:20', '2015-04-23 17:13:20', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2244', '0', 'post', '', '0');
