INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2265', '14', '2015-05-21 14:29:28', '2015-05-21 20:29:28', '<div>The brain and digestive system share a complex connection that becomes more vulnerable during times of stress. The gut is also known as the second brain and may explain how stress affects a wide range of digestive issues including:<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Stomach.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-2262\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Stomach-150x150.png\" alt=\"Stomach\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Irritable Bowel Syndrome</li>\r\n	<li>Ulcers</li>\r\n	<li>Heart burn and indigestion</li>\r\n	<li>Inflammatory Bowel Diseases</li>\r\n	<li>Changes in appetite</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nHaving a gut-feeling is one indication of how strong the brain and digestive tract communicate during times of stress. When stress occurs, the brain sends signals to the digestive system to either slow digestion or stop it completely so all energy is being diverted to the stressor. Long term stress, when left unmanaged, leads to a host of gastrointestional disorders and explains why inflammatory bowel diseases like Chron\'s and colitis are exacerbated during times of chronic stress.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>If you think stress may be the root of your digestive issues, stress management techniques, cognitive behavior therapy, relaxation therapy, and hypnosis have all been proven effective therapies to provide relief.<a href=\"http://www.webmd.com/parenting/features/anxiety-stress-and-stomachaches\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" shape=\"rect\">More</a></div>', 'Stress and Your Stomach', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2259-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-05-21 14:29:28', '2015-05-21 20:29:28', '', '2259', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/2259-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2266', '14', '2015-05-09 14:29:38', '2015-05-09 20:29:38', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Physician-Relationship.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-2264\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Physician-Relationship-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"Physician Relationship\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>Preventive screenings are one of the most proactive things you can do for you health. Detecting and treating illness in the early stages can provide the best outcomes. The Centers for Disease Control has set guidelines that apply to healthy adults in the general population. Work with your physician to develop the best plan for you, as your needs may differ based on your health risks, family history, and physician recommendations. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001Yho2juwkbO5_KdeGEDh3R4ERjwVQ-GgjaywEnxDVJAx09d_bwzX00YcbExHmHJDPhRPCPo-5B-uL2ezsHtla_PvoBtHMgnGcji9cAUrNpQ4iqfVrCsu02MkHQQVbckOKgdBNE2q4_aRPwBgadfDo0IVsKO5hDoJP2iLuxVDam1LMWCbPKmDohg==&amp;c=lOF5qHyC3fxbBM-TaXUETFJmGSnmIn7f07KKzJMuCS3tDUXBUwvLsA==&amp;ch=_3yMhgxP2yb0LuyxoHtUL_A2-XaKoaqAT2nL_3KMZM4nrBVF4x0pWQ==\"><em>More</em></a>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Cholesterol</strong>- Recommended for all adults starting at age 20 or earlier if high risk for heart disease.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Colorectal screening</strong>- Colonoscopy for all adults over the age of 50 every 10 years, or more frequently based on results and risk for colon cancer.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Dermatology</strong>- Skin cancer screening every 3 years for all adults over the age of 18.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Well-Woman screening</strong>- Pap test every 1-3 years for all women over the age of 21.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Prostate Exam</strong>- Annual digital rectal exam and prostate specific antigen (PSA) test for all men over the age of 50.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Breast exam</strong>- Monthly self-exam recommended for all women over 20 and mammogram for women over 40 every 1-2 years.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Get Screened. Stay Healthy.', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'get-screened-stay-healthy', '', '', '2015-05-21 14:30:26', '2015-05-21 20:30:26', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2266', '0', 'post', '', '0');
