INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2271', '14', '2015-05-21 14:32:20', '2015-05-21 20:32:20', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Yoga-Flow.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-2263\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Yoga-Flow-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"Yoga Flow\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>The ancient practice of yoga originated in India thousands of years ago and slowly made its way to the US in the 1980s. As it gains popularity, more Americans are reaping the benefits. Yoga practice moves through a series of poses and flows that focus on breathing, self-awareness, and stretching. Benefits of yoga are shown to reduce insomnia, lower blood pressure, reduce weight, increase energy, and provide protection from injury.\r\n\r\nIn addition to the physical benefits, yoga can impact the mind, body, and spirit to improve mental well-being. Yoga has been shown to improve resiliency and coping skills, relieve chronic stress, and gain a more positive outlook on life. You do not have to be flexible or athletic to do yoga, as modifications for easier yoga poses can accommodate all fitness levels and abilities. Try it at home with <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001Yho2juwkbO5_KdeGEDh3R4ERjwVQ-GgjaywEnxDVJAx09d_bwzX00YcbExHmHJDPMvlR6pQaMR-SBRjbVghzJ94uuefY6iCZxfgJW3S_OFwalhMfJ1RwtBD8cG47CIVGk3-5InQdC8NE138YvxPgrR0d2gmmLhmzm4e7dXhM38P9hBwLRM_OAKU7c-lvAnrSH5gfl6q5g6EANw2MNpg53g==&amp;c=lOF5qHyC3fxbBM-TaXUETFJmGSnmIn7f07KKzJMuCS3tDUXBUwvLsA==&amp;ch=_3yMhgxP2yb0LuyxoHtUL_A2-XaKoaqAT2nL_3KMZM4nrBVF4x0pWQ==\">beginner</a> and <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001Yho2juwkbO5_KdeGEDh3R4ERjwVQ-GgjaywEnxDVJAx09d_bwzX00YcbExHmHJDPw0UlxfaWY1P--BmfCiTuEwwSsjOfIhJd-mUTdoMRiHHeRdz_wBW-Sa7ifprDNfA-pMw7DvBuMpCUezTRChWTjcLeuxfgp8Hu2AEYXiFv22nIOcsq5fKifDqP59pxG-dtxkJOxZxvb1v7gP2j_BRL73AbVqWOJLIF8muCTokGCVavMEPIdL8BW9Z6DbjhiE2SFMVcq30WM-dLyWXt6F5z1MsI3pFdO4b-AssdvA1GXRalQOuJkb5zrpEXq6HGFcomcqvhGa2qqj4=&amp