INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2293', '14', '2015-06-18 11:25:09', '2015-06-18 17:25:09', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/summer-heat.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-2290\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/summer-heat-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"summer heat\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>A little extra diligence and planning will keep you and your loved ones safe this summer! Guard yourself against these common summer emergencies.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>When it doubt, throw it out-</strong> The rule of \"not letting food sit out for more than two hours\" is shortened to one hour if the temperature is above 90º F.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Swim smart-</strong> Never boat or swim alone. Young children or inexperienced swimmers should always wear a life jacket. Always supervise kids around water, even with a lifeguard present.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Cover Up-</strong> The hours between 10am-4pm are the most hazardous for UV radiation exposure. Reapply sunscreen with an SPF of 15 or higher every two hours when you\'re in the sun or right after you swim. Make sure the sunscreen protects against UVA and UVB rays.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWatch for signs of heat exhaustion or heat stroke, especially in children. Kids\' bodies absorb more heat on a hot day than adults, and children are less able to lower their body heat by sweating. Watch for red and hot skin, absence of sweating, an abnormally fast or slow pulse, a throbbing headache, dizziness, confusion, or strange behavior. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001GMAWedr49fh3ISFKxGgKn_hpr1BKvGPvuOYgGnFK3O6Wc8YBcVoUHkEFa3OCvx--YH8p8BtboIEkinVh08yZEBMdaKkkRkwztlxCw1oOR0td528t2w5Jjz9J7u0m_raakstPUYz88xKgnfsMeUMfubrOO9qslvOf8Wba_cI4kNQ=\"><em>More</em></a>', 'Beat the Summer Heat', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2287-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-18 11:25:09', '2015-06-18 17:25:09', '', '2287', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/2287-revisio