INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2294', '14', '2015-06-12 11:25:26', '2015-06-12 17:25:26', '<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/water.jpg\"><img class=\" size-thumbnail wp-image-2292 alignleft\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/water-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"water\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>Over 60% of an adult\'s body is made up of water. Every system in the body depends on water to carry nutrients to cells and flush toxins. Although the \"eight, 8 ounce glasses\" rule is easy to remember, there is no magic number for how much water is right for you. The Institute of Medicine determined a daily adequate intake of water is about 13 cups (3 liters) for men, and 9 cups (2.2 liters) for women.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Exercise level, humidity, hot weather, and caffeine can all increase water needs. Caffeinated beverages like soda and coffee act as a diuretic excreting excess water from the body. Drink one cup of water within an hour of every caffeinated beverage consumed to replace water stores. Drink water before, during, and after exercise, as up to 2-5 pounds of water weight can be lost during a workout and should be replaced quickly to avoid dehydration. Add some extra flavor to your water with fresh mint leaves, slices of lemon, lime, or cucumber. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001GMAWedr49fh3ISFKxGgKn_hpr1BKvGPvuOYgGnFK3O6Wc8YBcVoUHkEFa3OCvx--YH8p8BtboIGrw8GPHas0qGZbhD0sUFZxUq3yqkW-VSpHgQPaAFyq3i__fVMAp5vLLYBV9T3F1M55iHiwHDljrYDdTTrdb7-Zw9y9qtTBCZAseuKR5WUpLjnVWwSGBtXSgd_ndOr6qijE7xb4qxJSMjhrRsfCVN8Bn5Nur-88E4k=\"><em>More</em></a></p>', 'Water: The Essential Nutrient', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'water-the-essential-nutrient', '', '', '2015-06-18 11:26:26', '2015-06-18 17:26:26', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2294', '0', 'post', '', '0');
