INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2296', '14', '2015-06-18 11:27:39', '2015-06-18 17:27:39', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/coconut.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-2288\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/coconut-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"coconut\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>It\'s a fruit, it\'s a nut... it\'s a seed too! Classify it how you wish, all things coconut are flying off the shelves these days. While there are many health benefits found from the superfood, the coconut may not be all it\'s cracked up to be. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001GMAWedr49fh3ISFKxGgKn_hpr1BKvGPvuOYgGnFK3O6Wc8YBcVoUHkEFa3OCvx--YH8p8BtboIEF8ok96Q8D4fupeugozHWthDIPbvqiOgSvv342GgP4f2HC_SHCi23yHL7ghgSBxK4=\"><em>More</em></a>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Coconut Oil</strong>- With 87% saturated fat content, the medium chain fatty acid increases the bad cholesterol along with the good. Oils with less saturated fat that are liquid at room temperature, like olive and canola, are recommended over coconut. Conversely, the oil has been known to boost brain function and have beneficial beauty properties like skin and hair hydration.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Coconut Water</strong>- Dubbed \"mother nature\'s sports drink\" for its electrolytes and hydrating abilities, the refreshing water is tapped from young green coconuts and has as much potassium as 4 bananas.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Coconut Milk</strong>- A dairy-free alternative to cow\'s milk, the shelf-stable milk comes up short nutritionally with 4 grams of saturated fat per serving, no protein, and only 10% calcium, none of which is naturally occurring.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Coconut Flour</strong>- This gluten-free flour is a healthy way to add fiber to baked goods. Those with diabetes especially benefit from cooking with coconut flour because it lowers the glycemic index of foods.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Raw Coconut Flakes- </strong>The inner white meat of coconut is a low carb high fiber treat, but be cautious of portions as 1/4 cup unsweetened flakes has 9 grams of saturated fat and 100 calories.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'The Coconut Craze', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-coconut-craze', '', '', '2015-06-18 11:27:39', '2015-06-18 17:27:39', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2296', '0', 'post', '', '0');
