at of coconut is a low carb high fiber treat, but be cautious of portions as 1/4 cup unsweetened flakes has 9 grams of saturated fat and 100 calories.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'The Coconut Craze', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2296-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-18 11:27:39', '2015-06-18 17:27:39', '', '2296', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/2296-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2298', '14', '2015-06-22 11:28:00', '2015-06-22 17:28:00', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/swimming.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-2291\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/swimming-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"swimming\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>Swimming is a great low-impact cardiovascular exercise that is especially beneficial for anyone looking to increase joint range of motion or develop strength around painful joints. Since water offers 10 times the resistance of air, swimming exercises encourage strength building and cardiovascular development. There is very little risk for injury during water related exercises since the buoyancy of water reduces strain on the back, knees, and joints.\r\n\r\nAdd variety into a swimming routine by including kick boards, fins, or water weights. If this equipment isn\'t available, simply running laps, treading water, and jumping jacks can provide a great workout. Swimming is adaptable for all ages and athletic abilities. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001GMAWedr49fh3ISFKxGgKn_hpr1BKvGPvuOYgGnFK3O6Wc8YBcVoUHkEFa3OCvx--YH8p8BtboIEF8ok96Q8D4fupeugozHWtjFV82OD_ObW9a8AjaUFJ9KE8brj1BjMfAOZ9gNMpCSsDRZMbAgkblHgXEzs_x9K5PCobPFNjyC3Grh7fKQRqsg==\"><em>More</em></a>', 'A Stroke of Fitness', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'a-stroke-of-fitness', '', '', '2015-06-18 11:28:39', '2015-06-18 17:28:39', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2298', '0', 'post', '', '0');
