INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2314', '14', '2015-07-11 14:09:53', '2015-07-11 20:09:53', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/glycemic-index-pic.jpg\"><img class=\" size-thumbnail wp-image-2315 alignleft\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/glycemic-index-pic-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"glycemic index pic\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>The glycemic index has become a popular tool to guide healthy eating choices. When you eat or drink carbohydrates, your body breaks those down into glucose, the simplest form of sugar and the main source of energy for your cells. The glycemic index assigns a number to each food indicating the speed at which that breakdown occurs.\r\n\r\nLow glycemic foods like whole grains, yogurt, and legumes are digested more slowly. This slower release of glucose (sugar) into the blood stream helps you feel fuller longer. Conversely, high glycemic foods like soda, white bread, and candy are easily and quickly converted into glucose, causing a quick spike in blood sugar. Too many of these high-glycemic carbohydrates will make it harder for your body to control blood sugar, even with insulin and diabetes medication. Use <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001BLfvQ7vk2lv5d-8pDscYAs9o9UfbpjwpqVWFzoyV5YXDBdhpQ1MpqCscfgD0RKhQA88390JTpmOUhvQAfFkTHTUNsBgbY7H9SKgobwUSVDKRS-g6uRFJV34Xy-3fOtM9Ucv581ROrfRdGKTLnQCUT3_ZiKeVgnd9LinX69vgTWTcaC27MHc3Cd8-rqp9Do5UdFd6L99-XVktWLoTjkBT_WxWIif9NFBHshl358Znr0ojF-Q7DkqPuw==&amp;c=A6VqcGzdILDIHgDbP2a_XZsRgpgAXS4o3O07u-v7bGlcT7zo_075dg==&amp;ch=GKqa7GS_i1S77Vdt7rhpPdd8UejTI1yLyGNYCUguPe8-w91Nr5PTlA==\">this chart</a> to help identify slower-acting, healthier carbs from faster-acting options. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001BLfvQ7vk2lv5d-8pDscYAs9o9UfbpjwpqVWFzoyV5YXDBdhpQ1MpqCscfgD0RKhQ533kDcyFIbjmPyNvwcdz3DWcISPz3RPRylHmsAGIU7mrL3oTYQQU2D4x4TvMqfhQJ5qxf5EapQtmb04zliFJmmcRv8ANaSUJU9mPAMs_jUqJmtRSJ4VMH6K9tKoTcYlmbpmSoSc6syUUGlFxDWqLIcgpulh7Fe8yY6OcWRU