INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2342', '14', '2015-08-13 12:48:07', '2015-08-13 18:48:07', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/healthy-snack.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-2340\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/healthy-snack-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"healthy snack\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>Healthy snacks between 100-150 calories can prevent the drop in blood sugar between meals keeping your energy levels, blood sugar levels, and mental abilities steady. Since your brain uses glucose as fuel, feed it wisely with healthy combinations of protein and carbohydrates.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>1/2 banana + 1 tablespoon of peanut butter</li>\r\n	<li>1/2 cup cottage cheese + 1/2 cup fruit</li>\r\n	<li>1/2 cup Greek yogurt + 1 tablespoon of dried cranberries</li>\r\n	<li>10 baby carrots + 2 tablespoons of hummus</li>\r\n	<li>2 hard boiled eggs</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nNever go longer than 4 hours without food, and don\'t confuse a snack for a treat. Sip water regularly throughout the day to keep energy levels high, and be mindful that hunger is not confused for thirst. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001ifDocx7sEl8O4OqBmlnLntYnann2-SHHYnevnveP4LgEZsN7D8StpYq1WQJoqchPHlo6m_J4GsZwyRLjX0bM3vHWNerolozPehsWIsJ0xBiHyLPa8jKoEpiN2pq9kU2sOeX_xaBUfbUWo5PbIE9RTzYSWpaAkdhpyPtRAU-edoyezgUPc9s5RG8yGxDQjbw3zgc79NwdZstQV80fgT9vkd5o6y7aiXAKB_Mwg6asfVAWisgUK-XEeQ==&amp;c=s4ugFE-FmHqmsE8qZmqyHnF5tXgXR7E8lo45Da6M7-9WRMUjZzXnfQ==&amp;ch=R1d81_NR-gXMVvpUwqOU3AgxAIJO2NLIKON3fMYW5cgxguqp5Trx-w==\"><em>More</em></a>', 'Healthy Snack Attack', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2339-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-08-13 12:48:07', '2015-08-13 18:48:07', '', '2339', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/2339-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2343', '14', '2015-08-16 12:48:14', '2015-08-16 18:48:14', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/fish.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-2344\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/fish-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"fish\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>The American Heart Association recommends eating fish high in omega-3 fatty acids at least twice a week. Salmon, tuna, herring, and sardines are the best sources of heart-healthy omega-3 fats which have been shown to reduce the risk of heart disease, inflammation, and even triglycerides.\r\n\r\nIn general, wild caught fish is safer and healthier than farm raised. Additionally, smaller fish toward the bottom of the food chain like sardines have less chance of mercury build up than larger fish like shark and mackerel. Shellfish like lobster, crawfish, crab, and shrimp do not offer as much heart-healthy benefit and should be limited for those who have high cholesterol. Much of the health benefits of fish are dependent on how it is prepared. Grilling or baking fish is generally recommended over frying. One serving of fish is approximately 3 ounces, or about the size of a deck of cards. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001ifDocx7sEl8O4OqBmlnLntYnann2-SHHYnevnveP4LgEZsN7D8StpZ1zRJ7CWUhxirlfCSwM4LWsj2faI7adSwzCSDuXnK5XzNQ0M25IV1uZAtI33Ee3IzbIU4KmjckdkK90BQEP1hlMUlvIi55UcpOFpCEger65lbMWcCcCjeY8_wvi-O_SMJd0cW0_NhQF-CSFnGIyA2iYSqzi8LjbqjQ8-MR7q7n-sVsklynwS2eYohm-u4afLvaAZQSgKgnyJpcQ0gXU2ZDVcv45IUniAYWIC_d_Nmn851HArwMlgDp6zvjCqjjM06kCRdu5QQ69&amp;c=s4ugFE-FmHqmsE8qZmqyHnF5tXgXR7E8lo45Da6M7-9WRMUjZzXnfQ==&amp;ch=R1d81_NR-gXMVvpUwqOU3AgxAIJO2NLIKON3fMYW5cgxguqp5Trx-w==\"><em>More</em></a>', 'Fishin\' for Nutrition', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'fishin-for-nutrition', '', '', '2015-08-13 12:54:24', '2015-08-13 18:54:24', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2343', '0', 'post', '', '0');
