INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2349', '14', '2015-08-25 12:51:16', '2015-08-25 18:51:16', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Fresh-Berries-Popsicles.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-2350\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Fresh-Berries-Popsicles-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"Fresh-Berries-Popsicles\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>There\'s no guilt ending a hot day with these icy popsicles! The healthy pops are a sneaky way to get fruit into picky eaters. Mix your favorite combination of various berries, peaches, mangos, or bananas. If you don\'t have popsicle molds, use dixie cups and wooden popsicle sticks.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>2 cups fresh or frozen berries, thawed</li>\r\n	<li>2 tablespoons raw honey, divided</li>\r\n	<li>1 cup plain Greek yogurt</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn a blender, puree fruit until smooth. Transfer fruit to bowl and stir in 1 tablespoon honey. In separate bowl, mix yogurt and remaining honey. Alternate layers of fruit and yogurt, or mix puree and yogurt together before transferring to popsicle mold for a consistently blended pop.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001ifDocx7sEl8O4OqBmlnLntYnann2-SHHYnevnveP4LgEZsN7D8StpYJfg_6s2Rx92O709cq2qTuYlV15FQxe17mESdqsOtzVndmCB08CCALRVnDpLGV0X0MWsPj-mfdlwtv1rCZ158cK6gLvYuzdyu3sOKd25DBCo8CLIPwv8P1wRdjQKJzzZKBseEhuM-3L8RO7BTMmgmD8WaGrLF1o4l_9EHuUVOieevKbJqOF0Au9WlbOA1w48Ys-ro9BHNlcYfXYtEBUq7c=&amp;c=s4ugFE-FmHqmsE8qZmqyHnF5tXgXR7E8lo45Da6M7-9WRMUjZzXnfQ==&amp;ch=R1d81_NR-gXMVvpUwqOU3AgxAIJO2NLIKON3fMYW5cgxguqp5Trx-w==\"><em>Click here to get the full recipe from Clean Eating.</em></a>', 'Recipe of the Month- Greek Yogurt Berry Ice Pops', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'recipe-of-the-month-greek-yogurt-berry-ice-pops', '', '', '2015-08-13 12:53:48', '2015-08-13 18:53:48', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2349', '0', 'post', '', '0');
