INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2351', '14', '2015-08-13 12:53:48', '2015-08-13 18:53:48', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Fresh-Berries-Popsicles.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-2350\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Fresh-Berries-Popsicles-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"Fresh-Berries-Popsicles\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>There\'s no guilt ending a hot day with these icy popsicles! The healthy pops are a sneaky way to get fruit into picky eaters. Mix your favorite combination of various berries, peaches, mangos, or bananas. If you don\'t have popsicle molds, use dixie cups and wooden popsicle sticks.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>2 cups fresh or frozen berries, thawed</li>\r\n	<li>2 tablespoons raw honey, divided</li>\r\n	<li>1 cup plain Greek yogurt</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn a blender, puree fruit until smooth. Transfer fruit to bowl and stir in 1 tablespoon honey. In separate bowl, mix yogurt and remaining honey. Alternate layers of fruit and yogurt, or mix puree and yogurt together before transferring to popsicle mold for a consistently blended pop.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001ifDocx7sEl8O4OqBmlnLntYnann2-SHHYnevnveP4LgEZsN7D8StpYJfg_6s2Rx92O709cq2qTuYlV15FQxe17mESdqsOtzVndmCB08CCALRVnDpLGV0X0MWsPj-mfdlwtv1rCZ158cK6gLvYuzdyu3sOKd25DBCo8CLIPwv8P1wRdjQKJzzZKBseEhuM-3L8RO7BTMmgmD8WaGrLF1o4l_9EHuUVOieevKbJqOF0Au9WlbOA1w48Ys-ro9BHNlcYfXYtEBUq7c=&amp;c=s4ugFE-FmHqmsE8qZmqyHnF5tXgXR7E8lo45Da6M7-9WRMUjZzXnfQ==&amp;ch=R1d81_NR-gXMVvpUwqOU3AgxAIJO2NLIKON3fMYW5cgxguqp5Trx-w==\"><em>Click here to get the full recipe from Clean Eating.</em></a>', 'Recipe of the Month- Greek Yogurt Berry Ice Pops', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2349-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-08-13 12:53:48', '2015-08-13 18:53:48', '', '2349', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/2349-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2353', '14', '2015-08-13 12:54:24', '2015-08-13 18:54:24', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/fish.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-2344\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/fish-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"fish\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>The American Heart Association recommends eating fish high in omega-3 fatty acids at least twice a week. Salmon, tuna, herring, and sardines are the best sources of heart-healthy omega-3 fats which have been shown to reduce the risk of heart disease, inflammation, and even triglycerides.\r\n\r\nIn general, wild caught fish is safer and healthier than farm raised. Additionally, smaller fish toward the bottom of the food chain like sardines have less chance of mercury build up than larger fish like shark and mackerel. Shellfish like lobster, crawfish, crab, and shrimp do not offer as much heart-healthy benefit and should be limited for those who have high cholesterol. Much of the health benefits of fish are dependent on how it is prepared. Grilling or baking fish is generally recommended over frying. One serving of fish is approximately 3 ounces, or about the size of a deck of cards. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001ifDocx7sEl8O4OqBmlnLntYnann2-SHHYnevnveP4LgEZsN7D8StpZ1zRJ7CWUhxirlfCSwM4LWsj2faI7adSwzCSDuXnK5XzNQ0M25IV1uZAtI33Ee3IzbIU4KmjckdkK90BQEP1hlMUlvIi55UcpOFpCEger65lbMWcCcCjeY8_wvi-O_SMJd0cW0_NhQF-CSFnGIyA2iYSqzi8LjbqjQ8-MR7q7n-sVsklynwS2eYohm-u4afLvaAZQSgKgnyJpcQ0gXU2ZDVcv45IUniAYWIC_d_Nmn851HArwMlgDp6zvjCqjjM06kCRdu5QQ69&amp;c=s4ugFE-FmHqmsE8qZmqyHnF5tXgXR7E8lo45Da6M7-9WRMUjZzXnfQ==&amp;ch=R1d81_NR-gXMVvpUwqOU3AgxAIJO2NLIKON3fMYW5cgxguqp5Trx-w==\"><em>More</em></a>', 'Fishin\' for Nutrition', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2343-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-08-13 12:54:24', '2015-08-13 18:54:24', '', '2343', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/2343-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2355', '14', '2015-09-05 15:50:11', '2015-09-05 21:50:11', 'H<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Safe-Home.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright  wp-image-2360\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Safe-Home-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"Home insurance.\" width=\"196\" height=\"196\" /></a>ome is a place to relax and feel safe. The key to a safe home environment is planning and prevention. Having an emergency plan in place can prevent unintentional injuries or damage.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Create an <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=0011tvD9udTy8I7jbxUV6aMlIvh4_sKeAIGLbkomj7XrM3UiQ4bXrSsP7YN7z8NdwtVNzOQ3qF6BZo158LMJ4KI4MEujxvaDITsWXTLfsCGPLrFdlcuA5MALuyI-nZw79byEXby5c9qUiPRg_87aZ_76o85VRTcsLBfqSCi5De1Tuu2ftNdEFwG5A==&amp;c=3Neb1x8oCvXYazvdgjkHUftrjbnj96Yq_jxUtKLEbIumwUaXJ5w2iQ==&amp;ch=WXO2tZCDiMqrDGYp-D3oBS5nFNUpNxhxt5DmlMLPRB4DSeoYVR-ITA==\">emergency plan</a> for your family in case of disaster.</li>\r\n	<li>Check each smoke alarm throughout the house monthly.</li>\r\n	<li>Keep a fire extinguisher on each story of your home. Inspect it regularly.</li>\r\n	<li>Have at least one carbon monoxide detector in your home located close to sleeping areas.</li>\r\n	<li>Learn CPR and the Heimlich maneuver.</li>\r\n	<li>Dispose of expired or unused prescription medications.</li>\r\n	<li>Keep the poison control number (1-800-222-1222) in your home and programmed into your cell phone.</li>\r\n	<li>Restock First Aid kits in your car and home.</li>\r\n	<li>Always leave your driveway with your seat belt on, and avoid distractions while driving.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMost serious injuries are completely preventable. Small steps now can have life-saving benefits later. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=0011tvD9udTy8I7jbxUV6aMlIvh4_sKeAIGLbkomj7XrM3UiQ4bXrSsP5Bz3nkAcYVgJD0y2MJYG4ZXRQDwQ9MQjlC9zJgl6s_oi4ibssMKfuBa-HQyPqKvkgUxmGSJub1_WA_XgGlmSn15-z9pju8xKUMnP5aZkJtId1sREFWwqBFDoibFGr66Df-JFaODvHca0qYKTKmKTHNSlhf8DWT-GGgZ54MtchD6Kp65_uCyZG6nLLYQaUJHsnORnslsgDSG&amp;c=3Neb1x8oCvXYazvdgjkHUftrjbnj96Yq_jxUtKLEbIumwUaXJ5w2iQ==&amp;ch=WXO2tZCDiMqrDGYp-D3oBS5nFNUpNxhxt5DmlMLPRB4DSeoYVR-ITA==\"><em>More</em></a>', 'Safety Starts at Home', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'safety-starts-at-home', '', '', '2015-09-21 16:00:15', '2015-09-21 22:00:15', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2355', '0', 'post', '', '0');
