INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2365', '14', '2015-09-21 16:02:17', '2015-09-21 22:02:17', 'A healthy breakfast doesn\'t require much effort, but with over 100 varieties of cereal in many grocery stores, the options can seem endless. Narrow down your selection by focusing on the following:\r\n\r\n<strong><img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-2359\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/superior-cereal-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"superior cereal\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />Whole grains</strong>- should be listed as the first ingredient.\r\n\r\n<strong>Sugar</strong>- is often added in multiple forms under different names like cane syrup or agave nectar. Avoid cereals with sugar in the first 3 ingredients. Dried fruit in cereal can be coated in sugar, so add fresh fruit instead. Look for less than 8 grams per serving.\r\n\r\n<strong>Fiber</strong>- look for at least 3 grams of dietary fiber. Whole grain flours and added fiber like inulin are not good indicators of quality fiber, so look for bran, wheat germ, or steel-cut oat cereals.\r\n\r\n<b>Fats- </b>avoid cereals with trans fat or more than 1 gram of saturated fat. Many granolas marketed as healthy choices are packed with unhealthy fat.\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; margin-bottom: .0001pt; background: white;\"></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nChildren\'s cereals are particularly bad culprits of artificial food dyes and sugar. Some kids\' cereals contain more than 40% sugar, more than a glazed doughnut!  Breakfast can jump-start the metabolism and fuel your brain and body with energy it needs to succeed. Breakfast eaters tend to be thinner than their counterparts and also make healthier decisions throughout the day. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=0011tvD9udTy8I7jbxUV6aMlIvh4_sKeAIGLbkomj7XrM3UiQ4bXrSsP5Bz3nkAcYVg9N6WEXDAjsnx0ttRBstAjQMxGxODFsGfyATnTkff_s7CgpNqrV12ZxDpDZbnX2yOegXAbnjOVg_RDTp_9Cppk-NvQ-PmJjFLr8dCUViszJ0ongbvrhVyaCKdy_B3TNbOwppAqN0A_dJ66eKZU_Fuqwz8-TBnykRQ_hsjvD2mdi5pGI6k-yufYaRXsO4zUXwbuysRzVXcKqk=&amp;c=3Neb1x8oCvXYazvdgjkHUftrjbnj96Yq_jxUtKLEbIumwUaXJ5w2iQ==&amp;ch=WXO2tZCDiMqrDGYp-D3oBS5nFNUpNxhxt5DmlMLPRB4DSeoYVR-ITA==\"><em>More</em></a>', 'Superior Cereal', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '2362-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-09-21 16:02:17', '2015-09-21 22:02:17', '', '2362', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/2362-autosave-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2368', '14', '2015-09-15 16:02:47', '2015-09-15 22:02:47', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Sell-By-dates.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-2356\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Sell-By-dates-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"Sell By dates\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>Is it worth our time to pay attention to the dates on food labels? There is no universally accepted system for food dating in the United States. In general, food is still safe to eat after the date marked on the product, but use your best judgement and always store food according to <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=0011tvD9udTy8I7jbxUV6aMlIvh4_sKeAIGLbkomj7XrM3UiQ4bXrSsP5Bz3nkAcYVgjbMenhlS6iKu52ZCCwSKTH955R73X3IFNgLvJKS9POYRr-O3UJToiwnasMiDhn9VQ6JSmUIbruKU4cY-5YyqcRmcKh0OfaTJ-z0skT-lPJuwibu6Q8pX_qHvuxBTxLt3d2t4boIbGbwwSDxWlJd5CSKmB_3N2HkC2vo-GvHJVaFKqmXXB8xHU1J8ruSNz6wH86z7yps_zgL_wx0GNIDueLTKyt9w18whOMEauzCy0lHk6VafNB-_lAC6AxLgC4-B1z05Pn1dAhbJqKG7jGREkVxTUvuoN5ytPdEnTNMiCVxuKlr3ui2UuJsk54t_33s0&amp;c=3Neb1x8oCvXYazvdgjkHUftrjbnj96Yq_jxUtKLEbIumwUaXJ5w2iQ==&amp;ch=WXO2tZCDiMqrDGYp-D3oBS5nFNUpNxhxt5DmlMLPRB4DSeoYVR-ITA==\">storage guidelines.</a>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Sell By</strong> dates are found on perishable foods like meat, seafood, and milk. These serve as a guide for stores to know how long to display the item, however the items are still safe past this date if you follow storage guidelines.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Best By, Use By, and Best if Used By</strong> dates are synonymous and voluntary from the manufacturer. These dates are not an issue of safety, but the date when the product is at its best quality, and are usually found on shelf-stable products like peanut butter and mustard.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Expires On</strong> dates are only found on infant formula and some baby foods, and are the only products the USDA regulates with regard to dating.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAccording to the USDA, eggs may be good within three to five weeks from your purchase date, and certain canned foods like soup and vegetables have an unopened shelf life of up to five years. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=0011tvD9udTy8I7jbxUV6aMlIvh4_sKeAIGLbkomj7XrM3UiQ4bXrSsP5Bz3nkAcYVgLgaupWmXZoimEO7VWl_oBZtA0NQ2aYWYFVbH-60hFzfozA_QSjzjK31NTccyvvQABJlWsghnmUtIABfAqmF6LVDDF8Rdty34RI_2q1Dnqzk7lMWfW5DPHwJ3E7uNKoINa2E6sHEblBpZXZ67jDoAWA4JIDLL9J9aS2PpAnwy8kNs0N26vxoJd445UY3cwP1yBoFvzicfzgCvxjlHw48_Deb35LDGnZNzyNn9IT-3bY76iLROiHrPZHfe2dLHWtX6TZLFk76G2_DZDe6pfxifFO6LQDA183lnukC7S1-VBmES_NH5SICNmg==&amp;c=3Neb1x8oCvXYazvdgjkHUftrjbnj96Yq_jxUtKLEbIumwUaXJ5w2iQ==&amp;ch=WXO2tZCDiMqrDGYp-D3oBS5nFNUpNxhxt5DmlMLPRB4DSeoYVR-ITA==\"><em>More</em></a>', 'Decoding Expiration Dates', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'decoding-expiration-dates', '', '', '2015-09-21 16:03:28', '2015-09-21 22:03:28', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2368', '0', 'post', '', '0');
