ding to the USDA, eggs may be good within three to five weeks from your purchase date, and certain canned foods like soup and vegetables have an unopened shelf life of up to five years. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=0011tvD9udTy8I7jbxUV6aMlIvh4_sKeAIGLbkomj7XrM3UiQ4bXrSsP5Bz3nkAcYVgLgaupWmXZoimEO7VWl_oBZtA0NQ2aYWYFVbH-60hFzfozA_QSjzjK31NTccyvvQABJlWsghnmUtIABfAqmF6LVDDF8Rdty34RI_2q1Dnqzk7lMWfW5DPHwJ3E7uNKoINa2E6sHEblBpZXZ67jDoAWA4JIDLL9J9aS2PpAnwy8kNs0N26vxoJd445UY3cwP1yBoFvzicfzgCvxjlHw48_Deb35LDGnZNzyNn9IT-3bY76iLROiHrPZHfe2dLHWtX6TZLFk76G2_DZDe6pfxifFO6LQDA183lnukC7S1-VBmES_NH5SICNmg==&amp;c=3Neb1x8oCvXYazvdgjkHUftrjbnj96Yq_jxUtKLEbIumwUaXJ5w2iQ==&amp;ch=WXO2tZCDiMqrDGYp-D3oBS5nFNUpNxhxt5DmlMLPRB4DSeoYVR-ITA==\"><em>More</em></a>', 'Decoding Expiration Dates', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '2368-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-21 16:03:28', '2015-09-21 22:03:28', '', '2368', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/2368-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2370', '14', '2015-09-22 16:03:48', '2015-09-22 22:03:48', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/stairs.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-2358\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/stairs-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"stairs\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>No time for a gym? Hit the stairs! Any indoor staircase, stadium bleachers, or even a hill will do. Climbing stairs improves leg strength for all major muscles in the lower body. It also improves bone density, aerobic lung capacity, and builds a stronger heart to deliver oxygen to muscles, making everyday tasks seem less tiring.\r\nThe weight loss benefits of stair climbing can significantly add up as well. Taking the stairs burns twice as many calories as walking, and 8-9 times more than taking an elevator. Climbing an additional two flights of stairs daily could result in a weight loss of 6 pounds in a year! As a safety consideration, start stair climbing slowly, take breaks when needed, and never run down stairs.\r\n\r\nThe CDC recommends adults get at least 2 hours and 30 minutes of moderate-intensity aerobic activity each week. Ten minute intervals of activity count toward that total, so start stepping! <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=0011tvD9udTy8I7jbxUV6aMlIvh4_sKeAIGLbkomj7XrM3UiQ4bXrSsP5Bz3nkAcYVgoxZHmIaqcRAJ4lcwKx-4nImdKGhZQ-sWHSfgj8DqJApFV87y7vpSFv8Rh7pETc9Ma58fvrAmoM32vFlCYCtvKhZfAAPcUHYLGqeuTuTL_pNwH3CqVvFm7KmXpDWUt6EHYEzau0SoEXWKCjhiDJeEJMTKWLf95Au_1nDqhr6xEIi2pbbvCEqHDN4R-5e1F5T-&amp;c=3Neb1x8oCvXYazvdgjkHUftrjbnj96Yq_jxUtKLEbIumwUaXJ5w2iQ==&amp;ch=WXO2tZCDiMqrDGYp-D3oBS5nFNUpNxhxt5DmlMLPRB4DSeoYVR-ITA==\"><em>More</em></a>', 'Steps, Stairs, and Stadiums', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'steps-stairs-and-stadiums', '', '', '2015-09-21 16:04:23', '2015-09-21 22:04:23', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2370', '0', 'post', '', '0');
