INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2385', '14', '2015-10-12 08:42:20', '2015-10-12 14:42:20', '<em><a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/healthy-tea.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-2379\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/healthy-tea-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"healthy tea\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>The Benefits of Tea </em>\r\n\r\nThe consumption of tea is on the rise and the health benefits could be to credit. True teas like green, black, and white tea come only from the Camellia sinensis plant and contain caffeine. The high concentrations of antioxidants and polyphenols in these teas may promote stronger bones, lower cholesterol, and reduce the risk of certain cancers.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Green tea</strong> has the highest concentration of EGCG, an antioxidant that may improve brain function, fight inflammation, prevent cancer, and boost immunity.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Black tea</strong> contains 2-3 times more caffeine than green tea but fewer polyphenols due to the oxidation process that turns the tea leaves black. It has antibacterial properties associated with fighting cavities and bad breath, and additionally may reduce the risk of stroke.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>White tea</strong> is the least processed of all teas leaving it with the most polyphenols and cancer-fighting powers of any tea. Because of its purity, white teas tend to be more expensive.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nHerbal tea does not come from the same Camellia sinensis plant as true teas and is often not considered \"tea\" in other countries. Herbal teas are instead derived from fruit, roots, flowers, and spices of non-tea plants. Most herbal teas are caffeine free and provide health benefits as well. <a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001PboQc0qUVyji43QGlZipBEpBwr1EVVWeHQ44fHxt3DpbN_gRoEx921cAdGyaKwsM3ECc0rgayVWTi4ktlWclXl8N82sXZ4k2UpoJYZpycSRNaxvEoSVvJr7eqXS4gjRKf_sWcllN0krv3Yeb2AkpNdcPRiDm7GYK-i7eLrPzk7252oFSVj54cjVo-sJhAmXLyBq72VR1gNCfmNLiXHkjGFz7jENEkZur&amp;c=5aH9Yz5McRf1Ar-uaa_atp7q0U5kWxYtWO0XEch4lqI-Ayq0juJtEg==&amp;ch=F6TqsZ750kKJCkNMVKTvqYLQpmI4Xq_cYmD8dEsTBUhA1T_TkO4XmQ==\"><em>More</em></a>', 'A Cup of Good Health', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'a-cup-of-good-health', '', '', '2015-10-22 08:43:13', '2015-10-22 14:43:13', '', '0', 'http://www.sterling-wellness.com/?p=2385', '0', 'post', '', '0');
