INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('2387', '14', '2015-10-18 08:43:40', '2015-10-18 14:43:40', '<a href=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Oh-My-Omega.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-2381\" src=\"http://www.sterling-wellness.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Oh-My-Omega-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"Oh My Omega\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>Fatty acids are important for nearly every system of the body to function optimally. These nutrients play roles in brain function, vision, heart health, joint mobility and fetal development. When it comes to healthy fat, omega 3s are among the best.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Omega 3</strong> is a more common term for essential fatty acids EPA, DHA, and ALA. These are naturally occurring in fatty fish like salmon, flax seed, and wheat germ.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Omega 6</strong>, or linoleic acid, is found commonly in fast food, frozen entrees, and high calorie snacks. Ideally, you should get twice as much Omega 6 as Omega 3, but most American diets provide up to 15 times more, causing a skewed ratio that negates any health benefits.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Omega 9</strong> is a non-essential fatty acid produced by the body when there is enough of Omega 3 and 6 fatty acids. Omega 9 is found naturally in many nuts like pecans, cashews, almonds, pistachios and macadamias.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nBefore taking a fish oil or omega 3 supplement, talk to your doctor about specific recommendations or warnings.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001PboQc0qUVyji43QGlZipBEpBwr1EVVWeHQ44fHxt3DpbN_gRoEx921cAdGyaKwsMI0AVVD6QLBQRw4juBgP4apVC4PPCeOyg0cRnFxy5PQYMiGBe7geVW0-uToAse6kJqJJ0yK_N-_bGsGKRLWfK2vInJ0HEQzC3xu2l3jleESSfhkA7Syg4znNGFZ1vPC9KMMfW5mpbR40l1bvhPsWQe4E--8FHlhK4wR3h40cbdFE=&amp;c=5aH9Yz5McRf1Ar-uaa_atp7q0U5kWxYtWO0XEch4lqI-Ayq0juJtEg==&amp;ch=F6TqsZ750kKJCkNMVKTvqYLQpmI4Xq_cYmD8dEsTBUhA1T_TkO4XmQ==\"><em>More</em></a>', 'Oh My Omega ', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'oh-my-omega', '', '', 